{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Cain and Abel

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 4}Adam lay with his wife Eve and she became pregnant and gave birth to Cain, and she said, \uc1\u8216*I have created a man with the help of the {\scaps {\super\cf2\fs24 1}Lord}!\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 2}She also gave birth to his brother Abel. Abel was a shepherd, while Cain was a farmer.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}In the course of time Cain brought some of the ground\uc1\u8217*s produce as an offering to the {\scaps Lord}. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Abel too brought some of the choicest animals of his flock and sacrificed their fat pieces. The {\scaps Lord} looked with approval on Abel and his offering {\super\cf2\fs24 5}but he could not receive Cain and his offering with approval.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
Cain burned with anger and his face fell. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}So the {\scaps Lord} said to Cain, \uc1\u8216*Why are you angry and why do you scowl? {\super\cf2\fs24 7}If you do what is right and good, can\uc1\u8217*t you hold your head up high? But if you do wrong, sin crouches at the door and longs to have you, but you must master it.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Cain said to his brother Abel, \uc1\u8216*Let us go into the field.\uc1\u8217* While they were there, Cain attacked his brother and killed him.
