{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Abram\uc1\u8217*s vision

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 15}After these things God spoke to Abram in a vision saying, \uc1\u8216*Do not be afraid, Abram, I am your shield. Your reward will be exceedingly great.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 2}But Abram said, \uc1\u8216*Lord {\scaps God}, what can you give me? I am childless, and the person who will be possessor of my house is Eliezer of Damascus, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}to me you have given no offspring, and, so a slave born in my house is my heir.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 4}The word of the {\scaps Lord} came to him, \uc1\u8216*This man will not be your heir, but a child of your own will be your heir.\uc1\u8217*
