{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Abram said, \uc1\u8216*Lord {\scaps God}, how will I know that I will inherit it?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}The {\scaps Lord} said to him, \uc1\u8216*Bring me a heifer of three years old, and a she-goat of three years old, and a ram of three years old, and a turtle dove, and a young pigeon.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Abram brought him all these, and divided them in the middle, and laid each half over against the other; but the birds he did not divide. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}The birds of prey came down upon the carcasses, but Abram drove them away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}When the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell upon Abram, and a horror of great darkness fell on him. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}The {\scaps Lord} said to Abram, \uc1\u8216*Know certainly that your descendants will be foreigners in a land that is not theirs, and will be slaves there; and they will be held there for four hundred years. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}But I will judge that nation, whom they will serve, and afterward they will come out with many goods. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}But you will go to your fathers in peace; you will be buried in a good old age. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}In the fourth generation they return here again; for the iniquity of the Amorite is not yet full.\uc1\u8217*
