{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Hagar and Ishmael

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 16}Now Sarai, Abram\uc1\u8217*s wife, had borne him no children, but she had an Egyptian slave-girl whose name was Hagar. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Sarai said to Abram, \uc1\u8216*the {\scaps Lord} has denied me children; Take my slave-girl; maybe I will obtain children by her.\uc1\u8217* Then Abram listened to her {\super\cf2\fs24 3}so she took Hagar the Egyptian, her slave-girl, after Abram had lived for ten years in the land of Canaan, and gave her to Abram her husband to be his wife {\super\cf2\fs24 4}and Abram lay with Hagar, and she conceived. When she saw that she had conceived, she looked with contempt on her mistress.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Sarai complained to Abram, \uc1\u8216*May the wrong I suffer be on you! I myself gave my slave-girl to you; and now that she sees that she has conceived, I am despised by her; may the {\scaps Lord} judge between me and you.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But Abram said to Sarai, \uc1\u8216*Your maid-servant is in your power, do to her whatever seems right to you.\uc1\u8217* Then Sarai ill-treated her so that she fled from her presence.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}The messenger of the {\scaps Lord} found her by a spring of water in the wilderness, by the spring in the way to Shur. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}He said, \uc1\u8216*Hagar, Sarai\uc1\u8217*s slave-girl, where have you come from? And where are you going?\uc1\u8217* She said, \uc1\u8216*I am fleeing from the presence of mistress Sarai.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Then the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} said to her, \uc1\u8216*Return to your mistress and submit yourself to her authority.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Moreover the messenger of the {\scaps Lord} said to her, \uc1\u8216*I will make your descendants so many that they can not be numbered because they are so numerous.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 11}The messenger of the {\scaps Lord} also said to her, \uc1\u8216*You are pregnant, and will have a son; you must call him Ishmael God hears, because the {\scaps Lord} has heard of your ill-treatment.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}He shall be like a wild donkey,
