{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 29}When the time drew near for Jacob to die, he called his son Joseph and said to him, \uc1\u8216*If now you will do me a favour, put your hand under my thigh and swear that you will act kindly and faithfully with me. Do not bury me, I beg of you, in Egypt; {\super\cf2\fs24 30}but when I lie down to sleep with my ancestors, carry, me out of Egypt and bury me in their burying-place.\uc1\u8217* Joseph replied, \uc1\u8216*I will do as you have requested.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 31}Jacob said, \uc1\u8216*Give me your oath\uc1\u8217*; so Joseph gave him his oath; and Israel bowed toward the head of the bed. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 48}Now after these things, Joseph was told, \uc1\u8216*Your father is sick.\uc1\u8217* So he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and Ephraim. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}When Jacob was told, \uc1\u8216*Your son Joseph has come to you.\uc1\u8217* Jacob rallied his strength and sat up on the bed. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Then Jacob said to Joseph, \uc1\u8216*God Almighty appeared to me at Luz in the land of Canaan, and blessed me, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}and said to me, \uc1\u8220*I will make you fruitful, and numerous, and I will make of you a company of peoples, and will give this land to your descendants after you for an everlasting possession.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Now your two sons, who were born to you in the land of Egypt before I came to you into Egypt will be mine just as Reuben and Simeon are mine. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But your offspring, which you father after them, will be yours. Their inheritance will come from their older brothers. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}As for me, when I came from Paddan, Rachel died to my sorrow in the land of Canaan on the way, some distance from Ephrath: and I buried her there in the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem).\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}When Israel saw Joseph\uc1\u8217*s sons, he said, \uc1\u8216*Who are these?\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 9}And Joseph said to his father, \uc1\u8216*They are my sons, whom God has given me here.\uc1\u8217* Israel said, Bring them, I pray you, to me, and I will bless them. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Now the eyes of Israel were dim for age, so that he could not see. So Joseph brought them near to him; and he kissed them, and embraced them. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Israel said to Joseph, \uc1\u8216*I had not thought to see your face; and now God has let me see your offspring as well.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Joseph took them from his father\uc1\u8217*s lap, and bowed with his face to the earth.
