So the woman waited and nursed her son until she weaned him. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}When she had weaned him, she took him up with her, together with a three-year-old bullock and a bushel of flour and a skin of wine, and brought him to the house of the {\scaps Lord} in Shiloh. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}They slew the bullock and Hannah brought the lad to Eli. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}She said, \uc1\u8216*Oh, sir, by your life, I am the woman who stood near you here, praying fervently to the {\scaps Lord}. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}This is the lad regarding whom I was fervently praying, and the {\scaps Lord} has granted me my petition which I asked of him. {\super\cf2\fs24 28}Now, I on my part have given him to the {\scaps Lord}; as long as he lives he is given to the {\scaps Lord}.\uc1\u8217* So she left him there before the {\scaps Lord}. 
