{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}So Elkanah went to Ramah. But the lad was ministering to the {\scaps Lord} in the presence of Eli the priest. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Now the sons of Eli were base scoundrels; they had no regard for the {\scaps Lord}, {\super\cf2\fs24 13}nor for what was justly due to the priest from the people. Whenever a man offered a sacrifice, the priest\uc1\u8217*s servant would come, while the meat was boiling, with a three-pronged fork in his hand, {\super\cf2\fs24 14}and would strike into the pot or the kettle or the basin or the dish. All that the fork brought up the priest would take for himself. So they did to all the Israelites who came to sacrifice to the {\scaps Lord} in Shiloh. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Moreover before they burned the fat, the priest\uc1\u8217*s servant used to come and say to the man who was making the offering, \uc1\u8216*Give me meat to roast for the priest; for he will not take from you boiled flesh, but raw.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Should the man, however, say to him, \uc1\u8216*First you should burn the fat, then take as much as you desire,\uc1\u8217* he would reply, \uc1\u8216*No, you must give it at once or else I will take it by force.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 17}The sin of the young men was very great before the {\scaps Lord}, for the men had contempt for the offering of the {\scaps Lord}. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}And Samuel continued ministering before the {\scaps Lord} \uc1\u8211* a lad girded with a linen ephod. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}His mother used to make him a little robe and bring it to him from year to year, when she came up with her husband to offer the yearly sacrifice. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}And Eli would bless Elkanah and his wife and say, \uc1\u8216*The {\scaps Lord} repay you with offspring from this woman for the gift which she gave to the {\scaps Lord}.\uc1\u8217* Then they would return to their own home. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}And the {\scaps Lord} visited Hannah so that she conceived and bore three sons and two daughters. The child Samuel grew up before the {\scaps Lord}.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Now Eli was very old; and whenver he heard what his sons were doing to all Israel, how they lay with the women who did service at the door of the tent of meeting, {\super\cf2\fs24 23}he said to them, \uc1\u8216*Why do you do such things as these, which I hear from the mouth of all the people. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}No, my sons; for it is no good report that I hear the people of the {\scaps Lord} spreading abroad. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}If one man sin against another, God will mediate for him; but if a man sin against the {\scaps Lord}, who could act as mediator for him?\uc1\u8217* Notwithstanding they did not listen to the voice of their father, because the {\scaps Lord} desired to slay them. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}But the lad Samuel kept on growing larger and better in the estimation both of the {\scaps Lord} and of men.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 27}There came a man of God to Eli and said to him, \uc1\u8216*This is the {\scaps Lord}\uc1\u8217*s message: I revealed myself to your father\uc1\u8217*s house, when they were in Egypt servants to Pharaoh\uc1\u8217*s house, {\super\cf2\fs24 28}and I chose him from all the tribes of Israel to be my priest to go up to my altar to burn sacrifices, to bear an ephod before me, and I gave to your father\uc1\u8217*s house for food all the offerings of the Israelites made by fire. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}Why do you look with envious eyes on my sacrifices and offerings, and honour your sons above me in fattening yourselves with the first-fruits of all the offerings which the Israelites bring me?\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 30}Therefore the {\scaps Lord} the God of Israel says, \uc1\u8220*I had indeed thought that your house and the house of your father would walk before me forever,\uc1\u8221* but now the {\scaps Lord} says, \uc1\u8220*Far be it from me, for them who honour me I will honour, and they who despise me will be lightly esteemed. {\super\cf2\fs24 31}The days are quickly coming when I Will cut off your arm and the arm of your father\uc1\u8217*s house. {\super\cf2\fs24 32}You will look in affliction and enviously on all the prosperity which I will give Israel, and there will not be an old man in your house forever. {\super\cf2\fs24 33}The only one of you whom I do not cut off from my altar will be spared to weep out his eyes and to wear out his body, and all of your household will die by the sword of men. {\super\cf2\fs24 34}This will be the sign to you that will come upon your two sons, Hophni and Phinehas: on the same day both will die. {\super\cf2\fs24 35}And I will raise up for myself a faithful priest who will do according to that which is in my heart and in my desire, and I will build him an enduring house, and he will walk before my anointed forever. {\super\cf2\fs24 36}Anyone who is left in your house will come to do him obeisance for a piece of money or a loaf of bread, and will beg to be given in one of the priests\uc1\u8217* offices so that they may eat a morsel of bread.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217* 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}The child Samuel continued ministering before the {\scaps {\super\cf2\fs24 1}Lord} in the presence of Eli. The word of the {\scaps Lord} was rare in those days; there were no frequent visions. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Once at that time, when Eli was lying in his Samuel place \uc1\u8211* his eyes had begun to grow dim, so that he could not see \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 3}and while the lamp of God was still burning, and Samuel was lying in the temple of the {\scaps Lord} where the ark of God was, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}the {\scaps Lord} called, \uc1\u8216*Samuel! Samuel!\uc1\u8217* He said, \uc1\u8216*Here I am.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 5}He ran to Eli, and said, \uc1\u8216*Here I am; you called me.\uc1\u8217* But he said, \uc1\u8216*I didn\uc1\u8217*t call, lie down again.\uc1\u8217* So he went and lay down. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Then the {\scaps Lord} called yet again, \uc1\u8216*Samuel! Samuel!\uc1\u8217* And Samuel arose and went to Eli and said, \uc1\u8216*Here I am; you called me.\uc1\u8217* But he answered, \uc1\u8216*I didn\uc1\u8217*t call, my son. Lie down again.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Now Samuel did not yet know the {\scaps Lord} neither had the word of the {\scaps Lord} yet been revealed to him. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}So when the {\scaps Lord} called Samuel again the third time, he arose and went to Eli, and said, \uc1\u8216*Here I am; for you called me.\uc1\u8217* Then Eli realized that the {\scaps Lord} was calling the child. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}So Eli said to Samuel, \uc1\u8216*Go, lie down; and if you are called, say, \uc1\u8220*Speak, {\scaps Lord}, for your servant is listening.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221* So Samuel went and lay down in his place. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Then the {\scaps Lord} came, and stood there, and called as at other times, \uc1\u8216*Samuel! Samuel!\uc1\u8217* And Samuel said, \uc1\u8216*Speak; for your servant is listening.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 11}And the {\scaps Lord} said to Samuel, \uc1\u8216*See, I am about to do such a thing in Israel, that the ears of everyone who hears it will ring. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}In that day I will perform toward Eli all that I have spoken against his house from beginning to end. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}For I have told him that I will judge his house forever, for the guilt which he knew, in that his sons were blaspheming God and he did not restrain them. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore I have sworn to the house of Eli that the guilt of Eli\uc1\u8217*s house will not be expiated with sacrifice nor offering forever.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}And Samuel lay there until the morning. Then he rose early in the morning and opened the doors of the house of the {\scaps Lord}. Samuel was afraid to make the known the vision to Eli. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}But Eli called Samuel and said, \uc1\u8216*Samuel, my son.\uc1\u8217* He said, \uc1\u8216*I am here.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 17}He said, \uc1\u8216*What is the thing that the {\scaps Lord} has spoken to you? Hide nothing from me. May God do to you whatever he will, if you conceal from me a word of all that he spoke to you.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 18}So Samuel told him everything; and hid nothing from him. And Eli said, \uc1\u8216*It is the {\scaps Lord}; let him do what seems good to him.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}And Samuel grew, and the {\scaps Lord} was with him and let none of his words fall to the ground. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}All Israel from Dan even to Beersheba knew that Samuel was established as a prophet of the {\scaps Lord}. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}And the {\scaps Lord} again appeared in Shiloh, for the {\scaps Lord} revealed himself to Samuel,  {\cf1 4}and the word of Samuel came to all Israel.
