 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Then Achish called to David and said to him, \uc1\u8216*As the {\scaps Lord} lives, you are upright, and it is my desire that you should go out and fight with me, for I have found no evil in you from the time that you came to me to the present, but you are not regarded favourably by the lords. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore now return and go in peace, so that you do nothing to displease the lords of the Philistines.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 8}David said to Achish, \uc1\u8216*But what have I done? What have you found in your servant fromt the day that I entered into your service to this day, that I may not go and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 9}And Achish answered David, \uc1\u8216*I know that you are as good in my sight as a Messenger of God, but the commanders of the Philistines have said, \uc1\u8220*He must not go up with us to the battle.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Therefore now rise early in the morning, with the servants of your lord who came with you, and go to the place where I have stationed you, and do not entertain any evil design in your heart, for you are good in my sight, but rise early in the morning and as soon as it is light, depart.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 11}So David rose early, together with his men, to depart in the morning to return to the land of the Philistines. The Philistines went up to Jezreel. 
