{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}When he had brought him down, there they were spread over all the land, eating and drinking and dancing, on account of all the great spoil that they had taken from the land of the Philistines and from the land of Judah. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And David struck them from twilight to the following evening in order to destroy them completely. None escaped except four hundred young men, who rode on camels and fled. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}David recovered all the people whom the Amalekites had taken, and David rescued his two wives. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}There was nothing missing, either small or great, sons or daughters, spoil or anything that they had taken to themselves \uc1\u8211* David brought it all back. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}He took all the flocks and the herds and drove those animals before the people, and they said, \uc1\u8216*This is David\uc1\u8217*s spoil.\uc1\u8217*
