{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Now when David came to the two hundred men, who had been too faint to follow him, so that he had to leave them behind at the Wadi Besor, they went out to meet David, and the people who were with him. When they came near to the people, he saluted them. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Then all the wicked and base scoundrels among the men who went with David began to say, \uc1\u8216*Because they did not go with us, we will not give them any of the spoil that we have recovered, except to each, his wife and his children, that he may take them away and depart.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 23}But David said, No! My brothers, you must not do this with that which the {\scaps Lord} has given us \uc1\u8211* after he has preserved us and delivered the marauding band that came against us into our hand. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}Who will give heed to you in this matter? For:
