{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs48 The place of Wisdom in Popular Esteem
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}The following illustrations of wisdom came under {\super\cf2\fs24 14}my notice, and it greatly impressed me. There wasa small and thinly garrisoned town, which a power-ful king came and invested by building huge {\super\cf2\fs24 15}siege-works against it. But there happened to bein it a man, poor indeed, but endowed with a wisdomwhich enabled him to save the town. Not a soul, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}However, remembered this poor man. So, me-thought, wisdom of a poor man is held in contempt, and hiswords are not listened to. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Better wise words that are heard in quiet
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Than the shrieking of one who is lord among fools.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Better is wisdom than weapons of war,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
