{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Purchase
 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 32}The message which came to Jeremiah from Jehovah{\super\cf2\fs24 1}in the tenth year of Zedekiah, king of Judah, which {\super\cf2\fs24 2}was in the eighteenth year of Nebuchadrezzar. At thattime the forces of the king of Babylon were investingJerusalem, and Jeremiah the prophet was confined to {\super\cf2\fs24 3}the guard-house of the royal palace, where Zedekiah theking had shut him up on account of his propheticpreaching. "What do you mean," he had demanded,"by an announcement of this kind: \uc1\u8217*Thus saithJehovah, Depend upon it, I will give this city into thehands of the king of Babylon, and he shall take it. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Nor shall Zedekiah, king of Judah, escape the hands ofthe Chaldeans; he will assuredly be delivered into thehands of the king of Babylon. He shall speak to him {\super\cf2\fs24 5}face to face, and see him eye to eye; and he shall bringZedekiah to Babylon, where he will remain till I visithim. Though you fight with the Chaldeans you shallhave no success.\uc1\u8217*"
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Now there came to Jeremiah the following message {\super\cf2\fs24 7}from Jehovah: "Hanamel, the son of thine uncleShallum, is about to pay thee a visit, to request thee tobuy the land he holds at Anathoth; and he will urgethat, as thou art the next of kin, it is thy privilege and {\super\cf2\fs24 8}duty to receive it." And so it happened: my cousinHanamel paid me in the guard-house the visit Jehovahhad intimated, and said: "I want you to buy the landI possess at Anathoth; for you are the legal heir, andit is your duty to secure it \uc1\u8211* so buy it for yourself."Then I recognised that the message I had received was {\super\cf2\fs24 9}really from Jehovah. So I bought the land at Anathothfrom my cousin Hanamel, and I weighed out the money {\super\cf2\fs24 10}to him \uc1\u8211* seventeen silver shekels. Then I signed thedeed and sealed it, took witnesses, and paid him the {\super\cf2\fs24 11}money in full. I then took the purchase-deed\uc1\u8211*the one which was sealed and the one which was open\uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}and gave it to Baruch, the son of Neriah, the son ofMachesiah, in the presence of my cousin Hanamel, andof the witnesses who had signed the purchase-deed {\super\cf2\fs24 13}and of all the Jews in the guard-house. In theirpresence I then gave these instructions to Baruch: {\super\cf2\fs24 14}"Thus saith Jehovah of Hosts, the God of Israel:Take these deeds \uc1\u8211* this purchase deed which is sealedand this deed which is open \uc1\u8211* and put them in anearthenware jar, so that they may be preserved for a {\super\cf2\fs24 15}long time to come. For thus saith Jehovah of Hosts,the God of Israel: A time is coming when houses andfields and vineyards shall again be bought in this land."
\par}

