{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 31}In the thirty seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin,king of Judah, in the twenty-fifth day of the twelfthmonth, Evil-merodach, in the year of his accession tothe throne of Babylon, restored Jehoiachin, king of {\super\cf2\fs24 32}Judah, to favour, liberated him from prison, engagedhim in friendly intercourse, and gave him precedenceover the (other) kings who were (detained) with him {\super\cf2\fs24 33}in Babylon. He also changed his prison dress, and he {\super\cf2\fs24 34}dined at the royal table to the very end of his life. Aperpetual allowance, which was disbursed daily, wasassigned him by the king of Babylon, and he continuedto enjoy it all his life up to the day that he died.
