All desolate now are her gates,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And her priest are in sorrow.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Her virgins are dragged away far;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
She herself is in bitterness.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Supreme her foes are now,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And her enemies triumph.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
The Lord hath afflicted her sore
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
For her manifold sins.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Gone are her little once captive
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
In front of the foe.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}The glory is vanished clean
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
From the daughter of Zion.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Her princes are like unto harts
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
That can nowhere find pasture;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
All feeble they move on their way
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
With pursuers behind them.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Jerusalem calleth to mind
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
The days of her travail,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
When into the hands of the foemen
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Her people fell helpless.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
The mocking foe feasted his eyes
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
On her sore desolation.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Jerusalem hath grievously sinned,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And so she hath fallen.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
All they that honoured despise her
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
At sight of her nakedness.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
She meanwhile groaneth and moaneth
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And turneth her backward.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Her filthiness clung to her skirts;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
She became all abhorrent.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
To the future she gave not a thought,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
So her fall was appalling.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Behold, O Lord, what I suffer
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
From the insolent foe.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}The foeman hath stretched out his hand
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
To secure all her treasures.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
The hearthen she saw enter in
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And her temple profane\uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Even those Thou forbadest to mix
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
With Thine own congregation.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Her people all groan and moan
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
In their search after bread.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
They have given away their treasures
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
For food to revive them.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Behold, O Jehovah, and see
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
How abject am I.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}All ye that pass by, I appeal to you,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Look ye and see;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Has there ever been sorrow like mine,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Like that dealt out to me,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
When the Lord, in His fierce indignation,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Did put me to grief?
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}He hurled down fire from on high;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
It hath entered my bones.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
A net He hath spread for my feet;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
He hath turned me backward.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Faint He hath left me and desolate
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
All the day long.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}A watch He hath kept on my sins;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And into a yoke
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For my neck with His hands He hath twined them.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Then, crippling my strength,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
He hath given me into the hands
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Of a foe irresistible.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}The Lord hath hurled to the ground
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
All the strong men within me.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
He hath summoned a festal assembly
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
To crush my young (warriors).
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
The Lord in His wine-press hath trodden
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
The daughter of Judah.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}For these things I weep without creasing;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Mine eyes stream with tears;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For none have I now by my side
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
To refresh me and comfort me.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
My children are clean distraught,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
For the foe hath prevailed.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Zion hath stretched forth her hands;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
There is no one to comfort her.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
On her neighbours the Lord laid a charge
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
To be hostile to Jacob;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And now is Jerusalem vile
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And abhorrent among them.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}As for the Lord, He is just;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
For the rebel was I.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Ye peoples all, hear, I entreat you,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And look on my sorrow.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Together my maidens and youths
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Are gone into captivity.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}I called upon those that had loved me,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
But they have deceived me.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
In the city my priest and mine elders
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Have perished of hunger.
