 {\cf1 14}A day is coming for the {\scaps {\super\cf2\fs24 1}Lord}, when your plundered possessions will be divided while you watch. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}And all the nations will gather to Jerusalem, to fight against it. The city will be taken and the houses plundered and the women raped. Half of the city will go into captivity, and the rest of the people left in the ruins. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Then the {\scaps Lord} will go forth and fight against these nations, as once he fought in the day of battle. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}On that day his feet will stand on the Mount of Olives, (which is opposite Jerusalem, on the east). The Mount of Olives will be split into halves, from east to west, by an exceedingly great valley; and half of the mountain will slide northwards and half southwards. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}You will escape through my valley \uc1\u8211* the valley between the hills will extend as far as Azel, and you will flee as you fled from before the earthquake, in the days of Uzziah king of Judah. But the {\scaps Lord} your God will come, and all the holy ones with him.
