{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*You are salt for the world. But if salt becomes tasteless, how can it be made salty again? It is no longer good for anything, but is thrown away, and trampled underfoot. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}It is you who are the light of the world. A town that stands on a hill cannot be hidden. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}People do not light a lamp and put it under a basket, but on the lamp-stand, where it gives light to everyone in the house. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Let your light so shine before the eyes of others so that, seeing your good actions, they will praise your Father who is in heaven.
