{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*We have not more than five loaves and two fish,\uc1\u8217* they answered. \uc1\u8216*Unless indeed we are to go and buy food for all these people.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 14}(For the men among them were about five thousand.) \uc1\u8216*Get them seated in companies,\uc1\u8217* was his reply, \uc1\u8216*about fifty in each.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 15}This they did, and got all the people seated. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Taking the five loaves and the two fish, Jesus looked up to heaven and said the blessing over them. Then he broke them in pieces, and gave them to his disciples to set before the people. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Everyone had sufficient to eat, and what was left of the broken pieces was picked up \uc1\u8211* twelve baskets.
