 {\cf1 13}Before the Passover Festival began, Jesus knew that the time had come for him to leave the world and go to the Father. He had loved those who were his own in the world, and he loved them to the last. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}The devil had already put the thought of betraying Jesus into the mind of Judas Iscariot, the son of Simon; {\super\cf2\fs24 3}and at supper, Jesus \uc1\u8211* although knowing that the Father had put everything into his hands, and that he had come from God, and was to return to God \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Rose from his place, and, taking off his upper garments, tied a towel round his waist. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}He then poured some water into the basin, and began to wash the disciples\uc1\u8217* feet, and to wipe them with the towel which was tied round him. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}When he came to Simon Peter, Peter said, \uc1\u8216*You, Master! Are you going to wash my feet?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8216*You do not understand now what I am doing,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*but you will learn by and by.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8216*You will never wash my feet!\uc1\u8217* exclaimed Peter. \uc1\u8216*Unless I wash you,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*you have nothing in common with me.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8216*Then, Master, not my feet only,\uc1\u8217* exclaimed Simon Peter, \uc1\u8216*but also my hands and my head.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*He who has bathed,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*has no need to wash, unless it be his feet, but is altogether clean; and you,\uc1\u8217* he said to the disciples, \uc1\u8216*are clean, yet not all of you.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 11}For he knew who was going to betray him, and that was why he said \uc1\u8220*You are not all clean.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}When he had washed their feet, and had put on his upper garments and taken his place, he spoke to them again. \uc1\u8216*Do you understand what I have been doing to you?\uc1\u8217* he asked. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*You yourselves call me \uc1\u8220*the teacher\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*the Master\uc1\u8221*, and you are right, for I am both. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}If I, then \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*the Master\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*the teacher\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* have washed your feet, you also ought to wash one another\uc1\u8217*s feet; {\super\cf2\fs24 15}for I have given you an example, so that you may do just as I have done to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}In truth I tell you, a servant is not greater than their master, neither is a messenger greater than the one who sends them. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Now that you know these things, happy are you if you do them. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}I am not speaking about all of you. I know whom I have chosen; but this is in fulfilment of the words of scripture \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*He that is eating my bread has lifted his heel against me.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 19}For the future I will tell you of things before they take place, so that, when they take place, you may believe that I am what I am. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}In truth I tell you, the one who receives anyone that I send receives me; and the person who receives me receives him who sent me.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 21}After saying this, Jesus was much troubled, and said solemnly, \uc1\u8216*In truth I tell you that it is one of you who will betray me.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 22}The disciples looked at one another, wondering whom he meant. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Next to Jesus, in the place on his right hand, was one of his disciples, whom he loved. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}So Simon Peter made signs to that disciple, and whispered, \uc1\u8216*Tell me who it is that he means.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Being in this position, that disciple leant back on Jesus\uc1\u8217* shoulder, and asked him, \uc1\u8216*Who is it, Master?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 26}\uc1\u8216*It is the one,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*to whom I will give a piece of bread after dipping it in the dish.\uc1\u8217* And, when Jesus had dipped the bread, he took it and gave it to Judas, the son of Simon Iscariot; {\super\cf2\fs24 27}and it was then, after he had received it, that Satan took possession of him. So Jesus said to him, \uc1\u8216*Do at once what you are going to do.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 28}But no one at the table understood why he said this to Judas. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}Some thought that, as Judas kept the purse, Jesus meant that he was to buy some things needed for the Festival, or to give something to the poor. {\super\cf2\fs24 30}After taking the piece of bread, Judas went out immediately; and it was night.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 31}When Judas had gone out, Jesus said, \uc1\u8216*Now the Son of Man has been exalted, and God has been exalted through him; {\super\cf2\fs24 32}and God will exalt him with himself \uc1\u8211* yes, he will exalt him forthwith. {\super\cf2\fs24 33}My children, I am to be with you but a little while longer. You will look for me; and what I said to the people \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*You cannot come where I am going\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* I now say to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 34}I give you a new commandment \uc1\u8211* love one another; love one another as I have loved you. {\super\cf2\fs24 35}It is by this that everyone will recognise you as my disciples \uc1\u8211* by your loving one another.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 36}\uc1\u8216*Where are you going, Master?\uc1\u8217* asked Peter. \uc1\u8216*I am going where you cannot now follow me,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*but you will follow me later.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 37}\uc1\u8216*Why cannot I follow you now, Master?\uc1\u8217* asked Peter. \uc1\u8216*I will lay down my life for you.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 38}\uc1\u8216*Will you lay down your life for me?\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus. \uc1\u8216*In truth I tell you, the cock will not crow until you have disowned me three times.  {\cf1 14}Do not let your hearts be troubled. Believe in God; believe also in me. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}In my Father\uc1\u8217*s Home there are many dwellings. If it had not been so, I should have told you, for I am going to prepare a place for you. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}And, since I go and prepare a place for you, I will return and take you to be with me, so that you may be where I am; {\super\cf2\fs24 4}and you know the way to the place where I am going.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*We do not know where you are going, Master,\uc1\u8217* said Thomas. \uc1\u8216*So how can we know the way?\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Jesus answered, \uc1\u8216*I am the way, and the truth, and the life; no one ever comes to the Father except through me. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}If you had recognised me, you would have known my Father also; for the future you will recognise him, indeed you have already seen him.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8216*Master, show us the Father,\uc1\u8217* said Philip, \uc1\u8216*and we will be satisfied.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}\uc1\u8216*Have I been all this time among you,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus, \uc1\u8216*and yet you, Philip, have not recognised me? The person who has seen me has seen the Father, how can you say, then, \uc1\u8220*Show us the Father\uc1\u8221*? {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Don\uc1\u8217*t you believe that I am in union with the Father, and the Father with me? In giving you my teaching I am not speaking on my own authority; but the Father himself, always in union with me, does his own work. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Believe me,\uc1\u8217* he said to them all, \uc1\u8216*when I say that I am in union with the Father and the Father with me, or else believe me because of the work itself. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}In truth I tell you, the person who believes in me will themselves do the work that I am doing; and they will do greater work still, because I am going to the Father. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Whatever you ask, in my name, I will do, so that the Father may be honoured in the Son. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}If you ask anything, in my name, I will do it. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}If you love me, you will lay my commands to heart, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}and I will ask the Father, and he will give you another helper, to be with you always \uc1\u8211* the Spirit of truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}The world cannot receive this Spirit, because it does not see him or recognise him, but you recognise him, because he is always with you, and is within you. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}I will not leave you bereaved; I will come to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}In a little while the world will see me no more, but you will still see me; because I am living, you will be living also. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}At that time you will recognise that I am in union with the Father, and you with me, and I with you. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}It is they who have my commands and lays them to heart who loves me; and the person who loves me will be loved by my Father, and I will love them, and will reveal myself to them.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 22}\uc1\u8216*What has happened, Master,\uc1\u8217* said Judas (not Judas Iscariot), \uc1\u8216*that you are going to reveal yourself to us, and not to the world?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8216*Whoever loves me,\uc1\u8217* Jesus answered, \uc1\u8216*will lay my message to heart; and my Father will love him, and we will come to him and make our home with him. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}The person who does not love me will not lay my message to heart; and the message to which you are listening is not my own, but comes from the Father who sent me. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}I have told you all this while still with you, {\super\cf2\fs24 26}but the helper \uc1\u8211* the Holy Spirit whom the Father will send in my name \uc1\u8211* will teach you all things, and will recall to your minds all that I have said to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}Peace be with you! My own peace I give you. I do not give to you as the world gives. Do not let your hearts be troubled, or dismayed. {\super\cf2\fs24 28}You heard me say that I was going away and would return to you. Had you loved me, you would have been glad that I was going to the Father, because the Father is greater than I. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}And this I have told you now before it happens, so that, when it does happen, you may still believe in me. {\super\cf2\fs24 30}I will not talk with you much more, for the Spirit that is ruling the world is coming. He has nothing in common with me; {\super\cf2\fs24 31}but he is coming so that the world may see that I love the Father, and that I do as the Father commanded me. Come, let us be going. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 15}\uc1\u8216*I am the true vine, and my Father is the vine-grower. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Any unfruitful branch in me he takes away, and he cleanses every fruitful branch, so that it may bear more fruit. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}You are already clean because of the message that I have given you. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Remain united to me, and I will remain united to you. As a branch cannot bear fruit by itself, unless it remains united to the vine; no more can you, unless you remain united to me. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}I am the vine, you are the branches. If you remains united to me, while I remain united to you \uc1\u8211* you bear fruit plentifully; for you can do nothing apart from me. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}If anyone does not remain united to me, they are thrown away, as a branch would be, and withers up. Such branches are collected and thrown into the fire, and are burnt. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}If you remain united to me, and my teaching remains in your hearts, ask whatever you wish, and it will be yours. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}It is by your bearing fruit plentifully, and so showing yourselves my disciples, that my Father is honoured. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}As the Father has loved me, so have I loved you; remain in my love. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}If you lay my commands to heart, you will remain in my love; just as I have laid the Father\uc1\u8217*s commands to heart and remain in his love. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}I have told you all this so that my own joy may be yours, and that your joy may be complete. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}This is my command \uc1\u8211* love one another, as I have loved you. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}No one can give greater proof of love than by laying down their life for their friends. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}And you are my friends, if you do what I command you. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}I no longer call you \uc1\u8220*servants,\uc1\u8221* because a servant does not know what their master is doing; but I have given you the name of \uc1\u8220*friends,\uc1\u8221* because I made known to you everything that I learned from my Father. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}It wasn\uc1\u8217*t you who chose me, but I who chose you, and I appointed you to go and bear fruit \uc1\u8211* fruit that should remain, so that the Father might grant you whatever you ask in my name. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}I am giving you these commands that you may love one another. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}If the world hates you, you know that it has first hated me. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}If you belonged to the world, the world would love its own. Because you do not belong to the world, but I have chosen you out of the world \uc1\u8211* that is why the world hates you. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Remember what I said to you \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*A servant is not greater than their master.\uc1\u8221* If they have persecuted me, they will also persecute you; if they have laid my message to heart, they will lay yours to heart also. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}But they will do all this to you, because you believe in my name, for they do not know him who sent me. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}If I had not come and spoken to them, they would have had no sin to answer for; but as it is, they have no excuse for their sin. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}The person who hates me hates my Father also. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}If I had not done among them such work as no one else ever did, they would have had no sin to answer for; but, as it is, they have both seen and hated both me and my Father. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}And so is fulfilled what is said in their Law \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*They hated me without cause.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 26}But, when the helper comes, whom I will send to you from the Father \uc1\u8211* the Spirit of truth, who comes from the Father \uc1\u8211* will bear testimony to me; {\super\cf2\fs24 27}yes, and you also are to bear testimony, because you have been with me from the first.  {\cf1 16}\uc1\u8216*I have spoken to you in this way so that you may not falter. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}They will expel you from their synagogues; indeed the time is coming when anyone who kills you will think that they are making an offering to God. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}They will do this, because they have not learned to know the Father, or even me. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}But I have spoken to you of these things so that, when the time for them comes, you may remember that I told you about them myself. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}I did not tell you all this at first, because I was with you. But now I am to return to him who sent me; and yet not one of you asks me \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Where are you going?\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Although your hearts are full of sorrow at all that I have been saying to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Yet I am only telling you the truth; it is for your good that I should go away. For otherwise the helper will never come to you, but, if I leave you, I will send him to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}And he, when he comes, will bring conviction to the world as to sin, and as to righteousness, and as to judgment; {\super\cf2\fs24 9}as to sin, for people do not believe in me; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}as to righteousness, for I am going to the Father, and you will see me no longer; {\super\cf2\fs24 11}as to judgment, for the Spirit that is ruling this world has been condemned. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}I have still much to say to you, but you cannot bear it now. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Yet when he \uc1\u8211* The Spirit of truth \uc1\u8211* comes, he will guide you into all truth; for he will not speak on his own authority, but he will speak of all that he hears; and he will tell you of the things that are to come. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}He will honour me; because he will take of what is mine, and will tell it to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Everything that the Father has is mine; that is why I said that he takes of what is mine, and will tell it to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}In a little while you will no longer see me; and then in a little while you will see me indeed.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}At this some of his disciples said to one another, \uc1\u8216*What does he mean by saying to us \uc1\u8220*In a little while you will not see me, and then in a little while you will see me indeed\uc1\u8221*; and by saying \uc1\u8220*Because I am going to the Father\uc1\u8221*? {\super\cf2\fs24 18}What does he mean by \uc1\u8220*In a little while\uc1\u8221*?\uc1\u8217* they said. \uc1\u8216*We do not know what he is speaking about.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Jesus saw that they were wanting to ask him a question, and said, \uc1\u8216*Are you trying to find out from one another what I meant by saying \uc1\u8220*In a little while you will not see me; and then in a little while you will see me indeed\uc1\u8221*? {\super\cf2\fs24 20}In truth I tell you that you will weep and mourn, but the world will rejoice; you will suffer pain, but your pain will turn to joy. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}A woman in labour is in pain because her time has come; but no sooner is the child born, than she forgets her trouble in her joy that a child has been born into the world. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}You, in the same way, are sorry now; but I will see you again, and your hearts will rejoice, and no one will rob you of your joy. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}And at that time you will not ask me anything; in truth I tell you, if you ask the Father for anything, he will grant it to you in my name. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}So far you have not asked for anything, in my name; ask, and you will receive, so that your joy may be complete. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}I have spoken to you of all this in figures; a time is coming, however, when I will not speak any longer to you in figures, but will tell you about the Father plainly. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}You will ask, at that time, in my name; and I do not say that I will intercede with the Father for you; {\super\cf2\fs24 27}for the Father himself loves you, because you have loved me, and have believed that I came from the Father. {\super\cf2\fs24 28}I came out from the Father, and have come into the world; and now I am to leave the world, and go to the Father.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 29}\uc1\u8216*At last,\uc1\u8217* exclaimed the disciples, \uc1\u8216*you are using plain words and not speaking in figures at all. {\super\cf2\fs24 30}Now we are sure that you know everything, and need not wait for anyone to question you. This makes us believe that you did come from God.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 31}\uc1\u8216*Do you believe that already?\uc1\u8217* Jesus answered. {\super\cf2\fs24 32}\uc1\u8216*Listen! A time is coming \uc1\u8211* indeed it has already come \uc1\u8211* when you are to be scattered, each going his own way, and to leave me alone; and yet I am not alone, because the Father is with me. {\super\cf2\fs24 33}I have spoken to you in this way, so that in me you may find peace. In the world you will find trouble; yet, take courage! I have conquered the world.\uc1\u8217* 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 17}After saying this, Jesus raised his eyes heaven-wards, and said:
