 {\cf1 18}When Jesus had said this, he went out with his disciples and crossed the brook Kedron to a place where there was a garden, into which he and his disciples went. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}The place was well known to Judas, the betrayer, for Jesus and his disciples had often met there. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}So Judas, who had obtained the soldiers of the Roman garrison, and some police officers from the chief priests and the Pharisees, came there with lanterns, torches, and weapons. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Jesus, aware of all that was coming upon him, went to meet them, and said to them, \uc1\u8216*For whom are you looking?\uc1\u8217*
