{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*Jesus of Nazareth,\uc1\u8217* was their answer. \uc1\u8216*I am he,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus. (Judas, the betrayer, was also standing with them.) {\super\cf2\fs24 6}When Jesus said \uc1\u8220*I am he,\uc1\u8221* they drew back and fell to the ground. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}So he again asked for whom they were looking, and they answered, \uc1\u8216*Jesus of Nazareth.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8216*I have already told you that I am he,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*so, if it is for me that you are looking, let these people go.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 9}This was in fulfilment of his words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Of those whom you have given me I have not lost one.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}At this, Simon Peter, who had a sword with him, drew it, and struck the high priest\uc1\u8217*s servant, and cut off his right ear. The servant\uc1\u8217*s name was Malchus. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}But Jesus said to Peter, \uc1\u8216*Sheathe your sword. Should I not drink the cup which the Father has given me?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

