 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}So the soldiers of the garrison, with their commanding officer and the Jewish police, arrested Jesus and bound him, {\super\cf2\fs24 13}and took him first of all to Annas. Annas was the father-in-law of Caiaphas, who was high priest that year. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}It was Caiaphas who had counselled the religious authorities, that it was best that one person should die for the people. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Meanwhile Simon Peter followed Jesus, and so did another disciple. That disciple, being well-known to the high priest, went with Jesus into the high priest\uc1\u8217*s courtyard, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}while Peter stood outside by the door. Presently the other disciple \uc1\u8211* the one well-known to the high priest \uc1\u8211* went out and spoke to the portress, and brought Peter in. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}So the maidservant said to Peter, \uc1\u8216*Aren\uc1\u8217*t you also one of this man\uc1\u8217*s disciples?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*No, I am not,\uc1\u8217* he said. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}The servants and police officers were standing round a charcoal fire (which they had made because it was cold), and were warming themselves. Peter, too, was with them, standing and warming himself. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}The high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and about his teaching. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}\uc1\u8216*For my part,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*I have spoken to all the world openly. I always taught in some synagogue, or in the Temple Courts, places where everyone assembles, and I never spoke of anything in secret. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Why question me? Question those who have listened to me as to what I have spoken about to them. They must know what I said.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 22}When Jesus said this, one of the police officers, who was standing near, gave him a blow with his hand. \uc1\u8216*Do you answer the high priest like that?\uc1\u8217* he exclaimed. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u8216*If I said anything wrong, give evidence about it,\uc1\u8217* replied Jesus, \uc1\u8216*but if not, why do you strike me?\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 24}Annas sent him bound to Caiaphas the high priest. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Meanwhile Simon Peter was standing there, warming himself; so they said to him, \uc1\u8216*Aren\uc1\u8217*t you also one of his disciples?\uc1\u8217* Peter denied it. \uc1\u8216*No, I am not,\uc1\u8217* he said. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}One of the high priest\uc1\u8217*s servants, a relation of the man whose ear Peter had cut off, exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Didn\uc1\u8217*t I myself see you with him in the garden?\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 27}Peter again denied it; and at that moment a cock crowed.
