{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 28}From Caiaphas they took Jesus to the Government house. It was early in the morning. But they did not enter the Government house themselves, otherwise they might become defiled, and so be unable to eat the Passover. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}Therefore Pilate came outside to speak to them. \uc1\u8216*What charge do you bring against this man?\uc1\u8217* he asked. {\super\cf2\fs24 30}\uc1\u8216*If he had not been a criminal, we should not have given him up to you,\uc1\u8217* they answered. {\super\cf2\fs24 31}\uc1\u8216*Take him yourselves,\uc1\u8217* said Pilate, \uc1\u8216*and try him by your own Law.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*We have no power to put anyone to death,\uc1\u8217* the authorities replied \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 32}In fulfilment of what Jesus had said when indicating the death that he was destined to die. {\super\cf2\fs24 33}After that, Pilate went into the Government house again, and calling Jesus up, asked him, \uc1\u8216*Are you the king of the Jews?\uc1\u8217*
