{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8216*You would have no power over me at all,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*if it had not been given you from above; and, therefore, the man who betrayed me to you is guilty of the greater sin.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}This made Pilate anxious to release him; but the crowd shouted, \uc1\u8216*If you release that man, you are no friend of the Emperor! Anyone who makes himself out to be a king is setting himself against the Emperor!\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 13}On hearing what they said, Pilate brought Jesus out, and took his seat on the Bench at a place called \uc1\u8220*The Stone Pavement\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* in Hebrew \uc1\u8220*Gabbatha.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 14}It was the Passover Preparation day, and about noon. Then he said to the crowd, \uc1\u8216*Here is your king!\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 15}At that the people shouted, \uc1\u8216*Kill him! Kill him! Crucify him!\uc1\u8217*
