So they took Jesus; {\super\cf2\fs24 17}and he went out, carrying his cross himself, to the place which is named from a scull, or, in Hebrew, Golgotha. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}There they crucified him, and two others with him \uc1\u8211* one on each side, and Jesus between them. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Pilate also had these words written and put up over the cross \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*JESUS OF NAZARETH, THE KING OF THE JEWS.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 20}These words were read by many people, because the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city; and they were written in Hebrew, Latin and Greek. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}The chief priests said to Pilate, \uc1\u8216*Do not write \uc1\u8220*The king of the Jews\uc1\u8221*, but write what the man said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*I am the king of the Jews.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 22}But Pilate answered, \uc1\u8216*What I have written, I have written.\uc1\u8217*
