{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 20}On the first day of the week, early in the morning, while it was still dark, Mary of Magdala went to the tomb, and saw that the stone had been removed. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}So she came running to Simon Peter, and to that other disciple who was Jesus\uc1\u8217* friend, and said to them, \uc1\u8216*They have taken away the Master out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid him!\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 3}So, Peter started off with that other disciple, and they went to the tomb. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}The two began running together; but the other disciple ran faster than Peter, and reached the tomb first. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Stooping down, he saw the linen wrappings lying there, but did not go in. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Presently Simon Peter came following behind him, and went into the tomb; and he looked at the linen wrappings lying there, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}and the cloth which had been on Jesus\uc1\u8217* head, not lying with the wrappings, but rolled up on one side, separately. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Then the other disciple, who had reached the tomb first, went inside too, and he saw for himself and was convinced. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}For they did not then understand the passage of scripture which says that Jesus must rise again from the dead. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}The disciples then returned to their companions.
