{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Meanwhile Mary was standing close outside the tomb, weeping. Still weeping, she leant forward into the tomb, {\super\cf2\fs24 12}and perceived two angels clothed in white sitting there, where the body of Jesus had been lying, one where the head and the other where the feet had been. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}\uc1\u8216*Why are you weeping?\uc1\u8217* asked the angels. \uc1\u8216*They have taken my Master away,\uc1\u8217* she answered, \uc1\u8216*and I do not know where they have laid him.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 14}After saying this, she turned round, and looked at Jesus standing there, but she did not know that it was Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}\uc1\u8216*Why are you weeping? Whom are you seeking?\uc1\u8217* he asked. Supposing him to be the gardener, Mary answered, \uc1\u8216*If it was you, Sir, who carried him away, tell me where you have laid him, and I will take him away myself.\uc1\u8217*
