 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}In the evening of the same day \uc1\u8211* the first day of the week \uc1\u8211* after the doors of the room, in which the disciples were, had been shut because they were afraid of the religious authorities, Jesus came and stood among them and said, \uc1\u8216*Peace be with you\uc1\u8217*; {\super\cf2\fs24 20}after which he showed them his hands and his side. The disciples were filled with joy when they saw the Master. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Again Jesus said to them, \uc1\u8216*Peace be with you. As the Father has sent me as his messenger, so I am sending you.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 22}After saying this, he breathed on them, and said, \uc1\u8216*Receive the Holy Spirit; {\super\cf2\fs24 23}if you remit anyone\uc1\u8217*s sins, they have been remitted; and, if you retain them, they have been retained.\uc1\u8217*
