{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 30}There were many other signs of his mission that Jesus gave in presence of the disciples, which are not recorded in this book; {\super\cf2\fs24 31}but these have been recorded so that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God \uc1\u8211* and that, through your belief in his name, you may have life. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 21}Later on, Jesus showed himself again to the disciples by the Sea of Tiberias. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}It was in this way, \uc1\u8211* Simon Peter, Thomas, who was called \uc1\u8220*The Twin,\uc1\u8221* Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, Zebedee\uc1\u8217*s sons, and two other disciples of Jesus, were together, when Simon Peter said, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}\uc1\u8216*I am going fishing.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*We will come with you,\uc1\u8217* said the others. They went out and got into the boat, but caught nothing that night. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Just as day was breaking, Jesus came and stood on the beach; but the disciples did not know that it was he. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}\uc1\u8216*My children,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*have you anything to eat?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*No,\uc1\u8217* they answered. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}\uc1\u8216*Cast your net to the right of the boat,\uc1\u8217* he said, \uc1\u8216*and you will find fish.\uc1\u8217* So they cast the net, and now they could not haul it in because of the quantity of fish. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}The disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, \uc1\u8216*It is the Master!\uc1\u8217* When Simon Peter heard that it was the Master, he fastened his coat round him (for he had taken it off), and threw himself into the sea. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}But the rest of the disciples came in the boat (for they were only about a hundred yards from shore), dragging the net full of fish. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}When they had come ashore, they found a charcoal fire ready, with some fish already on it, and some bread as well. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8216*Bring some of the fish which you have just caught,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}So Simon Peter got into the boat and hauled the net ashore full of large fish, a hundred and fifty-three of them; and yet, although there were so many, the net had not been torn. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8216*Come and have breakfast.\uc1\u8217*, Jesus said. None of the disciples dared ask him who he was, because they knew it was the Master. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Jesus went and took the bread and gave it to them, and the fish too. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}This was the third time that Jesus showed himself to the disciples after he had risen from the dead.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}When breakfast was over, Jesus said to Simon Peter, \uc1\u8216*Simon, son of John, do you love me more than the others?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*Yes, Master,\uc1\u8217* he answered, \uc1\u8216*you know that I am your friend.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*Feed my lambs,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Then, a second time, Jesus asked, \uc1\u8216*Simon, son of John, do you love me?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*Yes, Master,\uc1\u8217* he answered, \uc1\u8216*you know that I am your friend.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*Tend my sheep,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}The third time, Jesus said to him, \uc1\u8216*Simon, son of John, are you my friend?\uc1\u8217* Peter was hurt at his third question being \uc1\u8220*Are you my friend?\uc1\u8221*; and exclaimed, \uc1\u8216*Master, you know everything! You can tell that I am your friend.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*Feed my sheep,\uc1\u8217* said Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8216*In truth I tell you,\uc1\u8217* he continued, \uc1\u8216*when you were young, you used to put on your own clothes, and walk wherever you wished; but, when you have grown old, you will have to stretch out your hands, while someone else puts on your clothes, and takes you where you do not wish.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Jesus said this to show the death by which Peter was to honour God, and then he added, \uc1\u8216*Follow me.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Peter turned round, and saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following \uc1\u8211* the one who at the supper leant back on the Master\uc1\u8217*s shoulder, and asked him who it was who would betray him. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Seeing him, Peter said to Jesus, \uc1\u8216*Master, what about this man?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 22}\uc1\u8216*If it is my will that he should wait until I come,\uc1\u8217* answered Jesus, \uc1\u8216*what has that to do with you? Follow me yourself.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 23}So the report spread among his followers that that disciple was not to die; yet Jesus did not say that he was not to die, but said \uc1\u8216*If it is my will that he should wait until I come, what has that to do with you?\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 24}It is this disciple who states these things, and who recorded them; and we know that his statement is true.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 25}There are many other things which Jesus did; but, if every one of them were to be recorded in detail, I suppose that even the world itself would not hold the books that would be written.
\par}
