{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}I thank God for inspiring Titus with the same keen interest in your welfare that I have; {\super\cf2\fs24 17}for Titus has responded to my appeals and, in his great earnestness, is starting to go to you of his own accord. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}We are sending with him one of the Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers whose fame in the service of the good news has spread through all the churches; {\super\cf2\fs24 19}and not only that, but he has been elected by the churches to accompany us on our journey, in connexion with this expression of your love, which we are personally administering to the honour of the Lord, and to show our deep interest. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}What we are specially guarding against is that any fault should be found with us in regard to our administration of this charitable fund; {\super\cf2\fs24 21}for we are trying to make arrangements which will be right, not only in the eyes of the Lord, but also in the eyes of people. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}We are also sending with them another of our friends, whose earnestness we have many a time proved in many ways, and whom we now find made even more earnest by his great confidence in you. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}If I must say anything about Titus, he is my intimate companion, and he shares my work for you; if it is our friends, they are delegates of the churches, an honour to Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}Show them, therefore \uc1\u8211* so that the churches may see it \uc1\u8211* the proof of your affection, and the ground for our boasting to them about you. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 9}With reference, indeed, to the Fund for your fellow Christians, it is quite superfluous for me to say anything to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}I know, of course, your willingness to help, and I am always boasting of it to the Macedonians. I tell them that you in Greece have been ready for a year past; and it was really your zeal that stimulated most of them. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}So my reason for sending our friends is to prevent what we said about you from proving, in this particular matter, an empty boast, and to enable you to be as well prepared as I have been saying that you are. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Otherwise, if any Macedonians were to come with me, and find you unprepared, we \uc1\u8211* to say nothing of you \uc1\u8211* should feel ashamed of our present confidence. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Therefore I think it necessary to beg the friends to go to you in advance, and to complete the arrangements for the gift, which you have already promised, so that it may be ready, as a gift, before I come, and not look as if it were being given under pressure.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Remember the saying \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Scanty sowing, scanty harvest; plentiful sowing, plentiful harvest.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Let everyone give as he has determined before hand, not grudgingly or under compulsion; for God loves a cheerful giver. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}God has power to shower all kinds of blessings on you, so that, having, under all circumstances and on all occasions, all that you can need, you may be able to shower all kinds of benefits on others. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}(As scripture says \uc1\u8211*
