{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Letter to the

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Philippians
  {\cf1 1}To all Christ\uc1\u8217*s people at Philippi, with the supervisors and assistants, from Paul and Timothy, servants of Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}May God, our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ bless you, and give you peace. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Every recollection that I have of you is a cause of thankfulness to God, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}always, in every prayer that I offer for you all \uc1\u8211* my prayers are full of joy \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Because of the share that you have had in spreading the good news, from the first day that you received it until now. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}For of this I am confident, that he who began a good work in you will complete it in readiness for the day of Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}And, indeed, I am justified in feeling like this about you all; because you have a warm place in my heart \uc1\u8211* you who all, both in my imprisonment and in the work of defending and establishing the good news, shared my privilege with me. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}God will bear me witness how I yearn over you all with the tenderness of Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}And what I pray for is this \uc1\u8211* that your love may grow yet stronger and stronger, with increasing knowledge and all discernment, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}until you are able to appreciate all moral distinctions. And I pray, too, that you may be kept pure and blameless against the day of Christ, {\super\cf2\fs24 11}bearing a rich harvest of that righteousness which comes through Jesus Christ, to the glory and praise of God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Friends, I want you to realise that what has happened to me has actually served to forward the good news. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}It has even become evident, not only to all the imperial guard, but to everyone else, that it is for Christ\uc1\u8217*s sake that I am in chains. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}And besides this, most of our fellow followers have gained confidence in the Lord through my chains, and now venture with far greater freedom to speak of God\uc1\u8217*s message fearlessly. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}It is true that some do proclaim the Christ out of Jealousy and opposition; but there are others who proclaim him from goodwill. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}The latter do it from love for me, knowing that I have been appointed to plead the cause of the good news. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}The former spread the news of the Christ in a factious spirit, and not sincerely, thinking to add to the pain of my chains. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}But what of that? Only that in some way or other, either with assumed or with real earnestness, Christ is being made known; and at that I rejoice. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Yes, and I will rejoice, for I know that, through your prayers and through a rich supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ, all this will make for my salvation. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}And this will fulfil my earnest expectation and hope that I will have no cause for shame, but that, with unfailing courage, now as hitherto, Christ will be honoured in my body, whether by my life or by my death, {\super\cf2\fs24 21}for to me life is Christ, and death is gain. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}But what if the life here in the body \uc1\u8211* if this brings me fruit from my labours? Then which to choose I cannot tell! I am sorely perplexed either way! {\super\cf2\fs24 23}My own desire is to depart and be with Christ, for this would be far better. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}But, for your sakes, it may be more needful that I should still remain here in the body. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Yes, I am confident that this is so, and therefore I am sure that I will stay, and stay near you all, to promote your progress and joy in the faith; {\super\cf2\fs24 26}so that, when you once more have me among you, you, in your union with Christ Jesus, may find in me fresh cause for exultation. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}Under all circumstances let your lives be worthy of the good news of the Christ: so that, whether I come and see you, or whether I hear of your affairs at a distance, I may know that you are standing firm, animated by one spirit, and joining with one heart in a common struggle for the faith taught by the good news, {\super\cf2\fs24 28}without ever shrinking from your opponents. To them this will be a sign of their destruction and of your salvation \uc1\u8211* a sign from God. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}For, on behalf of Christ, you have had the privilege granted you, not only of trusting in him, but also of suffering on his behalf. {\super\cf2\fs24 30}You will be engaged in the same hard struggle as that which you once saw me waging, and which you hear that I am waging still. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}If, then, any encouragement comes through union with Christ, if there is any persuasive power in love, if there is any communion with the Spirit, if there is any tenderness or pity, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}I entreat you to make my happiness complete \uc1\u8211* Live together animated by the same spirit and in mutual love, one in heart, animated by one Spirit. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Nothing should be done out of selfish ambition or vain conceit. Rather, in humility lift others up above yourselves, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}considering not only your own interests but also the interests of others. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Let the spirit of Christ Jesus be yours also. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Though the divine nature was his from the beginning, yet he did not look on equality with God as above all things to be clung to, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}but impoverished himself by taking the nature of a servant and becoming like one of us; {\super\cf2\fs24 8}he appeared among us as a man, and still further humbled himself by submitting even to death \uc1\u8211* to death on a cross! {\super\cf2\fs24 9}And that is why God raised him to the very highest place, and gave him the name which stands above all other names, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}so that in adoration of the name of Jesus every knee should bend, in heaven, on earth, and under the earth, {\super\cf2\fs24 11}and that every tongue should acknowledge JESUS CHRIST as LORD \uc1\u8211* to the glory of God the Father. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Therefore, my dear friends, as you have always been obedient in the past, so now work out your own salvation with anxious care, not only when I am with you, but all the more now that I am absent. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Remember it is God who, in his kindness, is at work within you, enabling you both to will and to work. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}In all that you do, avoid murmuring and dissension, {\super\cf2\fs24 15}so as to prove yourselves blameless and innocent \uc1\u8211* faultless children of God, in the midst of an evil-disposed and perverse generation, in which you are seen shining like stars in a dark world, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}offering to them the message of life; and then I will be able at the day of Christ to boast that I did not run my course for nothing, or toil for nothing. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And yet, even if, when your faith is offered as a sacrifice to God, my lifeblood must be poured out in addition, still I will rejoice and share the joy of you all; {\super\cf2\fs24 18}and you must also rejoice and share my joy. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}I hope, however, as one who trusts in the Lord Jesus, to send Timothy to you before long, so that I may myself be cheered by receiving news of you. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}For I have no one but him to send \uc1\u8211* no one of kindred spirit who would take the same genuine interest in your welfare. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}They are all pursuing their own aims and not those of Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}But you know what Timothy has proved himself to be, and how, like a child working for his father, he worked hard with me in spreading the good news. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}It is Timothy, then, whom I hope to send, as soon as ever I can foresee how it will go with me. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}And I am confident, as one who trusts in the Lord Jesus, that before long I myself will follow. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Still I think it necessary to send Epaphroditus to you now, for he is my dear friend, fellow worker, and fellow soldier, and he was also your messenger to help me in my need. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}For he has been longing to see you all, and has been distressed because you heard of his illness. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}And I can assure you that his illness very nearly proved fatal. But God had pity on him, and not on him only but also on me, so that I might not have sorrow on sorrow. {\super\cf2\fs24 28}I am all the more ready, therefore, to send him, so that the sight of him may revive your spirits and my own sorrow be lightened. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}Give him, then, the heartiest of Christian welcomes, and hold such people in great honour. {\super\cf2\fs24 30}For it was owing to his devotion to the Master\uc1\u8217*s work that he was at the point of death, having risked his own life in the effort to supply what was wanting in the help that you sent me. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}In conclusion, my friends, all joy be yours in your union with the Lord. To repeat what I have already written does not weary me, and is the safe course for you. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Beware of those dogs! Beware of those mischievous workers! Beware of the men who mutilate themselves! {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For it is we who are the circumcised \uc1\u8211* we whose worship is prompted by the Spirit of God, who exult in Christ Jesus, and who do not rely on external privileges; {\super\cf2\fs24 4}though I, if anyone, have cause to rely even on them. If anyone thinks he can rely on external privileges, far more can I! {\super\cf2\fs24 5}I was circumcised when eight days old; I am an Israelite by birth, and of the tribe of Benjamin; I am a Hebrew, and the child of Hebrews. As to the Law, I was a Pharisee; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}as to zeal, I was a persecutor of the church; as to such righteousness as is due to Law, I proved myself blameless. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}But all the things which I once held to be gains I have now, for the Christ\uc1\u8217*s sake, come to count as loss. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}More than that, I count everything as loss, for the sake of the exceeding value of the knowledge of Christ Jesus my Lord. And for his sake I have lost everything, and count it as refuse, if I may but gain Christ and be found in union with him; {\super\cf2\fs24 9}any righteousness that I have being, not the righteousness that results from Law, but the righteousness which comes through faith in Christ \uc1\u8211* the righteousness which is derived from God and is founded on faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Then indeed I will know Christ, and the power of his resurrection, and all that it means to share his sufferings, {\super\cf2\fs24 11}in the hope that, if I become like him in death, I may possibly attain to the resurrection from the dead. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Not that I have already laid hold of it, or that I am already made perfect. But I press on, in the hope of actually laying hold of that for which indeed I was laid hold of by Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}For I, friends, do not regard myself as having yet laid hold of it. But this one thing I do \uc1\u8211* forgetting what lies behind, and straining every nerve for that which lies in front, {\super\cf2\fs24 14}I press on to the goal, to gain the prize of that heavenward call which God gave me through Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Let all of us, then, whose faith is mature, think this way. Then, if on any matter you think otherwise, God will make that also plain to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Only we are bound to order our lives by what we have already attained.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}My friends, unite in following my example, and fix your eyes on those who are living by the pattern which we have set you. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}For there are many \uc1\u8211* of whom I have often told you, and now tell you even with tears \uc1\u8211* who are living in enmity to the cross of the Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}The end of such people is ruin; for their appetites are their God, and they glory in their shame; their minds are given up to earthly things. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}But we are citizens of heaven, and from heaven we expect a saviour to come, the Lord Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}By the exercise of his power to bring everything into subjection to himself, he will make our humble bodies like his glorious body. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 4}So then, my dear friends, whom I am longing to see \uc1\u8211* you who are my joy and my crown, stand fast in union with the Lord, dear friends. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}I entreat Euodia, and I entreat Syntyche, to live in harmony, in union with the Lord; {\super\cf2\fs24 3}yes, and I ask you, my true comrade, to help them, remembering that they toiled by my side in spreading the good news; and so, too, did Clement and my other fellow workers, whose names are in the book of life. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}All joy be yours at all times in your union with the Lord. Again I repeat \uc1\u8211* All joy be yours. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Let your forbearing spirit be plain to everyone. The Lord is near. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Do not be anxious about anything; but under all circumstances, by prayer and entreaty joined with thanksgiving, make your needs known to God. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Then the peace of God, which is beyond all human understanding, will stand guard over your hearts and thoughts, through your union with Christ Jesus.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}In conclusion, friends, whenever you find things that are true or honourable, righteous or pure, loveable or praiseworthy, or if virtue and honour have any meaning, let them fill your thoughts. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}All that you learned and received and heard and saw in me put into practice continually; and then God, the giver of peace, will be with you. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}It was a matter of great joy to me, as one in union with the Lord, that at length your interest in me had revived. The interest indeed you had, but not the opportunity. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Do not think that I am saying this under the pressure of want. For I, however I am placed, have learned to be independent of circumstances. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}I know how to face humble circumstances, and I know how to face prosperity. Into all and every human experience I have been initiated \uc1\u8211* into plenty and hunger, into prosperity and want. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}I can do everything in the strength of him who makes me strong! {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Yet you have acted nobly in sharing my troubles. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}And you at Philippi know, as well as I, that in the early days of the good news \uc1\u8211* at the time when I had just left Macedonia \uc1\u8211* no church, with the one exception of yourselves, had anything to do with me as far as giving and receiving are concerned. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Indeed, even while I was still in Thessalonica, you sent more than once to relieve my wants. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}It is not that I am anxious for your gifts, but I am anxious to see the abundant return that will be placed to your account. I have enough of everything, and to spare. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}My wants are fully satisfied, now that I have received from Epaphroditus the gifts which you sent me \uc1\u8211* the sweet fragrance of a sacrifice acceptable and pleasing to God. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}And my God, out of the greatness of his wealth, will, in glory, fully satisfy your every need, through your union with Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}To him, our God and Father, be ascribed all glory for every and ever. Amen. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Give my greeting to everyone of the people of Christ Jesus. The Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers who are with me send your their greetings. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}All Christ\uc1\u8217*s people here, and especially those who belong to the Emperor\uc1\u8217*s household, send theirs.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 23}May the blessing of the Lord Jesus Christ rest on your souls.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Colossians (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Letter to the

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Colossians
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}From Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus, by the will of God, and from Timothy, also a follower of the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}To Christ\uc1\u8217*s people at Colossae \uc1\u8211* the followers who are faithful to him: May God, our Father, bless you and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Whenever we pray we never fail to thank God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, for you, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}now that we have heard of your faith in Christ Jesus and of the love that you have for all his people, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}because of the hope which is kept safe for you in heaven. Of this hope you heard long ago in the true message of the good news which reached you, {\super\cf2\fs24 6}bearing fruit and growing, as it does, through all the world, just as it did among you from the very day that you heard of God\uc1\u8217*s loving kindness, and understood what that loving kindness really is. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}It is just what you learned from Epaphras, our dear fellow servant, who, as a minister of the Christ, faithfully represents us, {\super\cf2\fs24 8}and who told us of the love with which the Spirit has inspired you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}And therefore we, from the very day that we heard this, have never ceased praying for you, or asking that you may be filled with the knowledge of the will of God, which comes through all true spiritual wisdom and insight. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Then you will live lives worthy of the Master, and so please God in every way. Your lives will be fruitful in every kind of good action, and grow into a fuller knowledge of God; {\super\cf2\fs24 11}you will be made strong at all points with a strength worthy of the power manifested in his glory \uc1\u8211* strong to endure with patience, and even with gladness, whatever may happen to you; {\super\cf2\fs24 12}and you will give thanks to the Father who made you fit to share the lot which awaits Christ\uc1\u8217*s people in the realms of light.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Person and Work of the Christ

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}For God has rescued us from the tyranny of darkness, and has removed us into the kingdom of his Son, who is the embodiment of his love, {\super\cf2\fs24 14}and through whom we have found deliverance in the forgiveness of our sins.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}For Christ is the incarnation of the invisible God \uc1\u8211* first-born and head of all creation; {\super\cf2\fs24 16}for in him was created all that is in heaven and on earth, the visible and the invisible \uc1\u8211* angels and archangels and all the powers of heaven. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}All has been created through him and for him. He was before all things, and all things unite in him; {\super\cf2\fs24 18}and he is the head of the church, which is his body. The first-born from the dead, he is to the church the Source of its life, that he, in all things, may stand first. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}For it pleased the Father that in him the divine nature in all its fulness should live, {\super\cf2\fs24 20}and through him to reconcile all things to himself (making peace by the shedding of Christ\uc1\u8217*s blood offered on the cross) \uc1\u8211* whether on earth or in heaven. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}And it pleased God that you, once estranged from him and hostile towards him in your thoughts, intent only on wickedness \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 22}But now he has reconciled you to himself by the sacrifice of Christ\uc1\u8217*s earthly body in death \uc1\u8211* it has pleased God that you should stand in his presence holy, pure, and blameless, {\super\cf2\fs24 23}if only you remain true to your faith, firm and immovable, never abandoning the hope held out in the good news to which you listened, which has been proclaimed among all created things under heaven, and of which I, Paul, was made an assistant.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 24}Now at last I can rejoice in my sufferings on your behalf, and in my own person I supplement the afflictions endured by the Christ, for the sake of his body, the church; {\super\cf2\fs24 25}of which I myself became a minister in virtue of the office with which God entrusted me for your benefit, to declare the message of God in all its fulness \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 26}That truth which has been hidden from former ages and generations. But now it has been revealed to God\uc1\u8217*s people, {\super\cf2\fs24 27}to whom it was his pleasure to make known the surpassing glory of that hidden truth when proclaimed among the Gentiles \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Christ among you! Your hope of glory!\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 28}This is the Christ whom we proclaim, warning everyone, and instructing everyone, with all the wisdom that we possess, in the hope of bringing everyone into God\uc1\u8217*s presence perfected by union with Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}It is for that I toil, struggling with all the energy which he inspires and which works powerfully within me.  {\cf1 2}I want you to know in how great a struggle I am engaged for you and for Christ\uc1\u8217*s people at Laodicea, and for all who have not yet seen me; {\super\cf2\fs24 2}in the hope that they, being bound to one another by love, and keeping in view the full blessedness of a firm conviction, may be encouraged to strive for a perfect knowledge of God\uc1\u8217*s hidden truth, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}even Christ himself, in whom all treasures of wisdom and knowledge lie hidden. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}I say this to prevent anyone from deceiving you by plausible arguments. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}It is true that I am not with you in person, but I am with you in spirit, and am glad to see the good order and the unbroken front resulting from your faith in Christ.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Since, therefore, you have received Jesus, the Christ, as your Lord, live your lives in union with him \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 7}rooted in him, building up your characters through union with him, growing stronger through your faith, as you were taught, overflowing with faith and thanksgiving. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Take care there is not someone who will carry you away by his \uc1\u8220*philosophy\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* a hollow sham! \uc1\u8211* following, as it does, mere human traditions, and dealing with puerile questions of this world, and not with Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}For in Christ the Godhead in all its fulness dwells incarnate; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and, by your union with him, you also are filled with it. He is the head of all archangels and powers of heaven. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}By your union with him you received a circumcision that was not performed by human hands, when you threw off the tyranny of the earthly body, and received the circumcision of the Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}For in baptism you were buried with Christ; and in baptism you were also raised to life with him, through your faith in the omnipotence of God, who raised him from the dead. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}And to you, who once were dead, by reason of your sins and your uncircumcised nature \uc1\u8211* to you God gave life in giving life to Christ! He pardoned all our sins! {\super\cf2\fs24 14}He canceled the bond which stood against us \uc1\u8211* the bond that consisted of ordinances \uc1\u8211* and which was directly hostile to us! He has taken it out of our way by nailing it to the cross! {\super\cf2\fs24 15}He rid himself of all the powers of evil, and held them up to open contempt, when he celebrated his triumph over them on the cross!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Do not, then, allow anyone to take you to task on questions of eating or drinking, or in the matter of annual or monthly or weekly festivals. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}These things are only the shadow of what is to come; the substance is in the Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Do not let anyone defraud you of the reality by affecting delight in so-called \uc1\u8220*humility\uc1\u8221* and angel-worship. Such a person busies themselves with their visions, and without reason are rendered conceited by their merely human intellect. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}They fail to maintain union with the head, to whom it is due that the whole body, nourished and knit together by the contact and connexion of every part, grows with a divine growth.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Since, with Christ, you became dead to the puerile teaching of this world, why do you submit, as if you still belonged to the world, {\super\cf2\fs24 21}to such ordinances as \uc1\u8220*Do not handle, or taste, or touch\uc1\u8221*? {\super\cf2\fs24 22}For all the things referred to in them cease to exist when used. You are following mere human directions and instructions. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Such prohibitions appear reasonable where there is a desire for self-imposed service, and so-called \uc1\u8220*humility,\uc1\u8221* and harsh treatment of the body, but are of no real value against the indulgence of our earthly nature.  {\cf1 3}Since, therefore, you were raised to life with the Christ, seek for the things that are above; for it is there that the Christ is seated at the right hand of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Fix your thoughts on the things that are above, not on those that are on earth. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For you died, and your life now lies hidden, with the Christ, in God. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}When the Christ, who is our life, appears, then you also will appear with him in glory.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Gospel in the Daily Life

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Therefore destroy all that is earthly in you \uc1\u8211* immorality, uncleanness, passions, evil desires, and that greed which is idolatry. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}These are the things because of which the wrath of God comes, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}and to which you, like others, once devoted your lives, when you lived for them. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}You, however, must now lay aside all such things \uc1\u8211* anger, passion, malice, slander, abuse. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Never lie to one another. Get rid of your old self and its habits, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and clothe yourselves with that new self, which, as it gains in knowledge, is being constantly renewed in resemblance to him who made it. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}In that new life there is no distinction between Greek and Jew, circumcised and uncircumcised, barbarian, Scythian, slave, free; but Christ is all! \uc1\u8211* and in all!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Therefore, as God\uc1\u8217*s people, consecrated and dear to him, clothe yourselves with tenderness of heart, kindliness, humility, gentleness, forbearance; {\super\cf2\fs24 13}bearing with one another, and, when there is any ground for complaint, forgiving one another freely. As the Master freely forgave you, so you must forgive one another. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Over all these virtues put on love; for that is the belt which makes all complete. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Let the peace that the Christ gives decide all doubts within your hearts; for you also were called to the enjoyment of peace as members of one body. And show yourselves thankful. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Let the message of the Christ be alive in your minds in all its wealth, bringing all wisdom with it. Teach and admonish one another with psalms, and hymns, and sacred songs, full of the loving kindness of God, lifting your hearts in song to him. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And, whatever you say or do, do everything in the name of the Lord Jesus; and through him offer thanksgiving to God the father.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Wives, submit to your husbands, as befits those who belong to the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Husbands, love your wives, and never treat them harshly. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Children, always obey your parents; for that is pleasant to see in those who belong to the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Fathers, never irritate your children, otherwise they might become disheartened. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Slaves, always obey your earthly masters, not only when their eyes are on you, as if you had but to please people alone, but giving them ungrudging service, in your respect for the Master. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Whatever you do, do it with all your heart, as if working for the Master and not for people, {\super\cf2\fs24 24}since you know that it is from the Master that you will receive the inheritance which will be your reward. You are serving Christ, the Master. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Those who do wrong will reap the wrong they have done; and there will be no partiality.  {\cf1 4}Masters, do what is right and fair by your slaves, for you know that you also have a Master \uc1\u8211* in heaven.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Devote yourselves to prayer. Give your whole mind to it, and also offer thanksgiving; {\super\cf2\fs24 3}and at the same time pray for us, so that God may give us an opening for our message, so that we may speak of the truths hidden in the Christ \uc1\u8211* the truths for which I am in chains! {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Then I will make them known, as I ought to do. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Show tact in your behaviour to the outside world, making the most of every opportunity. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Let your conversation always be kindly, but not bland, season it, as it were, with salt; be aware in each case of the answer you should be giving.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Our dear friend, Tychicus, will tell you all about me. He is a faithful minister, and a fellow servant in the Master\uc1\u8217*s cause. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}I send him to you expressly that you may learn our circumstances, and that he may give you encouragement. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}With him will be Onesimus, our dear faithful friend, who is one of yourselves. They will tell you all that is going on here.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}My fellow prisoner, Aristarchus, sends you his greeting, and Barnabas\uc1\u8217*s cousin, Mark, sends his. (You have received directions about him. If he comes to you, make him welcome.) {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Joshua, who is called Justus, also sends his greeting. These are the only converts from Judaism who have worked with me for the kingdom of God; I have found them a great comfort. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Epaphras, who is one of yourselves, sends you his greeting. He is a servant of Christ Jesus, and is always most earnest in your behalf in his prayers, praying that you may stand firm, with a matured faith and with a sure conviction of all that is in accordance with God\uc1\u8217*s will. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}I can bear testimony to the deep interest he takes in you, as well as in the followers at Laodicea and at Hierapolis. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Luke, our dear doctor, sends you his greeting, and Demas sends his. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Give my greeting to the followers at Laodicea, and to Nymphe, and to the church that meets at her house. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}And when this letter has been read to you, see that it is also read before the church at Laodicea, and that you yourselves read the letter which will be forwarded from there. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Give this message to Archippus \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Take care to discharge to the best of your ability the office to which you were appointed in the Master\uc1\u8217*s cause.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}I, Paul, add this greeting in my own handwriting. Remember these chains of mine. God\uc1\u8217*s blessing be with you.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 1 Thessalonians (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 Paul\uc1\u8217*s First Letter to the

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Thessalonians
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}To the Thessalonian church in union with God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ, from Paul, Silas, and Timothy. May God bless you and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Apostle and his Converts

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}We always mention you in our prayers and thank God for you all; {\super\cf2\fs24 3}recalling continually before our God and Father the efforts that have resulted from your faith, the toil prompted by your love, and the patient endurance sustained by your hope in our Lord Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Friends, whom God loves, we know that he has chosen you, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}because the good news that we brought came home to you, not merely as so many words, but with a power and a fulness of conviction due to the Holy Spirit. For you know the life that we lived among you for your good. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And you yourselves began to follow, not only our example, but the Master\uc1\u8217*s also; and, in spite of much suffering, you welcomed the message with a joy inspired by the Holy Spirit, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}and so became a pattern to all who believed in Christ throughout Macedonia and Greece. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}For it was from you that the Lord\uc1\u8217*s message resounded throughout Macedonia and Greece; and, more than that, your faith in God has become known far and wide; so that there is no need for us to say another word. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Indeed, in speaking about us, the people themselves tell of the reception you gave us, and how, turning to God from your idols, you became servants of the true and living God, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and are now awaiting the return from heaven of his Son whom he raised from the dead \uc1\u8211* Jesus, our deliverer from the coming wrath. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}Yes, friends, you yourselves know that your reception of us was not without result. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}For, although we had experienced suffering and ill treatment, as you know, at Philippi, we had the courage, by the help of our God, to tell you God\uc1\u8217*s good news in spite of great opposition. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Our appeal to you was not based on a delusion, nor was it made from unworthy motives, or with any intention of misleading you. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}But, having been found worthy by God to be entrusted with the good news, therefore we tell it; with a view to please, not people, but God who proves our hearts. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Never at any time, as you know, did we use the language of flattery, or make false professions in order to hide selfish aims. God will bear witness to that. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Nor did we seek to win honour from people, whether from you or from others, although, as apostles of Christ, we might have burdened you with our support. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}But we lived among you with the simplicity of a child; we were like a woman nursing her own children. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}In our strong affection for you, that seemed to us the best way of sharing with you, not only God\uc1\u8217*s good news, but our lives as well \uc1\u8211* so dear had you become to us. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}You will not have forgotten, friends, our labour and toil. Night and day we used to work at our trades, so as not be a burden to any of you, while we proclaimed to you God\uc1\u8217*s good news. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}You will bear witness, and God also, that our relations with you who believed in Christ were pure, and upright, and beyond reproach. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Indeed, you know that, like a father with his own children, we used to encourage and comfort every one of you, and solemnly plead with you; {\super\cf2\fs24 12}so that you should make your daily lives worthy of God who is calling you into the glory of his kingdom.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}This, too, is a reason why we, on our part, are continually thanking God \uc1\u8211* because, in receiving the teaching that you had from us, you accepted it, not as the teaching of humans, but as what it really is \uc1\u8211* the teaching of God, which is even now doing its work within you who believe in Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}For you, friends, began to follow the example of the churches of God in Judea which are in union with Jesus Christ; you, in your turn, suffering at the hands of your fellow citizens, in the same way as those churches did at the hands of their people \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 15}who killed both the Lord Jesus and the prophets, and persecuted us also. They do not try to please God, and they are enemies to all humanity, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}for they try to prevent us from speaking to the Gentiles with a view to their salvation, and so are always filling up the measure of their iniquity. But the wrath of God has come upon them to the full!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}As for ourselves, friends, our having been bereaved of you even for a short time \uc1\u8211* though in body only, and not in spirit \uc1\u8211* made us all the more eager to see your faces again; and the longing to do so was strong on us. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}That was why we made up our minds to go and see you \uc1\u8211* at least I, Paul, did, more than once \uc1\u8211* but Satan put difficulties in our way. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}For what hope or joy will be ours, or what crown will we have to boast of, in the presence of our Lord Jesus, at his coming, if it isn\uc1\u8217*t you? {\super\cf2\fs24 20}You are our pride and our delight! 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}And so, as we could bear it no longer, we made up our minds to remain behind alone at Athens, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}and sent Timothy, our dear friend and God\uc1\u8217*s minister of the good news of the Christ, to strengthen you, and to encourage you in your faith, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}so that none of you should be shaken by the troubles through which you are passing. You yourselves know that we are destined to meet with such things. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}For, even while we were with you, we warned you beforehand that we were certain to encounter trouble. And so it proved, as you know. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Therefore, since I could no longer endure the uncertainty, I sent to make inquiries about your faith, fearing that the Tempter had tempted you, and that our toil might prove to have been in vain. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But, when Timothy recently returned to us from you with good news of your faith and love, and told us how kindly you think of us \uc1\u8211* always longing, he said, to see us, just as we are longing to see you \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 7}on hearing this, we felt encouraged about you, friends, in the midst of all our difficulties and troubles, by your faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}For it is new life to us to know that you are holding fast to the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}How can we thank God enough for all the happiness that you are giving us in the sight of our God? {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Night and day we pray most earnestly that we may see you face to face, and make good any deficiency in your faith.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}May our God and Father himself, and Jesus, our Lord, make the way plain for us to come to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}And for you, may the Lord fill you to overflowing with love for one another and for everyone, just as we are filled with love for you; {\super\cf2\fs24 13}and so make your hearts strong, and your lives pure beyond reproach, in the sight of our God and Father, at the coming of our Lord Jesus, with all his Holy Ones. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Advice on Daily Life

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 4}Further, friends, we beg and urge you in the name of our Lord Jesus to carry out more fully than ever \uc1\u8211* as indeed you are already doing \uc1\u8211* all that you have heard from us as to what your daily life must be, if it is to please God. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}For you have not forgotten the directions that we gave you on the authority of our Lord Jesus.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For this is God\uc1\u8217*s purpose \uc1\u8211* that you should be pure; abstaining from all immorality; {\super\cf2\fs24 4}each of you learning to gain control over your own body, in a way that is holy and honourable, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}and not for the mere gratification of your passions, like the Gentiles who know nothing of God; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}none of you overreaching or taking advantage of their fellow follower of the Lord in such matters. The Lord takes vengeance on all who do such things, as we have already warned you and solemnly declared. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}For God\uc1\u8217*s call to us does not permit of an impure life, but demands purity. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Therefore the person who disregards this warning disregards, not people, but God who gives you his Holy Spirit.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}As to love for each other there is no need to write to you; for you have yourselves been taught by God to love one another; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and indeed you do act in this spirit towards all his people throughout Macedonia.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
Yet, friends, we beg you to do even more. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Make it your ambition to live quietly, and to attend to your own business, and to work with your hands, as we directed you; {\super\cf2\fs24 12}so that your conduct may win respect from those outside the church, and that you may not want for anything.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Dead in Christ at the coming of the Lord

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}We don\uc1\u8217*t want you to be ignorant, friends, about those who have passed to their rest. We don\uc1\u8217*t want you to grieve like other people who have no hope. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}For, as we believe that Jesus died and rose again, so also we believe that God will bring, with Jesus, those who through him have passed to their rest. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}This we tell you on the authority of the Lord \uc1\u8211* that those of us who are still living at the coming of the Lord will not anticipate those who have passed to their rest. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}For, with a loud summons, with the shout of an archangel, and with the trumpet-call of God, the Lord himself will come down from heaven. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Then those who died in union with Christ will rise first; and afterwards we who are still living will be caught up in the clouds, with them, to meet the Lord in the air; and so we will be for ever with the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Therefore, comfort one another with what I have told you. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 5}But as to the times and the moments, there is no need, friends, for anyone to write to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}You yourselves know well that the day of the Lord will come just as a thief comes in the night. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}When people are saying \uc1\u8220*All is quiet and safe,\uc1\u8221* it is then that, like birth pains on a pregnant woman, ruin comes suddenly upon them, and there will be no escape! {\super\cf2\fs24 4}You, however, friends, are not in darkness, that the daylight should take you by surprise as if you were thieves. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}For you all are children of light and children of the day.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
We have nothing to do with night, or darkness. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Therefore let us not sleep as others do. No, let us be watchful and self-controlled. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}It is at night that people sleep, and at night that drunkards get drunk. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}But let us, who belong to the day, control ourselves, and put on faith and love as a breast plate, and the hope of salvation as a helmet. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}For God destined us, not for wrath, but to win salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ, who died for us, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}that, whether we are still watching or have fallen asleep, we may live with him. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Therefore encourage one another, and try to build up one another\uc1\u8217*s characters, as indeed you are doing.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}We beg you, friends, to value those who toil among you, and are your leaders in the Lord\uc1\u8217*s service, and give you counsel. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Hold them in the very greatest esteem and affection for the sake of their work. Live at peace with one another. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}We entreat you also, friends \uc1\u8211* warn the disorderly, comfort the faint-hearted, give a helping hand to the weak, and be patient with everyone. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Take care that none of you ever pays back wrong for wrong, but always follow the kindest course with one another and with everyone. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Always be joyful; {\super\cf2\fs24 17}never cease to pray; {\super\cf2\fs24 18}under all circumstances give thanks to God. For this is his will for you as made known in Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Do not quench the Spirit; {\super\cf2\fs24 20}do not make light of preaching. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Bring everything to the test; cling to what is good; {\super\cf2\fs24 22}shun every form of evil. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}May God himself, the giver of peace, make you altogether holy; and may your spirits, souls, and bodies be kept altogether faultless until the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}He who calls you will not fail you; he will complete his work.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Friends, pray for us.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 26}Greet all the Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers with a sacred kiss. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}I order you in the Lord\uc1\u8217*s name to have this letter read to all the brethren.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 28}May the blessing of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 2 Thessalonians (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Second Letter to the

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Thessalonians
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}To the Thessalonian church in union with God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ, From Paul, Silas, and Timothy. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}May God, the Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ bless you and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Apostle and his Converts

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Friends, it is our duty always to thank God about you, as is but right, considering the wonderful growth of your faith, and because, without exception, your love for one another is continually increasing. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}So much is this the case that we ourselves speak with pride, before the churches of God, of the patience and faith which you have shown, in spite of all the persecutions and troubles that you are enduring. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}These persecutions will vindicate the justice of God\uc1\u8217*s judgment, and will result in your being reckoned worthy of God\uc1\u8217*s kingdom, for the sake of which you are now suffering; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}since God deems it just to inflict suffering on those who are now inflicting suffering on you, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}and to give relief to you who are suffering, as well as to us, at the appearing of the Lord Jesus from heaven with his mighty angels, in flaming fire. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Then he will inflict punishment on those who refuse to know God, and on those who turn a deaf ear to the good news of Jesus, our Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}They will pay the penalty of unutterable ruin \uc1\u8211* banished from the presence of the Lord and from the glorious manifestation of his might, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}when he comes to be honoured in his people, and to be revered in all who have learned to believe in him (for you also believed our testimony) \uc1\u8211* as he will be on that day. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}With this in view, our constant prayer for you is that our God may count you worthy of the call that you have received, and by his power make perfect your delight in all goodness and the efforts that have resulted from your faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Then, in the loving kindness of our God and the Lord Jesus Christ, will the name of Jesus, our Lord, be honoured in you, and you in him. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Events that must precede the Lord\uc1\u8217*s Coming

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}As to the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, and our being gathered to meet him, we beg you, friends, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}not lightly to let your minds become unsettled, or disturbed by any revelation, or by any message, or by any letter, purporting to come from us, to the effect that the day of the Lord is come. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Do not let anyone deceive you, whatever he may do. For it will not come until after the Great Apostasy, and the appearing of that Incarnation of Wickedness, that Lost Soul, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}who so opposes himself to everyone that is spoken of as a God or as an object of worship, and so exalts himself above them, that he seats himself in the Temple of God, and displays himself as God! {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Don\uc1\u8217*t you remember how, when I was with you, I used to speak to you of all this? {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And you know now what the restraining influence is which prevents his appearing before his appointed time. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Wickedness, indeed, is already at work in secret; but only until he who at present restrains it is removed out of the way. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Then will \uc1\u8220*Wickedness Incarnate\uc1\u8221* appear, but the Lord Jesus will destroy him with the breath of his lips, and annihilate him by the splendour of his coming. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}For at the coming of the Lord there will be great activity on the part of Satan, in the form of all kinds of deceptive miracles, signs, and marvels, as well as of wicked attempts to delude \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}to the ruin of those who are on the path to destruction, because they have never received and loved the truth to their own salvation. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}That is why God places them under the influence of a delusion, to cause them to believe a lie; {\super\cf2\fs24 12}so that sentence may be passed on all those who refuse to believe the truth, but delight in wickedness.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}But, friends, whom the Lord loves, it is our duty always to thank God about you, for, from the first, God chose you for salvation through the purifying influence of the Spirit, and your belief in the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}To this you were called by the good news which we brought you, to attain to the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Stand firm then, friends, and hold fast to the truths that we taught you, whether by word or by letter. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}And may our Lord Jesus Christ himself, and God our Father, who loved us and, in his loving kindness, gave us unfailing consolation and good ground for hope, {\super\cf2\fs24 17}console your hearts, and strengthen you to do and to say all that is right. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}In conclusion, friends, pray for us \uc1\u8211* pray that the Lord\uc1\u8217*s message may spread rapidly, and be received everywhere with honour, as it was among you; {\super\cf2\fs24 2}and that we may be preserved from wrong-headed and wicked people \uc1\u8211* for it is not everyone who believes in Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}But the Lord will not fail you. He will give you strength, and guard you from evil. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Yes, and the confidence that our union with the Lord enables us to place in you leads us to believe that you are doing, and will do, what we direct you. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}May the Lord bring you to the love of God, and to the patience of the Christ.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}We beg you, friends, in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ, to avoid any follower who is living an ill-ordered life, which is not in agreement with the teaching that you received from us. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}For you know well that you ought to follow our example. When we were with you, our life was not ill-ordered, {\super\cf2\fs24 8}nor did we eat anyone\uc1\u8217*s bread without paying for it. Night and day, labouring and toiling, we used to work at our trades, so as not to be a burden on any of you. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}This was not because we had not a right to receive support, but our object was to give you a pattern for you to copy. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Indeed, when we were with you, the rule we laid down was \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Whoever does not choose to work will not get to eat.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 11}We hear that there are among you people who are living ill-ordered lives, and who, instead of attending to their own business, are mere busybodies. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}All such people we beg, and implore, in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ, to attend quietly to their business, and earn their own living. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}You, friends, must not grow weary of doing what is right. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}If anyone disregards what we have said in this letter, take note of them and avoid their company, so that they may feel ashamed. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Yet do not think of them as an enemy, but caution them as you would a brother or sister. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}May the Lord, from whom all peace comes, himself give you his peace at all times and in all ways. May he be with you all.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}I, Paul, add this greeting in my own handwriting. It is my signature to every letter. This is how I write. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}May the blessing of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 1 Timothy (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 Paul\uc1\u8217*s First Letter to

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Timothy
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}From Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the appointment of God, our Saviour, and Christ Jesus, our hope. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}To Timothy, my true child in the faith: May God, the Father, and Christ Jesus, our Lord, bless you, and be merciful to you, and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}I beg you, as I did when I was on my way into Macedonia, to remain at Ephesus; so that you may instruct certain people there not to teach new and strange doctrines, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}nor to devote their attention to legends and interminable genealogies, which tend to give rise to argument rather than to further that divine plan which is revealed in the faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}The object of all instruction is to call forth that love which comes from a pure heart, a clear conscience, and a sincere faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And it is because they have not aimed at these things that the attention of certain people has been diverted to unprofitable subjects. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}They want to be teachers of the Law, and yet do not understand either the words they use, or the subjects on which they speak so confidently. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}We know, of course, that the Law is excellent, when used legitimately, {\super\cf2\fs24 9}by one who recognises that laws were not made for good people, but for the lawless and disorderly, for irreligious and wicked people, for those who are irreverent and profane, for those who ill-treat their fathers or mothers, for murderers, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}for the immoral, for perverts, for slave-dealers, for liars, for perjurers, and for whatever else is opposed to sound Christian teaching \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 11}as is taught in the glorious good news of the ever-blessed God, with which I was entrusted.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}I am thankful to Christ Jesus, our Lord, who has been my strength, for showing that he thought me worthy of trust by appointing me to his ministry, {\super\cf2\fs24 13}though I once used to blaspheme, and to persecute, and to insult. Yet mercy was shown me, because I acted in ignorance, while still an unbeliever; {\super\cf2\fs24 14}and the loving kindness of our Lord was boundless, and filled me with that faith and love which come from union with Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}How true the saying is, and worthy of the fullest acceptance, that \uc1\u8220*Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners\uc1\u8221*! And there is no greater sinner than I! {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Yet mercy was shown me for the express purpose that Christ Jesus might exhibit in my case, beyond all others, his exhaustless patience, as an example for those who were afterwards to believe on him and attain eternal life. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}To the eternal King, ever-living, invisible, the one God, be ascribed honour and glory for ever and ever. Amen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}This, then, is the charge that I lay on you, Timothy, my child, in accordance with what was predicted of you \uc1\u8211* Fight the good fight in the spirit of those predictions, {\super\cf2\fs24 19}with faith, and with a clear conscience; and it is because they have thrust this aside, that, as regards the faith, some have wrecked their lives. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Hymenaeus and Alexander are instances \uc1\u8211* the men whom I delivered over to Satan so that they might be taught not to blaspheme. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 General Directions on Church Matters

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}First of all, then, I ask that petitions, prayers, intercessions, and thanksgivings should be offered for everyone, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}especially for kings and all who are in high positions, in order that we may lead a quiet and peaceful life in a deeply religious and reverent spirit. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}This will be good and acceptable in the eyes of God, our Saviour, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}whose will is that everyone should be saved, and attain to a full knowledge of the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}There is but one God, and one mediator between God and humanity \uc1\u8211* the human, Christ Jesus, {\super\cf2\fs24 6}who gave himself as a ransom on behalf of all.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
This must be our testimony, as opportunities present themselves; {\super\cf2\fs24 7}and it was for this that I was myself appointed a herald and an apostle (I am telling the simple truth and no lie) \uc1\u8211* a teacher of the Gentiles in the faith and truth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}My desire, then, is that it should be the custom everywhere for the men to lead the prayers, with hands reverently uplifted, avoiding heated controversy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}I also desire that women should adorn themselves with appropriate dress, worn quietly and modestly, and not with wreaths or gold ornaments for the hair, or pearls, or costly clothing, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}but \uc1\u8211* as is proper for women who profess to be religious \uc1\u8211* with good actions. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}They must learn, listening quietly to their teachers and showing them all deference. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}I do not consent to them becoming teachers, or exercising authority over men; they ought to not make a fuss. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Adam was formed first, not Eve. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}And it was not Adam who was deceived; it was the woman who was entirely deceived and fell into sin. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}But she will be saved by the birth of a child, if they never abandon faith, love, or holiness, and behave with modesty. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}How true is this saying:{\super\cf2\fs24 1}\uc1\u8220*To aspire to be to be a supervisor in the church is to be ambitious for a noble task.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 2}The supervisor should be of blameless character; a faithful partner; living a temperate, discreet, and well-ordered life; hospitable, and a skilful teacher, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}not addicted to drink or brawling, but of a forbearing and peaceable disposition, and not a lover of money; {\super\cf2\fs24 4}they should provide for own household well, and their children should kept under control and be well-behaved. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}If someone does not know how to provide for their own household, how can they take charge of the church of God? {\super\cf2\fs24 6}The supervisor should not be a recent convert, or they might become blinded by pride and fall under the same judgement as the devil. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}They should also be well spoken of by outsiders, so that they may not incur censure and so fall into the devil\uc1\u8217*s trap. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}So, too, assistants should be serious and straightforward, not given to taking much drink or to questionable money-making, {\super\cf2\fs24 9}but people who hold the deep truths of the faith and have a clear conscience. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}They should be tested first, and only appointed to their office if no objection is raised against them. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}It should be the same with the women in this office. They should be serious, not gossips, sober, and trustworthy in all respects. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Assistants should be faithful partners who manage their children and their households well. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Those who have filled that post with honour gain for themselves an honourable position, as well as great confidence through the faith that they place in Christ Jesus.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Special Directions to Timothy

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}I am writing this to you, though I hope that I will come to see you before long; {\super\cf2\fs24 15}but in case I should be delayed, I want you to know what your conduct ought to be in the Household of God, which is the church of the living God \uc1\u8211* the pillar and stay of the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Yes, and confessedly wonderful are the deep truths of our religion; for \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*He was revealed in our nature,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Pronounced righteous in spirit,
\par}

{\pard\fi-1720\li2800
Seen by angels,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Proclaimed among the Gentiles,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Believed on in the world,
\par}

{\pard\fi-1720\li2800
Taken up into glory.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
  {\cf1 4}But the Spirit distinctly says that in later times there will be some who will fall away from the faith, and devote their attention to misleading spirits, and to the teaching of demons, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}who will make use of the hypocrisy of lying teachers. These people\uc1\u8217*s consciences are seared, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}and they discourage marriage and enjoin abstinence from certain kinds of food; though God created these foods to be enjoyed thankfully by those who hold the faith and have attained a full knowledge of the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Everything created by God is good, and there in nothing that need be rejected \uc1\u8211* provided only that it is received thankfully; {\super\cf2\fs24 5}for it is consecrated by God\uc1\u8217*s blessing and by prayer.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Put all this before the followers, and you will be a good servant of Christ Jesus, sustained by the precepts of the faith and of that good teaching by which you have guided your life. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}As for profane legends and old wives\uc1\u8217* tales, leave them alone. Train yourself to lead a religious life; {\super\cf2\fs24 8}for while the training of the body is of service in some respects, religion is of service in all, carrying with it, as it does, a promise of life both here and hereafter. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}How true that saying is and worthy of the fullest acceptance! {\super\cf2\fs24 10}With that aim we toil and struggle, for we have set our hopes on the living God, who is the Saviour of all, and especially of those who hold the faith.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Remember these things in your teaching. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Do not let anyone look down on you because you are young, but, by your conversation, your conduct, your love, your faith, and your purity, be an example to those who hold the faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Until I come, apply yourself to public reading, preaching, and teaching. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Do not neglect the divine gift within you, which was given you, amid many a prediction, when the hands of the church elders were laid on your head. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Practice these things, devote yourself to them, so that your progress may be plain to everyone. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Look to yourself as well as to your teaching. Persevere in this, for your doing so will mean salvation for yourself as well as for your hearers. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 5}Do not reprimand an older man, but plead with him as if he were your father. Treat the young men as brothers, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}the older women as mothers, and the younger women as sisters \uc1\u8211* with all purity. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Show consideration for widows \uc1\u8211* I mean those who are really widowed. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}But, if a widow has children or grandchildren, they should learn to show proper regard for the members of their own family first, and to make some return to their parents; for that is pleasing in God\uc1\u8217*s sight. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}As for the woman who is really widowed and left quite alone, her hopes are fixed on God, and she devotes herself to prayers and supplications night and day. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But the life of a widow who is devoted to pleasure is a living death. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Those are the points you should teach, so that there may be no call for your censure. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Anyone who fails to provide for their own relatives, and especially for those under their own roof, has disowned the faith, and is worse than an unbeliever. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}A widow, when her name is added to the list, should not be less than sixty years old; she should have been a faithful wife, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and be well spoken of for her kind actions. She should have brought up children, have shown hospitality to strangers, have washed the feet of her fellow Christians, have relieved those who were in distress, and devoted herself to every kind of good action. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}But you should exclude the younger widows from the list; for, when they grow restive under the yoke of the Christ, they want to marry, {\super\cf2\fs24 12}and so they bring condemnation on themselves for having broken their previous promise. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}And not only that, but they learn to be idle as they go about from house to house. Nor are they merely idle, but they also become gossips and busybodies, and talk of what they ought not. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore I advise young widows to marry, bear children, and attend to their homes, and so avoid giving the enemy an opportunity for scandal. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}There are some who have already left us, to follow Satan. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Any Christian woman, who has relatives who are widows, ought to relieve them and not allow them to become a burden to the church, so that the church may relieve those widows who are really widowed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Those church elders who fill their office well should be held deserving of especial consideration, particularly those whose work lies in preaching and teaching. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}The words of scripture are \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You should not muzzle the ox while it is treading out the grain.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
and again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The worker is worth their wages.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Do not entertain a charge against an church elder, unless it is supported by two or three witnesses; {\super\cf2\fs24 20}but rebuke offenders publicly, so that others may take warning. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}I charge you solemnly, before God and Christ Jesus and the chosen angels, to carry out these directions, unswayed by prejudice, never acting with partiality. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Never ordain anyone hastily, and take no part in the wrong-doing of others. Keep your life pure. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Do not continue to drink water only, but take a little wine because of the weakness of your stomach, and your frequent ailments. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}There are some people whose sins are conspicuous and lead on to judgment, while there are others whose sins dog their steps. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}In the same way noble deeds become conspicuous, and those which are otherwise cannot be concealed. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 6}All who are in the position of slaves should regard their masters as deserving of the greatest respect, so that the name of God, and our teaching, may not be maligned. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Those who have Christian masters should not think less of them because they are also followers of Christ, but on the contrary they should serve them all the better, because those who are to benefit by their good work are dear to them as their fellow Christians.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Conclusion
Those are the things to insist on in your teaching.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Anyone who teaches otherwise, and refuses their assent to sound instruction \uc1\u8211* the instruction of our Lord Jesus Christ \uc1\u8211* and to the teaching of religion, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}is puffed up with conceit, not really knowing anything, but having a morbid craving for discussions and arguments. Such things only give rise to envy, quarrelling, recriminations, base suspicions, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}and incessant wrangling on the part of these corrupt-minded people who have lost all hold on the truth, and who think of religion only as a source of gain. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Of course religion is a great source of gain \uc1\u8211* when combined with contentment! {\super\cf2\fs24 7}For we brought nothing into the world, because we cannot even carry anything out of it. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}So, with food and shelter, we will be content. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Those who want to be rich fall into the net of temptation, and become the prey of many foolish and harmful ambitions, which plunge people into destruction and ruin. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Love of money is a source of all kinds of evil; and in their eagerness to be rich some have wandered away from the faith, and have been pierced to the heart by many a regret.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}But you must, servant of God, avoid all this. Aim at righteousness, piety, faith, love, endurance, gentleness. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Run the great race of the faith, and win the eternal life. It was for this that you received the call, and, in the presence of many witnesses, made the great profession of faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}I beg you, as in the sight of God, the source of all life, and of Christ Jesus who before Pontius Pilate made the great profession of faith \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 14}I implore you to keep his command free from stain or reproach, until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}This will be brought about in his own time by the one ever-blessed Potentate, the king of all kings and Lord of all lords, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}who alone is possessed of immortality and dwells in unapproachable light, whom no one has ever seen or ever can see \uc1\u8211* to whom be ascribed honour and power for ever. Amen.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Teach those who are wealthy in this life not to pride themselves, or fix their hopes, on so uncertain a thing as wealth, but on God, who gives us a wealth of enjoyment on every side. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Teach them to show kindness, to exhibit a wealth of good actions, to be open-handed and generous, {\super\cf2\fs24 19}storing up for themselves what in the future will prove to be a good foundation, so that they may gain the only true life.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Timothy, guard what has been entrusted to you. Avoid the profane prattle and contradictions of what some miscall \uc1\u8220*theology,\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 21}for there are those who, while asserting their proficiency in it, have yet, as regards the faith, gone altogether astray.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
God bless you all.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 2 Timothy (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Second Letter to

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Timothy
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}From Paul who, by the will of God, is an apostle of Christ Jesus, charged to proclaim the life that comes from union with Christ Jesus, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}to Timothy, my dear child: may God, the Father, and Christ Jesus, our Lord, bless you, and be merciful to you, and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}I am thankful to God, whom I serve, as my ancestors did, with a clear conscience, when I remember you, as I never fail to do, in my prayers \uc1\u8211* night and day alike, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}as I think of your tears, longing to see you, that my happiness may be completed, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}now that I have been reminded of the sincere faith that you have shown. That faith was seen first in your grandmother Lois and your mother Eunice, and is now, I am convinced, in you also. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And that is my reason for reminding you to stir into flame that gift of God, which is yours through your ordination at my hands. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}For the Spirit which God gave us was not a spirit of cowardice, but a spirit of power, love, and self-control. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Do not, therefore, be ashamed of the testimony which we have to bear to our Lord, or of me imprisoned for his sake; but join with me in suffering for the good news, as far as God enables you. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}It was God who saved us, and from him we received our solemn call \uc1\u8211* not as a reward for anything that we had done, but in fulfilment of his own loving purpose. For that love was extended to us, through Christ Jesus, before time began, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and has now been made apparent through the appearing of our Saviour, Christ Jesus; who has made an end of death, and has brought life and Immortality to light by that good news, {\super\cf2\fs24 11}of which I was myself appointed a herald and apostle, and teacher. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}That is why I am undergoing these sufferings; yet I feel no shame, for I know in whom I have put my faith, and am convinced that he is able to guard what I have entrusted to him until that day. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Keep before you, as an example of sound teaching, all that you learnt from me as you listened with that faith and love which come from union with Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Guard by the help of the Holy Spirit, who is within us, the glorious trust that has been committed to you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}You know, of course, that all our friends in Roman Asia turned their backs on me, including Phygellus and Hermogenes. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}May the Lord show mercy to the household of Onesiphorus; for he often cheered me and was not ashamed of my chains. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}On the contrary, when he arrived in Rome, he sought eagerly for me until he found me. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}The Lord grant that he may find mercy at the hands of the Lord on that day. The many services that he rendered at Ephesus you have the best means of knowing. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Injunctions to Timothy

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}You must, then, my child, find strength in the help which comes from the union with Christ Jesus; {\super\cf2\fs24 2}and what you learnt from me, in the presence of many listeners, entrust to reliable people, who will be able in their turn to teach others. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Share hardships with me, as a true soldier of Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}A soldier on active service, to please his superior officer, always avoids entangling himself in the affairs of ordinary life. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}No athlete is ever awarded the wreath of victory unless they have kept the rules. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}The labourer who does the work should be the first to receive a share of the fruits of the earth. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Reflect on what I say; the Lord will always help you to understand. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Keep before your mind Jesus Christ, raised from the dead, a descendant of David, as told in the good news entrusted to me; {\super\cf2\fs24 9}in the service of which I am suffering hardships, even to being put in fetters as a criminal. But the message of God is not fettered; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and that is why I submit to anything for the sake of God\uc1\u8217*s people: so that they also may obtain the salvation which comes from union with Christ Jesus, and imperishable glory. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}How true this saying is \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*If we have shared his death, we will also share his life. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}If we continue to endure, we will also share his throne. If we should ever disown him, he, too, will disown us. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}If we lose our trust, he is still to be trusted, for he cannot be false to himself!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Remind people of all this; tell them solemnly, as in the sight of God, to avoid controversy, a useless thing and the ruin of those who listen to it. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Do your utmost to show yourself true to God, a worker with no reason to be ashamed, accurate in delivering the message of the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Avoid profane prattle. Those who indulge in it only get deeper into irreligious ways, {\super\cf2\fs24 17}and their teaching will spread like a cancer. Hymenaeus and Philetus are instances of this. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}They have gone completely astray as regards the truth; they say that a resurrection has already taken place, and so upset some people\uc1\u8217*s faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Yet God\uc1\u8217*s firm foundation still stands unmoved, and it bears this inscription \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*THE LORD KNOWS THOSE WHO ARE HIS\uc1\u8221*;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
and this \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*LET ALL THOSE WHO USE THE NAME OF THE LORD TURN AWAY FROM WICKEDNESS.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Now in a large house there are not only things of gold and silver, but also others of wood and earthenware, some for better and some for common use. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}If, then, a person has escaped from the pollution of such errors as I have mentioned, they will be like a thing kept for better use, set apart, serviceable to its owner, ready for any good purpose. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Flee from the passions of youth, but pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace, in the company of those who, with a pure heart, invoke the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Shun foolish and ignorant discussions, for you know that they only breed quarrels; {\super\cf2\fs24 24}and a servant of the Lord should never quarrel. They ought, on the contrary, to be courteous to everyone, skilful teachers, and forbearing. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}They should instruct their opponents in a gentle spirit; for, possibly, God may give those opponents a repentance that will lead to a fuller knowledge of truth, {\super\cf2\fs24 26}and they may yet come to a sober mind, and escape from the devil\uc1\u8217*s net, when captured by the Lord\uc1\u8217*s servant to do the will of God. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}Be sure of this, that in the last days difficult times will come. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}People will be selfish, mercenary, boastful, haughty, and blasphemous; disobedient to their parents, ungrateful, impure, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}incapable of affection, merciless, slanderous, wanting in self-control, brutal, careless of the right, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}treacherous, reckless, and puffed up with pride; they will love pleasure more than they love God; {\super\cf2\fs24 5}and while they retain the outward form of religion, they will not allow it to influence them. Turn your back on such people as these. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}For among them are to be found those who creep into homes and captivate weak women \uc1\u8211* women who, loaded with sins, and slaves to all kinds of passions, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}are always learning, and yet never able to attain to a real knowledge of the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Just as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so do these people, in their turn, oppose the truth. Their minds are corrupted, and, as regards the faith, they are utterly worthless. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}They will not, however, make further progress; for their wicked folly will be plain to everyone, just as the folly Jannes and Jambres was. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}But you, Timothy, were a close observer of my teaching, my conduct, my purposes, my faith, my forbearance, my love, and my patient endurance, {\super\cf2\fs24 11}as well as of my persecutions, and of the sufferings which I met with at Antioch, Iconium, and Lystra. You know what persecutions I underwent; and yet the Lord brought me safe out of all! {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Yes, and all who aim at living a religious life in union with Christ Jesus will have to suffer persecution; {\super\cf2\fs24 13}but wicked people and impostors will go from bad to worse, deceiving others and deceived themselves. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}You, however, must stand by what you learnt and accepted as true. You know who they were from whom you learnt it; {\super\cf2\fs24 15}and that, from your childhood, you have known the sacred writings, which can give you the wisdom that, through belief in Christ Jesus, leads to salvation. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}All scripture is God-breathed: helpful for teaching, for refuting error, for giving guidance, and for training others in righteousness; {\super\cf2\fs24 17}so that God\uc1\u8217*s people may be capable and equipped for good work of every kind. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 4}I solemnly charge you \uc1\u8211* in the sight of God and of Christ Jesus, who will one day judge the living and the dead \uc1\u8211* I charge you by his appearing and by his kingdom: {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Proclaim the message, be ready in season and out of season, convince, rebuke, encourage, never failing to instruct with forbearance. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For a time will come when people will not tolerate sound teaching. They will follow their own wishes, and, in their itching for novelty, procure themselves a crowd of teachers. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}They will turn a deaf ear to the truth, and give their attention to legends instead. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}But you, Timothy, must always be temperate. Face hardships; do the work of a missionary; discharge all the duties of your office.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}As for me, my life blood is already being poured out; the time of my departure is close at hand. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}I have run the great race; I have finished the course; I have kept the faith. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}And now the crown of righteousness awaits me, which the Lord, the just judge, will give me on that day \uc1\u8211* and not only to me, but to all who have loved his appearing.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Do your utmost to come to me soon; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}for Demas, in his love for the world, has deserted me. He has gone to Thessalonica, Crescens to Galatia, and Titus to Dalmatia. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}There is no one but Luke with me. Pick up Mark on your way, and bring him with you, for he is useful to me in my work. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}I have sent Tychicus to Ephesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Bring with you, when you come, the cloak which I left at Troas with Carpus, and the books, especially the parchments. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Alexander, the coppersmith, showed much ill feeling towards me. The Lord will give him what his actions deserve. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}You must also on your guard against him, for he is strongly opposed to our teaching. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}At my first trial no one stood by me. They all deserted me. May it never be counted against them! {\super\cf2\fs24 17}But the Lord came to my help and strengthened me, in order that, through me, the proclamation should be made so widely that all the Gentiles should hear it; and I was rescued out of the lion\uc1\u8217*s mouth. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}The Lord will rescue me from all evil, and bring me safe into his Heavenly kingdom. All glory to him for ever and ever! Amen.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Give my greeting to Prisca and Aquila, and to the household of Onesiphorus. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Erastus remained at Corinth, and I left Thophimus ill at Miletus. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Do your utmost to come before winter. Eubulus, Pudens, Linus and Claudia send you their greetings, and so do the rest of the Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 22}May the Lord be with your soul. God bless you all.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Titus (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Letter to

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Titus
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}From Paul, a servant of God, and an apostle of Jesus Christ, on behalf of the faith of God\uc1\u8217*s chosen people, and their knowledge of that truth which makes for godliness {\super\cf2\fs24 2}\uc1\u8211* and is based on the hope of eternal life, which God, who never lies, promised before the ages began, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}and has revealed at his own time in his message, with the preaching of which I was entrusted by the command of God our Saviour. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}To Titus, my true child in our shared faith: May God, the Father, and Christ Jesus, our Saviour, bless you and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Mission of Titus in Crete

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}My reason for leaving you in Crete was that you might put in order what had been left unfinished, and appoint church elders in the various towns, as I myself directed you. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}They are to be of irreproachable character, faithful to their partners, whose children are believers in Christ and have never been open to the charge of being wild or unruly. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}For a supervisor, as God\uc1\u8217*s steward, ought to be of blameless character \uc1\u8211* not arrogant or quick-tempered, not given to drunkeness, violence or shady money-making. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Instead, they should be hospitable, love what is good, self-controlled, upright, people of holy life and disciplined, {\super\cf2\fs24 9}holding firmly to the trustworthy message as it has been taught \uc1\u8211* so that they may be able to encourage others by sound teaching, as well as to refute those who contradict it.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}For there are many undisciplined persons who lead others astray with their nonsense, especially those of the group advocating the necessity of circumcision. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}They need to be kept quiet as they disrupt whole households by teaching what they ought not to teach, simply to make shameful financial gain. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}It was a Cretan \uc1\u8211* one of their own prophets \uc1\u8211* who said: \uc1\u8220*Cretans are always liars, evil beasts, and lazy gluttons.\uc1\u8221* This statement is true. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Therefore rebuke them sharply, so that they may be sound in the faith, {\super\cf2\fs24 14}and may pay no attention to Jewish legends, or to the directions of those who turn their backs on the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}To those whose minds are pure, all things are ritually pure, but to those whose minds are tainted and unbelieving nothing is pure, as their minds and consciences are alike polluted. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}They claim to know God, but by their actions they deny him. They are detestable and disobedient and useless for any good work. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}You however, should speak of such subjects as properly have a place in sound teaching. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Teach that the older men should be soberly clear minded, dignified and self-controlled \uc1\u8211* sound in faith, love, and patient endurance. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}So, too, that the older women should live reverent lives, not slanderers, not slaves to excessive drinking. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}They should teach what is good, so as to train the younger women to love their husbands and children, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}and to be self-controlled, pure-minded, to be watching over their home, to be kind, respecting the authority of their husbands, so that no one will speak badly of God\uc1\u8217*s message. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}In the same way with the younger men \uc1\u8211* encourage them to be self-controlled. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}In all things, set an example of doing good. In your teaching, show integrity and seriousness \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 8}let the instruction that you give be sound and above reproach, so that those who oppose you may be ashamed when they fail to find anything bad to say about us. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Tell slaves to respect their owner\uc1\u8217*s authority in all circumstances, and to try their best to please them. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Teach them not to contradict or to pilfer, but to show such praiseworthy fidelity in everything, as to recommend the teaching about God our Saviour by all that they do.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}For the loving kindness of God has been revealed, bringing salvation for all, {\super\cf2\fs24 12}leading us to renounce ungodliness and worldly desires, and to live self-controlled, upright, and godly lives here in this present age, {\super\cf2\fs24 13}while awaiting our blessed hope \uc1\u8211* the appearing in glory of our great God and Saviour, Christ Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}For he gave himself on our behalf, to deliver us from all wickedness, and to purify for himself a people who should be truly his own and eager to do good. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Tell them of all this, and encourage and rebuke with all authority. Do not let anyone belittle you.  {\cf1 3}Remind them to respect and obey the rulers and authorities, to be ready for every kind of good work, to slander no one, to avoid quarrelling, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}to be reasonable, and under all circumstances to show a gentle spirit with all. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}There was a time when we ourselves were foolish, disobedient, misled, enslaved to all kinds of desires and pleasures, living in malice and envy, hating ourselves and hating one another. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}But, when the kindness of God our Saviour and his love for humanity appeared, he saved us, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}not as the result of any righteous actions that we had done, but due to his mercy. He saved us though the washing of rebirth and renewal by the power of the Holy Spirit, {\super\cf2\fs24 6}which he poured out on us abundantly through Jesus Christ our Saviour \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 7}so that, having been put right with God through his grace, we become heirs to the hope of eternal life. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}This saying is trustworthy! And it is on these subjects that I want you to lay special emphasis, so that those who have learned to trust in God may be careful to devote themselves to doing good. Such subjects are excellent in themselves, and of benefit to all. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}But have nothing to do with foolish controversies, or with genealogies, or with quarrels, or fights about the Law. They are useless and futile. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}If someone is causing divisions among you then, after giving them a second warning, excuse yourself from them. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}You can be sure that such a person has forsaken the truth and is in the wrong. They stand self-condemned.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}As soon as I send Artemas or Tychicus to you, join me as quickly as possible at Nicopolis, for I have arranged to spend the winter there. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Do your best to help Zenas, the teacher of the Law, and Apollos, on their way, and see that they want for nothing. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Let all our people learn to devote themselves to doing good, so as to meet the most pressing needs, and that their lives may not be unfruitful.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}All who are with me here send you their greeting. Give my greeting to our friends in the faith.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
God bless you all.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Philemon (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 Paul\uc1\u8217*s Letter to

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Philemon
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}From Paul, now a prisoner for Christ Jesus, and from Timothy, a fellow follower of the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}To our dear friend and fellow worker Philemon, to our sister Apphia, to our fellow soldier Archippus; and to the church that meets at Philemon\uc1\u8217*s house; {\super\cf2\fs24 3}may God, our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ bless you and give you peace.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Request regarding runaway slave

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}I always mention you in my prayers and thank God for you, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}because I hear of the love and the faith which you show, not only to the Lord Jesus, but also to all his people; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}and I pray that your participation in the faith may result in action, as you come to a fuller realisation of everything that is good and Christlike in us. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}I have indeed found great joy and encouragement in your love, knowing, as I do, how the hearts of Christ\uc1\u8217*s People have been cheered, friend, by you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}And so, though my union with Christ enables me, with all confidence, to dictate the course that you should adopt, {\super\cf2\fs24 9}yet the claims of love make me prefer to plead with you \uc1\u8211* yes, even me, Paul, though I am an ambassador for Christ Jesus and, now a prisoner for him as well. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}I plead with you for this child of mine, Onesimus, to whom, in my prison, I have become a father. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Once he was of little service to you, but now he has become of great service, not only to you, but to me as well; {\super\cf2\fs24 12}and I am sending him back to you with this letter \uc1\u8211* though it is like tearing out of my heart. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}For my own sake I should like to keep him with me, so that, while I am in prison for the good news, he might attend to my wants on your behalf. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}But I do not wish to do anything without your consent, because I want your generosity to be voluntary and not, as it were, compulsory. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}It may be that he was separated from you for an hour, for this reason, so that you might have him back for ever, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}no longer as a slave, but as something better \uc1\u8211* a dearly loved friend and follower of the Lord, especially dear to me, and how much more so to you, not only as a person, but as your fellow Christian! {\super\cf2\fs24 17}If, then, you count me your friend, receive him as you would me. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}If he has caused you any loss, or owes you anything, charge it to me. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}I, Paul, put my own hand to it \uc1\u8211* I will repay you myself. I say nothing about your owing me your self. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Yes, friend, let me gain something from you because of your union with the Lord. Cheer my heart by your Christlike spirit.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Even as I write, I have such confidence in your compliance with my wishes, that I am sure that you will do even more than I am asking. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Please also get a lodging ready for me, for I hope that I will be given back to you all in answer to your prayers.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Messages and Blessing

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Epaphras, who is my fellow prisoner for Christ Jesus, sends you his greeting; {\super\cf2\fs24 24}and Marcus, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow workers, send theirs.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 25}May the blessing of the Lord Jesus Christ rest on your souls.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Hebrews (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 The Letter to the

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Hebrews
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Christ the Mediator

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}God, who, of old, at many times and in many ways, spoke to our ancestors, by the prophets, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}has in these latter days spoken to us by the Son, whom he appointed the heir of all things, and through whom he made the universe. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For he is the radiance of the glory of God and the expression of his being, upholding all creation by the power of his word; and, when he had made an expiation for the sins of humanity, he took his seat at the right hand of God\uc1\u8217*s Majesty on high, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}having shown himself as much greater than the angels as the name that he has inherited surpasses theirs.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}For to which of the angels did God ever say \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You are my Son; this day I have become your Father\uc1\u8221*?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
or again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will be to him a Father, and he will be to me a Son\uc1\u8221*?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And again, when God brought the first-born into the world, he said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Let all the angels of God bow down before him.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Speaking of the angels, he said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*He makes the winds his angels
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And the flames of fire his servants\uc1\u8221*;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}while of the Son he said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*God is your throne for ever and ever;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
The sceptre of his kingdom is the sceptre of Justice;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}You love righteousness and hates iniquity;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Therefore God, your God, has anointed you with the festal oil more abundantly than your peers.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You, Lord, in the beginning did lay the foundation of the earth,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
and the heavens are the work of your hands.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}They will perish, but you remain;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
as a garment they will all grow old;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}As a mantle you will fold them up,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
and as a garment they will be changed,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
but you are the same, and your years will know no end.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}To which of the angels has God ever said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Sit you at my right hand
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
until I put your enemies as a stool for your feet\uc1\u8221*?
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Are not all the angels spirits in the service of God, sent out to minister for the sake of those who are destined to obtain salvation? 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}Therefore we must give still more heed to what we were taught, so we do not drift away. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}For, if the message which was delivered by angels had its authority confirmed, so that every offence against it, or neglect of it, met with a fitting requital, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}how can we, of all people, expect to escape, if we disregard so great a salvation? It was the Master who at the outset spoke of this salvation, and its authority was confirmed for us by those who heard him, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}while God himself added his testimony to it by signs, and marvels, and many different miracles, as well as by imparting the Holy Spirit as he saw fit.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}God has not given to angels the control of that future world of which we are speaking! {\super\cf2\fs24 6}No; a writer has declared somewhere \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*What are mere mortals that you should remember them?
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Or human beings that you should care for them?
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}You have made them, for a while, lower than angels;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
With glory and honour you have crowned them;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
You have set them over all that your hands have made;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}You have placed all things beneath their feet.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
This \uc1\u8220*placing of everything\uc1\u8221* under humanity means that there was nothing which was not placed under them. As yet, however, we do not see everything placed under humanity. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}What our eyes do see is Jesus, who was made for a while lower than angels, now, because of his sufferings and death, crowned with glory and honour; so that his tasting the bitterness of death should, in God\uc1\u8217*s loving kindness, be on behalf of all humanity. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}It was, indeed, fitting that God, for whom and through whom all things exist, should, when leading many children to glory, make the author of their salvation perfect through suffering. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}For he who purifies, and those whom he purifies, all spring from One; and therefore he is not ashamed to call them his brothers and sisters. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}He says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will tell of your name to my brothers and sisters,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
In the midst of the congregation I will sing your praise.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}And again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*As for me, I will put my trust in God.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
And yet again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*See, here am I and the children whom God gave me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore, since human nature is the common heritage of the children, Jesus also shared it, in order that by death he might render powerless him whose power lies in death \uc1\u8211* that is, the devil \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 15}and so might deliver all those who, from fear of death, had all their lives been living in slavery. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}It was not, surely, to the help of the angels that Jesus came, but to the help of the descendants of Abraham. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And consequently it was necessary that he should in all points be made like his brothers and sisters, in order that he might prove a merciful as well as a faithful high priest in humanity\uc1\u8217*s relations with God, for the purpose of expiating the sins of his people. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}The fact that he himself suffered under temptation enables him to help those who are tempted. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}Therefore, my Christian friends, you who, all alike, have received the call from heaven, fix your attention on Jesus, the apostle and high priest of our religion. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}See how faithful he was to the God who appointed him, as Moses was in the whole house of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}He has been deemed worthy of far higher honour than Moses, just as the founder of the house is held in greater regard than the house itself. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}For every house has its founder, and the founder of the universe is God. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}While the faithful service of Moses in the whole house of God was that of a servant, whose duty was to bear testimony to a message still to come, {\super\cf2\fs24 6}the faithfulness of Christ was that of a son set over the house of God. And we are his house \uc1\u8211* if only we retain, unshaken to the end, the courage and confidence inspired by our hope.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore, as the Holy Spirit says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*If today you hear God\uc1\u8217*s voice,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}harden not your hearts, as when Israel provoked me
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
On the day when they tried my patience in the desert,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Where your ancestors tried my forbearance,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And saw my mighty deeds for forty years.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Therefore I was sorely vexed with that generation,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Their hearts are always straying;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
They have never learned my ways\uc1\u8217*;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}While in my wrath I swore \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
\uc1\u8216*They will never enter upon my rest.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Be careful, friends, that there is never found in anyone of you a wicked and faithless heart, shown by that person separating themselves from the living God. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Rather encourage one another daily \uc1\u8211* while there is a today \uc1\u8211* to prevent anyone among you from being hardened by the deceitfulness of sin. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}For we now all share in the Christ, if indeed we retain, unshaken to the end, the confidence that we had at the first. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}To use the words of scripture \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*If today you hear God\uc1\u8217*s voice,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Harden not your hearts, as when Israel provoked me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Who were they who heard God speak and yet provoked him? Were not they all those who left Egypt under the leadership of Moses? {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And with whom was it that God was sorely vexed for forty years? Was not it with those who had sinned, and who fell dead in the desert? {\super\cf2\fs24 18}And who were they to whom God swore that they should not enter upon his rest, if not those who had proved faithless? {\super\cf2\fs24 19}We see, then, that they failed to enter upon it because of their want of faith.  {\cf1 4}We must, therefore, be very careful, though there is a promise still standing that we will enter upon God\uc1\u8217*s rest, that none of you even appear to have missed it. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}For we have had the good news told us just as they had. But the message which they heard did them no good, since they did not share the faith of those who were attentive to it. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Upon that rest we who have believed are now entering. As God has said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*In my wrath I swore \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
\uc1\u8216*They will never enter upon my rest;\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
Although God\uc1\u8217*s work was finished at the creation of the world; {\super\cf2\fs24 4}for, in a passage referring to the seventh day, you will find these words \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*God rested on the seventh day after all his work.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}On the other hand, we read in that passage \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*They will never enter upon my rest.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Since, then, there is still a promise that some will enter upon this rest, and since those who were first told the good news did not enter upon it, because of their disbelief, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}again God fixed a day. \uc1\u8220*Today,\uc1\u8221* he said, speaking after a long interval through the mouth of David, in the passage already quoted \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*If today you hear God\uc1\u8217*s voice
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Harden not your hearts.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Now if Joshua had given \uc1\u8220*rest\uc1\u8221* to the people, God would not have spoken of another and later day. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}There is, then, a Sabbath rest still awaiting God\uc1\u8217*s people. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}For the person who enters upon God\uc1\u8217*s rest do themselves rest after their work, just as God did. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Let us, therefore, make every effort to enter upon that rest, so that none of us fall through such disbelief as that of which we have had an example. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}God\uc1\u8217*s message is a living and active power, sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing its way until it penetrates soul and spirit \uc1\u8211* not the joints only but the marrow \uc1\u8211* and detecting the inmost thoughts and purposes of the mind. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}There is no created thing that can hide itself from the sight of God. Everything is exposed and laid bare before the eyes of him to whom we have to give account.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}We have, then, in Jesus, the Son of God, a great high priest who has passed into the highest heaven; let us, therefore, hold fast to the faith which we have professed. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Our high priest is not one unable to sympathise with our weaknesses, but one who has in every way been tempted, exactly as we have been, but without sinning. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore, let us draw near boldly to the throne of love, to find pity and love for the hour of need. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 5}Every high priest, taken from among the people, is appointed as their representative in their relations with God, to offer both gifts and sacrifices in expiation of sins. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}And he is able to sympathise with the ignorant and deluded, since he is himself subject to weakness, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}and is therefore bound to offer sacrifices for sins, not only for the people, but equally so for himself. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Nor does anyone take that high office on themselves, until they have been called to do so by God, as Aaron was. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}In the same way, even the Christ did not take the honour of the high priesthood on himself, but he was appointed by him who said to him \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You are my Son; this day I have become your Father\uc1\u8221*;
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}and on another occasion also \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You are a priest for all time of the order of Melchizedek.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Jesus, in the days of his earthly life, offered prayers and supplications, with earnest cries and with tears, to him who was able to save him from death; and he was heard because of his devout submission. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Son though he was, he learned obedience from his sufferings; {\super\cf2\fs24 9}and, being made perfect, he became to all those who obey him the source of eternal salvation, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}while God himself pronounced him a high priest of the order of Melchizedek.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Now on this subject I have much to say, but it is difficult to explain it to you, because you have shown yourselves so slow to learn. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}For whereas, considering the time that has elapsed, you ought to be teaching others, you still need someone to teach you the alphabet of the divine revelation, and need again to be fed with milk instead of with \uc1\u8220*solid food.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 13}For everyone who still has to take milk knows nothing of the teaching of righteousness; they are a mere infant. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}But solid food is for Christians of mature faith \uc1\u8211* those whose faculties have been trained by practice to distinguish right from wrong.  {\cf1 6}Therefore, let us leave behind the elementary teaching about the Christ and press on to perfection, not always laying over again a foundation of repentance for a lifeless formality, of faith in God \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 2}teaching concerning baptisms and the laying on of hands, the resurrection of the dead and a final judgment. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Yes and, with God\uc1\u8217*s help, we will. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}For if those who were once for all brought into the light, and learned to appreciate the gift from heaven, and came to share in the Holy Spirit, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}and learned to appreciate the beauty of the divine message, and the new powers of the coming age \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 6}if those, I say, fell away, it would be impossible to bring them again to repentance; they would be crucifying the Son of God over again for themselves, and exposing him to open contempt. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Ground that drinks in the showers that from time to time fall on it, and produces vegetation useful to those for whom it is tilled, receives a blessing from God; {\super\cf2\fs24 8}but, if it bears thorns and thistles, it is regarded as worthless, it is in danger of being cursed, and its end will be the fire.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}But about you, dear friends, even though we speak in this way, we are confident of better things \uc1\u8211* of things that point to your salvation. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}For God is not unjust; he will not forget the work that you did, and the love that you showed for his name, in sending help to your fellow Christians \uc1\u8211* as you are still doing. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}But our great desire is that every one of you should be equally earnest to attain to a full conviction that our hope will be fulfilled, and that you should keep that hope to the end. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Then you will not show yourselves slow to learn, but you will copy those who, through faith and patience, are now entering upon the enjoyment of God\uc1\u8217*s promises.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}When God gave his promise to Abraham, since there was no one greater by whom he could swear, he swore by himself. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}His words were \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*I will assuredly bless you and increase your numbers.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}And so, after patiently waiting, Abraham obtained the fulfilment of God\uc1\u8217*s promise. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}People, of course, swear by what is greater than themselves, and with them an oath is accepted as putting a matter beyond all dispute. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And therefore God, in his desire to show, with unmistakable plainness, to those who were to enter on the enjoyment of what he had promised, the unchangeableness of his purpose, bound himself with an oath. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}For he intended us to find great encouragement in these two unchangeable things, which make it impossible for God to prove false \uc1\u8211* we, I mean, who fled for safety where we might lay hold on the hope set before us. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}This hope is an anchor for our souls, secure and strong, and it reaches into the sanctuary that lies behind the curtain, {\super\cf2\fs24 20}where Jesus, our forerunner, has entered on our behalf, after being made for all time a high priest of the order of Melchizedek. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Paramount Priesthood of the Christ

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 7}It was this Melchizedek, king of Salem and priest of the Most High God, who met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings, and gave him his blessing; {\super\cf2\fs24 2}and it was to him that Abraham allotted a tithe of all the spoil. The meaning of his name is \uc1\u8220*king of righteousness,\uc1\u8221* and besides that, he was also king of Salem, which means \uc1\u8220*king of peace.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 3}There is no record of his father, or mother, or lineage, nor again of any beginning of his days, or end of his life. In this he resembles the Son of God, and stands before us as a priest whose priesthood is continuous.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Consider, then the importance of this Melchizedek, to whom even the patriarch Abraham himself gave a tithe of the choicest spoils. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Those descendants of Levi, who are from time to time appointed to the priesthood, are directed to collect tithes from the people in accordance with the Law \uc1\u8211* that is from their own kindred, although they also are descended from Abraham. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But Melchizedek, although not of this lineage, received tithes from Abraham, and gave his blessing to the man who had God\uc1\u8217*s promises. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Now no one can dispute that it is the superior who blesses the inferior. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}In the one case the tithes are received by people who are mortal; in the other case by one about whom there is the statement that his life still continues. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Moreover, in a sense, even Levi, who is the receiver of the tithes, has, through Abraham, paid tithes; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}for Levi was still in the body of his ancestor when Melchizedek met Abraham.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}If, then, perfection had been attainable through the Levitical priesthood \uc1\u8211* and it was under this priesthood that the people received the Law \uc1\u8211* why was it still necessary that a priest of a different order should appear, a priest of the order of Melchizedek and not of the order of Aaron? {\super\cf2\fs24 12}With the change of the priesthood a change of the Law became a necessity. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}And he of whom all this is said belonged to quite a different tribe, no member of which has ever served at the altar. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}For it is plain that our Lord had sprung from the tribe of Judah, though of that tribe Moses said nothing about their being priests. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}All this becomes even yet plainer when we remember that a new priest has appeared, resembling Melchizedek, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}and that he was appointed, not under a Law regulating only earthly matters, but by virtue of a life beyond the reach of death; {\super\cf2\fs24 17}for that is the meaning of the declaration \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You are for all time a priest of the order of Melchizedek.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}On the one hand, we have the abolition of a previous regulation as being both inefficient and useless {\super\cf2\fs24 19}(for the Law never brought anything to perfection); and, on the other hand, we have the introduction of a better hope, which enables us to draw near to God. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Then again, the appointment of this new priest was ratified by an oath, which is not so with the Levitical priests, {\super\cf2\fs24 21}but his appointment was ratified by an oath, when God said to him \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The Lord has sworn, and will not change, \uc1\u8216*You are a priest for all time.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 22}And the oath shows the corresponding superiority of the covenant of which Jesus is appointed the surety. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Again, new Levitical priests are continually being appointed, because death prevents their remaining in office; {\super\cf2\fs24 24}but Jesus remains for all time, and therefore the priesthood that he holds will never pass to another. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}And that is why he is able to save perfectly those who come to God through him, living for ever, as he does, to intercede of their behalf.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 26}This was the high priest that we needed \uc1\u8211* holy, innocent, spotless, withdrawn from sinners, exalted above the highest heaven, {\super\cf2\fs24 27}one who has no need to offer sacrifices daily as those high priests have, first for their own sins, and then for those of the people. For this he did once and for all, when he offered himself as the sacrifice. {\super\cf2\fs24 28}The Law appoints as high priests men who are weak, but the words of God\uc1\u8217*s oath, which was later than the Law, name the Son as, for all time, the perfect priest. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 8}To sum up what I have been saying: Such is the high priest that we have, one who has taken his seat at the right hand of the throne of God\uc1\u8217*s Majesty in heaven, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}where he serves in the sanctuary, in that true tent set up by the Lord and not by man. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Every high priest is appointed for the purpose of offering gifts and sacrifices to God; it follows, therefore, that this high priest must have some offering to make. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}If he were, however, still on earth, he would not even be a priest, since there are already priests who offer the gifts as the Law directs. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}(These priests, it is true, are engaged in a service which is only a copy and shadow of the heavenly realities, as is shown by the directions given to Moses when he was about to construct the tent. \uc1\u8220*Look to it,\uc1\u8221* are the words, \uc1\u8220*that you make every part in accordance with the pattern shown you on the mountain.\uc1\u8221*) {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But Jesus, as we see, has obtained a ministry as far excelling theirs, as the covenant of which he is the intermediary, based, as it is, on better promises, excels the former covenant. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}If that first covenant had been faultless, there would have been no occasion for a second. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}But, finding fault with the people, God says \uc1\u8211*
