{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The New Revelation and the Old

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 9}It is true that even the first covenant had its regulations for divine worship, and its sanctuary \uc1\u8211* though only a material one. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}For a tent was constructed, with an outer part which contained the stand for the lamps, and the table, and the consecrated bread. This is called the sanctuary. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}The part of the tent behind the second curtain is called the inner sanctuary. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}In it is the gold incense-altar, and the ark containing the covenant, completely covered with gold. In the ark is a gold casket containing the manna, Aaron\uc1\u8217*s rod that budded, and the tablets on which the covenant was written; {\super\cf2\fs24 5}while above it, and overshadowing the cover on which atonement was made, are the cherubim of the presence. Now is not the time to discuss these things in detail. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Such, then, was the arrangement of the tent. Into the outer part priests are constantly going, in the discharge of their sacred duties; {\super\cf2\fs24 7}but into the inner only the high priest goes, and that but once a year, and never without taking the blood of a victim, which he offers on his own behalf, and on behalf of the errors of the people. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}By this the Holy Spirit is teaching that the way into the sanctuary was hidden, as long as the outer part of the tent still remained. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}For that was only a type, to continue down to the present time; and, in keeping with it, both gifts and sacrifices are offered, though incapable of satisfying the conscience of the worshiper; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}the whole system being concerned only with food and drink and various ablutions \uc1\u8211* external ceremonials imposed until the coming of the new order.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}But, when Christ came, he appeared as high priest of that better system which was established; and he entered through that nobler and more perfect tent, not made by human hands \uc1\u8211* that is to say, not a part of this present creation. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Nor was it with the blood of goats and calves, but with his own blood, that he entered, once and for all, into the sanctuary, and obtained our eternal deliverance. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}For, if the blood of goats and bulls, and the sprinkling of the ashes of a heifer, purify those who have been defiled (as far as ceremonial purification goes), {\super\cf2\fs24 14}how much more will the blood of the Christ, who, through his eternal Spirit, offered himself up to God, as a victim without blemish, purify our consciences from a lifeless formality, and fit us for the service of the living God! {\super\cf2\fs24 15}And that is why he is the intermediary of a new covenant; in order that, as a death has taken place to effect a deliverance from the offences committed under the first covenant, those who have received the call may obtain the eternal inheritance promised to them. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Whenever such a covenant as a will is in question, the death of the testator must of necessity be alleged. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}For such a covenant takes effect only on death, it does not come into force as long as the testator is alive. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}This explains why even the first covenant was not ratified without the shedding of blood. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}For, when every command had been announced to all the people by Moses in accordance with the Law, he took the blood of the calves and of the goats, with water, scarlet wool, and a bunch of hyssop, and sprinkled even the book of the Law, as well as all the people, {\super\cf2\fs24 20}saying, as he did so \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*This is the blood that renders valid the covenant which God has commanded to be made with you.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 21}And in the same way he also sprinkled with the blood the tent and all the things that were used in public worship. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Indeed, under the Law, almost everything is purified with blood; and, unless blood is shed, no forgiveness is to be obtained.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 23}While, then, it was necessary for the copies of the heavenly realities to be purified by such means as these, the heavenly realities themselves required better sacrifices. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}For it was not into a sanctuary made by human hands, which merely foreshadowed the true one, that Christ entered, but into heaven itself, so that he might now appear in the presence of God on our behalf. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Nor yet was it to offer himself may times, as year after year the high priest entered the sanctuary with an offering of blood \uc1\u8211* but not his own blood; {\super\cf2\fs24 26}for then Christ would have had to undergo death many times since the creation of the world. But now, once and for all, at the close of the age, he has appeared, in order to abolish sin by the sacrifice of himself. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}And, as it is ordained for people to die but once (death being followed by judgment), {\super\cf2\fs24 28}so it is with the Christ. He was offered up once and for all, to bear away the sins of many; and the second time he will appear \uc1\u8211* but without any burden of sin \uc1\u8211* to those who are waiting for him, to bring salvation. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 10}The Law, though able to foreshadow the better system which was coming, never had its actual substance. Its priests, with those sacrifices which they offer continuously year after year, can never make those who come to worship perfect. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Otherwise, would not the offering of these sacrifices have been abandoned, as the worshipers, having been once purified, would have had their consciences clear from sins? {\super\cf2\fs24 3}But, on the contrary, these sacrifices recall their sins to mind year after year. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}For the blood of bulls and goats is powerless to remove sins. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}That is why, when he was coming into the world, the Christ declared \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Sacrifice and offering you do not desire, but you provide for me a body;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}You take no pleasure in burnt offerings and sacrifices for sin.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}So I said, \uc1\u8216*See, I have come\uc1\u8217* (as is written of me in the pages of the book),
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
\uc1\u8216*To do your will, God.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}First come the words \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*You do not desire, nor do you take pleasure in, sacrifices, offerings, burnt offerings, and sacrifices for sin\uc1\u8221* (offerings regularly made under the Law), {\super\cf2\fs24 9}and then there is added \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*See, I have come to do your will.\uc1\u8221* The former sacrifices are set aside to be replaced by the latter. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}And it is in the fulfilment of the will of God that we have been purified by the sacrifice, once and for all, of the body of Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Every other priest stands day after day at his ministrations, and offers the same sacrifices over and over again \uc1\u8211* sacrifices that can never take sins away. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}But, this priest, after he had offered one sacrifice for sins, which should serve for all time, \uc1\u8220*took his seat at the right hand of God,\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 13}and has since then been waiting \uc1\u8220*for his enemies to be put as a stool for his feet.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 14}By a single offering he has made perfect for all time those who are being purified. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}We have also the testimony of the Holy Spirit. For, after saying \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8220*\uc1\u8216*This is the covenant that I will make with them
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
After those days,\uc1\u8217* says the Lord;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8216*I will impress my laws on their hearts,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And will inscribe them on their minds,\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}then we have \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*And their sins and their iniquities I will no longer remember.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}And, when these are forgiven, there is no further need of an offering for sin.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Encouragement and Warning

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Therefore, friends, since we may enter the sanctuary with confidence, in virtue of the blood of Jesus, {\super\cf2\fs24 20}by the way which he inaugurated for us \uc1\u8211* a new and living way, a way through the sanctuary curtain (that is, his human nature); {\super\cf2\fs24 21}and, since we have in him \uc1\u8220*a great priest set over the house of God,\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 22}let us draw near to God in all sincerity of heart and in perfect faith, with our hearts purified by the sprinkled blood from all consciousness of wrong, and with our bodies washed with pure water. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}Let us maintain the confession of our hope unshaken, for he who has given us his promise will not fail us. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}Let us vie with one another in a rivalry of love and noble actions. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}And let us not, as some do, cease to meet together; but, on the contrary, let us encourage one another, and all the more, now that you see the day drawing near. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}Remember, if we sin wilfully after we have gained a full knowledge of the truth, there can be no further sacrifice for sin; {\super\cf2\fs24 27}there is only a fearful anticipation of judgment, and a burning indignation which will destroy all opponents. {\super\cf2\fs24 28}When someone disregarded the Law of Moses, they were, on the evidence of two or three witnesses, put to death without pity. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}How much worse then, think you, will be the punishment deserved by those who have trampled underfoot the Son of God, who have treated the blood that rendered the covenant valid \uc1\u8211* the blood by which they were purified \uc1\u8211* as if it were not holy, and who have outraged the Spirit of love? {\super\cf2\fs24 30}We know who it was that said \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*It is for me to avenge, I will requite\uc1\u8221*;
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
and again \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*The Lord will judge his people.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 31}It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 32}Call to mind those early days in which, after you had received the light, you patiently underwent a long and painful conflict. {\super\cf2\fs24 33}Sometimes, in consequence of the taunts and injuries heaped on you, you became a public spectacle; and sometimes you suffered through having shown yourselves to be the friends of people who were in the same position in which you had been. {\super\cf2\fs24 34}For you not only sympathised with those who were in prison, but you even took the confiscation of your possessions joyfully, knowing, as you did, that you had in yourselves a greater possession and a lasting one. {\super\cf2\fs24 35}Do not, therefore, abandon the confidence that you have gained, for it has a great reward awaiting it. {\super\cf2\fs24 36}You still have need of patient endurance, in order that, when you have done God\uc1\u8217*s will, you may obtain the fulfilment of his promise.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 37}\uc1\u8220*For there is indeed but a very little while
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
Ere He who is coming will have come, without delay;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 38}And through faith the righteous will find life,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
But, if anyone draws back, my heart can find no pleasure in them.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 39}But we do not belong to those who draw back, to their ruin, but to those who have faith, to the saving of their souls. 
