{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Greeting

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}James, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, greets the twelve tribes that are living abroad.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Advice on Various Subjects

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}My friends, whatever trials you may face from time to time, always regard them as a reason for rejoicing, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}knowing, as you do, that the testing of your faith develops endurance. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}And let endurance do its work perfectly, so that you may be altogether perfect, and in no respect lacking.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}If any one of you lacks wisdom, they should ask wisdom from the God who gives freely to everyone without reproach, and it will be given to them. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But they should ask with confidence, never doubting; for the person who doubts is like a wave of the sea driven here and there at the mercy of the wind \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Such a person must not expect that they will receive anything from the Lord, {\super\cf2\fs24 8}vacillating as they are, irresolute at every turn.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Let a follower in humble circumstances be proud of their exalted position, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}but a rich follower of their humiliation; for the rich will pass away like a wild flower. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}As the sun rises, and the hot wind blows, the plant withers, its flower fades, and all its beauty is gone. So is it with the rich. In the midst of their pursuits they will wither away.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Blessed is the person who remains firm under temptation, for, when they have stood the test, they will receive the crown of life, which the Lord has promised to those who love him. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Let no one say, when they are tempted, \uc1\u8216*It is God who is tempting me!\uc1\u8217* For God, who cannot be tempted to do wrong, does not himself tempt anyone. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}A man is in every case tempted by their own passions \uc1\u8211* allured and enticed by them. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Then passion conceives and gives birth to sin, and sin, on reaching maturity, brings forth death. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Do not be deceived, my dear friends. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Every good thing given us, and every perfect gift, is from above, and comes down to us from the Father of the lights in the heavens, who is himself never subject to change or to eclipse. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Because he so willed, he gave us life, through the message of the truth, so that we should be, as it were, a kind of first fruits of his creation.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Mark this, my dear friends \uc1\u8211* Let everyone be quick to listen, slow to speak, and slow to get angry; {\super\cf2\fs24 20}for human anger does not forward the righteous purpose of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Therefore, get rid of all filthiness and whatever wickedness still remains, and in a humble spirit receive that message which has been planted in your hearts and is able to save your souls. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Put that message into practice, and do not merely listen to it \uc1\u8211* deceiving yourselves. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}For, when anyone listens to it and does not practice it, they are like a person looking at their own face in a mirror. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}They look at themselves, then go on their way, {\super\cf2\fs24 25}but the person who looks carefully into the perfect Law, the Law of freedom, and continues to do so, not listening to it and then forgetting it, but putting it into practice \uc1\u8211* that person will be blessed in what they do. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}When a person appears to be religious, yet does not bridle their tongue, but imposes on their own conscience, that person\uc1\u8217*s religious observances are valueless. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}That religious observance which is pure and spotless in the eyes of God our Father is this \uc1\u8211* to visit orphans and widows in their trouble, and to keep oneself uncontaminated by the world. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Warning on Various Subjects

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}My friends, are you really trying to combine faith in Jesus Christ, our glorified Lord, with discrimination? {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Suppose a visitor should enter your synagogue, with gold rings and in grand clothes, and suppose a poor man should come in also, in shabby clothes, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}and you show more respect to the visitor who is wearing grand clothes, and say \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*There is a good seat for you here,\uc1\u8217* but to the poor man \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*You must stand; or sit down there by my footstool,\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Haven\uc1\u8217*t you made distinctions among yourselves, and used evil standards of judgement? {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Listen, my dear friends. Has not God chosen those who are poor in the things of this world to be rich through their faith, and to possess the kingdom which he has promised to those who love him? {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But you \uc1\u8211* you insult the poor man! Isn\uc1\u8217*t it the rich who oppress you? Isn\uc1\u8217*t it they who drag you into law courts? {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Isn\uc1\u8217*t it they who malign that honourable name spoken over you at your baptism? {\super\cf2\fs24 8}If you keep the royal law which runs \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*You must love your neighbour as you love yourself,\uc1\u8221* you are doing right; {\super\cf2\fs24 9}but, if you discriminate, you commit a sin, and stand convicted by that same law of being offenders against it. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}For a person who has laid the Law, as a whole, to heart, but has failed in one particular, is accountable for breaking all its provisions. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}He who said \uc1\u8220*You must not commit adultery\uc1\u8221* also said \uc1\u8220*You must not murder.\uc1\u8221* If, then, you commit murder but not adultery, you are still an offender against the Law. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Therefore, speak and act as people who are to be judged by the \uc1\u8220*Law of freedom.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 13}For there will be justice without mercy for the person who has not acted mercifully. Mercy triumphs over Justice.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}My friends, what good is it if someone claims that they have faith, but they do not prove it by actions? Can such faith save them? {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Suppose some brother or sister should be in need of clothes and of daily bread, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}and one of you says to them \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Go, and peace be with you; keep warm and eat well!\uc1\u8217* and yet you do not actually give them the necessities of life, what good would it be to them? {\super\cf2\fs24 17}In just the same way faith, if not followed by actions, is, by itself, a lifeless thing. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Someone, indeed, may say \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*You are a man of faith, and I am a man of action.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
\uc1\u8216*Then show me your faith,\uc1\u8217* I reply, \uc1\u8216*apart from any actions, and I will show you my faith by my actions.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 19}It is a part of your faith, is it not, that there is one God? Good; yet even the demons have that faith, and tremble at the thought. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Now do you really want to understand, fool, how it is that faith without actions leads to nothing? {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Look at our ancestor, Abraham. Was he not justified by his actions after he had offered his son, Isaac, on the altar? {\super\cf2\fs24 22}You see how, in his case, faith and actions went together; that his faith was perfected as the result of his actions; {\super\cf2\fs24 23}and that in this way the words of scripture came true \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Abraham believed God, and that was regarded by God as righteousness,\uc1\u8217* and \uc1\u8216*He was called the friend of God.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 24}You see, then, that a person is justified by actions, and not by faith alone. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Wasn\uc1\u8217*t it the same with the prostitute, Rahab? Was she not justified by her actions, after she had welcomed the messengers and helped them escape by another road? {\super\cf2\fs24 26}Just as a body is dead without a spirit, so faith is dead without actions. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}Not many of you should become teachers, my friends, because you know that we who teach will be judged more strictly than others. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}We often make mistakes, every one of us. Anyone who does not make mistakes when speaking is indeed a perfect person, able to bridle their whole body as well. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}When we put bits into horses\uc1\u8217* mouths to make them obey us, we change their course the rest of their bodies. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Again, think of ships. Large as they are, and even when driven by fierce winds, they are guided by a very small rudder and steered in whatever direction the man at the helm may determine. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}So is it with the tongue. Small as it is, it is a great boaster. Think how a tiny spark may set the largest forest ablaze! {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And the tongue is like a spark. It is a world of unrighteousness among the parts of our body. It contaminates the whole body; it sets the whole course of our existence on fire, and is itself set on fire by the flames of Gehenna. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}For while all kinds of animals, birds and reptiles and sea creatures can be tamed and have been tamed by humans, {\super\cf2\fs24 8}no human being can tame the tongue. It is a restless plague! It is charged with deadly poison! {\super\cf2\fs24 9}With it we bless our Lord and Father, and with it we curse people who are made \uc1\u8220*in God\uc1\u8217*s likeness.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}From the very same mouth come blessings and curses! My friends, it is not right that this should be so. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Does a spring give both good and bad water from the same source? {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Can a fig tree, my friends, bear olives? Or a vine bear figs? No, nor can a brackish well give good water.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Who among you claims to be wise and intelligent? They should show that their actions are the outcome of a good life lived in the humility of true wisdom. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}But if you harbour bitter envy and a spirit of rivalry in your hearts, do not boast or deny the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}That is not the wisdom which comes from above; no, it is earthly, animalistic, demonic. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}For where envy and rivalry exist, there you will also find disorder and all kinds of bad, worthless actions. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}But the wisdom from above is, before everything else, pure; then peace-loving, gentle, open to conviction, rich in compassion and good deeds, and free from partiality and insincerity. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Justice is the harvest peacemakers will reap from seeds sown in a spirit of peace. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 4}What is the cause of the fighting and quarrelling that goes on among you? Isn\uc1\u8217*t it to be found in the desires which are always at war within you? {\super\cf2\fs24 2}You crave, yet do not have, so you commit murder, so You covet, yet cannot gain your end. You quarrel and fight. You do not have, because you do not ask. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}You ask, yet do not receive, because you ask for a wrong purpose \uc1\u8211* to spend what you get on your pleasures. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Unfaithful people! Don\uc1\u8217*t you know that to be friends with the world means to be at enmity with God? Therefore whoever chooses to be friends with the world makes himself an enemy to God. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Do you suppose scripture means nothing when it says, \uc1\u8220*Envy results from the longings of the spirit which God has implanted within you?\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But he gives us greater grace; and that is why it says, \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*God opposes the haughty,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
but gives grace to the humble.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore submit to God. Stand up to the devil, and he will flee from you. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Make your hands clean, you sinners; and your hearts pure, you vacillators! {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Grieve, mourn, and lament! Let your laughter be turned to mourning, and your happiness to gloom! {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Humble yourselves before the Lord, and he will exalt you. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Do not disparage one another, friends. The person who disparages others, or passes judgment on them, disparages the Law and passes judgment on the Law. But, if you pass judgment on the Law, you are not obeying it, but judging it. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}There is only one lawgiver and judge \uc1\u8211* he who has the power both to save and to destroy. So then who are you to pass judgment on your neighbour?
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Listen to me, you who say \uc1\u8220*Today or tomorrow we will go to such and such a town and spend a year there, doing business and making money,\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 14}yet you do not know what your life will be like tomorrow! For you are but a puff of smoke that appears for a little while and then vanishes. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Instead you should say \uc1\u8220*If the Lord wills, we will live and do this or that.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 16}But as it is, you are boasting presumptuously! All such boasting is wicked. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}The person, then, who knows what is right but fails to do it \uc1\u8211* that is sin in them. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 5}Listen to me, you rich people, weep and wail for the miseries that are coming upon you! {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Your riches have wasted away, and your clothes have become moth-eaten. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Your gold and silver are rusted; and the rust on them will be evidence against you, and will eat into your flesh. It was fire, so to speak, that you stored up for yourselves in these last days. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Listen! The wages you have held back from the labourers who mowed your fields are crying out against you, and the outcries of your harvesters have reached the ears of the Lord of Hosts! {\super\cf2\fs24 5}You have lived on earth a life of extravagance and luxury; you have indulged your fancies in a time of bloodshed. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}You have condemned, you have murdered, the righteous one! Must not God be opposed to you?
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Concluding Appeal

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Be patient, then, friends, until the coming of the Lord. Even the farmer has to wait for the precious fruit of the earth, watching over it patiently, until it has had the spring and summer rains. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}And you must be patient also, and not be discouraged; for the Lord\uc1\u8217*s coming is near. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Do not make complaints against one another, friends, or judgment will be passed on you. The judge is already standing at the door! {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Friends, as an example of the patient endurance of suffering, take the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}We count those who displayed such endurance blessed! You have heard, too, of Job\uc1\u8217*s endurance, and have seen what the Lord\uc1\u8217*s purpose was, for \uc1\u8220*the Lord is full of pity and compassion.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Above all things, my friends, never take an oath, either by heaven, or by earth, or by anything else. Let your \uc1\u8220*Yes\uc1\u8221* suffice for yes, and \uc1\u8220*No\uc1\u8221* for no, so that you may escape condemnation.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}If anyone of you is in trouble, they should pray; if anyone is happy, they should sing hymns. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}If anyone of you is ill, they should send for the church elders, and let them pray over them, anointing them with oil in the name of the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}The prayer offered in faith will save the person who is sick, and the Lord will raise them from their bed; and if they have committed sins, they will be forgiven. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore, confess your sins to one another and pray for one another, so that you may be cured. Great is the power of a good person\uc1\u8217*s fervent prayer. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Elijah was only human like ourselves, but, when he prayed fervently that it might not rain, no rain fell on the land for three and a half years. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}And, when he prayed again, the clouds brought rain, and the land bore crops. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}My friends, should one of you be led astray from the truth, and someone bring them back again, {\super\cf2\fs24 20}be sure that the person who brings a sinner back from their mistaken ways will save that person\uc1\u8217*s soul from death, and will cover a multitude of sins.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 1 Peter (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Peter\uc1\u8217*s First Letter
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}To the people of God who are living abroad, dispersed throughout Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Roman Asia, and Bithynia, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}and who were chosen in accordance with the foreknowledge of God the Father, through the consecration of the Spirit, to learn obedience, and to be purified by the sprinkling of the blood of Jesus Christ, from Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ. May blessing and peace be yours in ever increasing measure.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Christian\uc1\u8217*s Hope of Salvation

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Blessed is the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has, in his great mercy, through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}given us the new life of undying hope, that promises an inheritance, imperishable, stainless, unfading, which has been reserved for you in heaven \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 5}for you who, through faith, are being guarded by the power of God, awaiting a salvation that is ready to be revealed in the last days. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}At the thought of this you are full of exultation, though (if it has been necessary) you have suffered for the moment somewhat from various trials; {\super\cf2\fs24 7}that the genuineness of your faith \uc1\u8211* a thing far more precious than gold, which is perishable, yet has to be tested by fire \uc1\u8211* may win praise and glory and honour at the appearing of Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Though you have never seen him, yet you love him; though you do not even now see him, yet you believe in him, and exalt with a triumphant happiness too great for words, {\super\cf2\fs24 9}as you receive the reward of your faith in the salvation of your souls! {\super\cf2\fs24 10}It was this salvation that the prophets, who spoke long ago of the blessing intended for you, sought, and strove to comprehend; {\super\cf2\fs24 11}as they strove to discern what that time could be, to which the Spirit of Christ within them was pointing, when foretelling the sufferings that Christ would have to endure, and the glories that would follow. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}And it was revealed to them that it was not for themselves, but for you, that they were acting as Ministers of the truths which have now been told to you, by those who, with the help of the Holy Spirit sent from heaven, have brought you the good news \uc1\u8211* truths into which even angels long to look.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Christian\uc1\u8217*s Character

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Therefore concentrate your minds, with the strictest self-control, and fix your hopes on the blessing that is coming for you at the appearing of Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Be like obedient children; do not let your lives be shaped by the passions which once swayed you in the days of your ignorance, {\super\cf2\fs24 15}but in your whole life show yourselves to be holy, after the pattern of the Holy One from whom you received your call. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}For scripture says \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*You will be holy, because I am holy.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And since you call on him as \uc1\u8220*Father,\uc1\u8221* who judges everyone impartially by what he has done, let respectful awe be the spirit of your lives during the time of your stay on earth. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}For you know that it was not by perishable things, such as silver and gold, that you were ransomed from the aimless way of living which was handed down to you from your ancestors, {\super\cf2\fs24 19}but by precious blood, as it were of a lamb, unblemished and spotless, the blood of Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Destined for this before the beginning of the world, he has been revealed in these last days for your sakes, {\super\cf2\fs24 21}who, through him, are faithful to God who raised him from the dead and gave him honour, so that your faith and hope are now in God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Now that, by your obedience to the truth, you have purified your lives, so that there is growing up among you a genuine affection, love one another earnestly with all your hearts; {\super\cf2\fs24 23}since your new life has come, not from perishable, but imperishable, seed, through the message of the Everliving God. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}For \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*All earthly life is but as grass,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
and all its splendour as the flower of grass.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
The grass fades,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
its flower falls,
\par}

{\pard\fi-1720\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 25}but the teaching of the Lord remains for ever.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
And that is the teaching of the good news which has been told to you.  {\cf1 2}Now that you have done with all malice, all deceitfulness, insincerity, jealous feelings, and all backbiting, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}like newly born infants, crave pure spiritual milk, so that you may be enabled by it to grow until you attain salvation \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 3}since \uc1\u8220*you have found by experience that the Lord is kind.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Come to him, then, as to a living stone, rejected, indeed, by men, but in God\uc1\u8217*s eyes choice and precious; {\super\cf2\fs24 5}and, as living stones, form yourselves into a spiritual house, to be a consecrated priesthood, for the offering of spiritual sacrifices that will be acceptable to God through Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}For there is a passage of scripture that runs \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*See, I am placing in Zion a choice and precious corner-stone;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And those who believe in him will have no cause for shame.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}It is to you, then, who believe in him that he is precious, but to those who do not believe he is \uc1\u8220*a stone which, though rejected by the builders, has now itself become the corner-stone,\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 8}and \uc1\u8220*a stumbling-block, and a rock which will prove a hindrance.\uc1\u8221* They stumble because they do not accept the message. This was the fate destined for them. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}But you are \uc1\u8220*a chosen people, a royal priesthood, a consecrated nation, God\uc1\u8217*s own people,\uc1\u8221* entrusted with the proclamation of the goodness of him who called you out of darkness into his wonderful light. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Once you were \uc1\u8220*not a people,\uc1\u8221* but now you are \uc1\u8220*God\uc1\u8217*s people\uc1\u8221*; once you \uc1\u8220*had not found mercy,\uc1\u8221* but now you \uc1\u8220*have found mercy.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Practical Appeals in view of the Dangers of the Times.

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Dear friends, I beg you, as pilgrims and strangers on earth, to refrain from indulging the cravings of your earthly nature, for they make war on the soul. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Let your daily life among the Gentiles be so upright, that, whenever they malign you as evil-doers, they may learn, as they watch, from the uprightness of your conduct, to praise God \uc1\u8220*at the time when he will visit them.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Submit to all human institutions for the Lord\uc1\u8217*s sake, alike to the emperor as the supreme authority, {\super\cf2\fs24 14}and to governors as sent by him to punish evil-doers and to commend those who do right. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}For God\uc1\u8217*s will is this \uc1\u8211* that you should silence the ignorance of foolish people by doing what is right. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Act as free people, yet not using your freedom as those do who make it a cloak for wickedness, but as Servants of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Show honour to everyone, love the Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers, \uc1\u8220*revere God, honour the emperor.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Those of you who are domestic servants should always be submissive and respectful to their masters, not only to those who are good and considerate, but also to those who are arbitrary. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}For this wins God\uc1\u8217*s approval when, because conscious of God\uc1\u8217*s presence, a person who is suffering unjustly bears their troubles patiently. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}What credit can you claim when, after doing wrong, you take your punishment for it patiently? But, on the other hand, if, after doing right, you take your sufferings patiently, that does win the approval of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}For it was to this that you were called! For Christ, too, suffered \uc1\u8211* on your behalf \uc1\u8211* and left you an example, that you should follow in his steps. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}He \uc1\u8220*never sinned, nor was anything deceitful ever heard from his lips.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 23}He was abused, but he did not answer with abuse; he suffered, but he did not threaten; he entrusted himself to him whose judgments are just. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}And he \uc1\u8220*himself carried our sins\uc1\u8221* in his own body to the cross, so that we might die to our sins, and live for righteousness. \uc1\u8220*His bruising was your healing.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Once you were straying like sheep, but now you have returned to the shepherd and guardian of your souls. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}Again, you married women should submit to your husbands, so that if any of them reject the message, they may, apart from the message, be won over, by the conduct of their wives, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}as they see your pure, reverent conduct. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Yours should be, not the external adornment of the arrangement of the hair, the wearing of jewellery, or the putting on of dresses, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}but the inner life with the imperishable beauty of a quiet and gentle spirit; for this is very precious in God\uc1\u8217*s sight. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}It was by this that the holy women of old, who rested their hopes on God, adorned themselves; submitting to their husbands, {\super\cf2\fs24 6}as Sarah did, who obeyed Abraham, and called him master. And you are her true children, as long as you live good lives, and let nothing terrify you.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Again, those of you who are married men should live considerately with their wives, showing due regard to their sex, as physically weaker than their own, and not forgetting that they share with you in the gift of life. Then you will be able to pray without hindrance.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Lastly, you should all be united, sympathetic, full of love for each other, kind-hearted, humble-minded; {\super\cf2\fs24 9}never returning evil for evil, or abuse for abuse, but, on the contrary, blessing. It was to this that you were called \uc1\u8211* to obtain a blessing!
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*The person who wants to enjoy life
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And see happy days \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
They should keep their tongue from evil
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And their lips from deceitful words,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}they should turn from evil and do good,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
They should seek for peace and follow after it;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
And his ears are attentive to their prayers,
\par}

{\pard\fi-1720\li2800
But the face of the Lord is set against those who do wrong.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Who, indeed, is there to harm you, if you prove yourselves to be eager for what is good? {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Even if you should suffer for righteousness, count yourselves blessed! \uc1\u8220*Do not let people terrify you, or allow yourselves to be dismayed.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Revere the Christ as Lord in your hearts; always ready to give an answer to anyone who asks your reason for the hope that you cherish, but giving it with courtesy and respect, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}and keeping your consciences clear, so that, whenever you are maligned, those who vilify your good and Christian conduct may be put to shame. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}It is better that you should suffer, if that should be God\uc1\u8217*s will, for doing right, than for doing wrong. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}For Christ himself died to atone for sins once for all \uc1\u8211* the good on behalf of the bad \uc1\u8211* that he might bring you to God; his body being put to death, but his spirit entering on new life. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}And it was then that he went and preached to the imprisoned spirits, {\super\cf2\fs24 20}who once were disobedient, at the time when God patiently waited, in the days of Noah, while the ark was being prepared; in which some few lives, eight in all, were saved by means of water. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}And baptism, which this foreshadowed, now saves you \uc1\u8211* not the mere cleansing of the body, but the search of a clear conscience after God \uc1\u8211* through the resurrection of Jesus Christ, {\super\cf2\fs24 22}who has gone into heaven, and is at God\uc1\u8217*s right hand, where angels and archangels and the powers of heaven now yield submission to him. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 4}Since, then, Christ suffered in body, arm yourselves with the same resolve as he; for he who has suffered in body has ceased to sin, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}and so will live the rest of his earthly life guided, not by human passions, but by the will of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Surely in the past you have spent time enough living as the Gentiles delight to live. For your path has lain among scenes of debauchery, licentiousness, drunkenness, revelry, hard-drinking, and profane idolatry. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}And, because you do not run to the same extremes of profligacy as others, they are astonished, and malign you. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}But they will have to answer for their conduct to him who is ready to judge both the living and the dead. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}For that was why the good news was told to the dead also \uc1\u8211* that, after they have been judged in the body, as people are judged, they might live in the spirit, as God lives.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}But the end of all things is near. Therefore exercise self-restraint and be calm, so that you may be able to pray. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Above all things, let your love for one another be earnest, for \uc1\u8220*Love throws a veil over countless sins.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Never grudge hospitality to one another. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Whatever the gift that each has received, use it in the service of others, as good stewards of the varied bounty of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}When anyone speaks, they should speak as one who is delivering the oracles of God. When anyone is endeavouring to serve others, they should do so in reliance on the strength which God supplies; so that in everything God may be honoured through Jesus Christ \uc1\u8211* to whom be ascribed all honour and might for ever and ever. Amen.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Dear friends, do not be astonished at the trial of fire that you are passing through, to test you, as though something strange were happening to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}No, the more you share the sufferings of the Christ, the more may you rejoice, that, when the time comes for the manifestation of his glory, you may rejoice and exult. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}If you are insulted for bearing the name of Christ, count yourselves blessed; because the divine glory and the Spirit of God are resting on you. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}I need hardly say that no one among you must suffer as a murderer, or a thief, or a criminal, or for interfering in matters which do not concern Christians. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}But, if someone suffers as a Christian, they should not be ashamed of it; they should bring honour to God even though they bear that name. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}For the time has come for judgment to begin with the house of God; and, if it begins with us, what will be the end of those who reject God\uc1\u8217*s good news? {\super\cf2\fs24 18}If \uc1\u8220*a good person is saved only with difficulty, what will become of the godless and the sinful?\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Therefore, I say, let those who suffer, because God wills it so, commit their lives into the hands of a faithful Creator, and persevere in doing right. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 5}As for the older ones among you, who are elders in the church, I, their fellow elder, and a witness to the sufferings of the Christ, who will also share in the glory that is to be revealed \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 2}I beg you to be true shepherds of the flock of God among you, not because you are compelled, but of your own free will; not from a base love of gain, but with a ready spirit; {\super\cf2\fs24 3}not as lords of your charges, but as examples to your flock. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Then, when the chief shepherd appears, you will win the crown of glory that never fades. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Again, you younger ones should show deference to the older. And all of you should put on the badge of humility in mutual service, for \uc1\u8220*God is opposed to the proud, but gives his help to the humble.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Humble yourselves, therefore, under the mighty hand of God, so that he may exalt you in his good time, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}laying all your anxieties on him, for he makes you his care. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Exercise self-control, be watchful. Your adversary, the devil, like a roaring lion, is prowling about, eager to devour you. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Stand firm against him, strong in your faith; knowing, as you do, that the sufferings which you are undergoing are being endured to the full by the Lord\uc1\u8217*s followers throughout the world. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}God, from whom all help comes, and who called you, by your union with Christ, into his eternal glory, will, when you have suffered for a little while, himself perfect, establish, strengthen you. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}To him be ascribed dominion for ever. Amen.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}I have been writing to you briefly by the hand of Silas, our true-hearted friend (for so I regard him), to encourage you, and to bear my testimony that in what I have written is to be found the true love of God. On that take your stand. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Your sister church in \uc1\u8220*Babylon\uc1\u8221* sends you greeting, and so does Mark, who is as a son to me. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Greet one another with the kiss of love.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
May God give his peace to you all in your union with Christ.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 2 Peter (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Peter\uc1\u8217*s Second Letter
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}To those to whom, through the justice of our God and Saviour Jesus Christ, there has been granted faith equally privileged with our own, from Simon Peter, a servant and an apostle of Jesus Christ.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}May blessing and peace be yours in ever increasing measure, as you advance in the knowledge of God and of Jesus, our Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For his divine power has given us everything that is needful for a life of piety, as we advance in the knowledge of him who called us by a glorious manifestation of his goodness. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}For it was through this that he gave us what we prize as the greatest of his promises, that through them you might participate in the divine nature, now that you have fled from the corruption in the world, resulting from human passions. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Yes, and for this reason do your best to supplement your faith by goodness, goodness by knowledge, {\super\cf2\fs24 6}knowledge by self-control, self-control by endurance, endurance by piety, {\super\cf2\fs24 7}piety by mutual affection, and mutual affection by love. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}For, when these virtues are yours, in increasing measure, they prevent your being indifferent to, or destitute of, a fuller knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Surely the person who has not these virtues is shortsighted even to blindness, and has chosen to forget that they have been purified from their sins of the past! {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Therefore, friends, do your best to put God\uc1\u8217*s call and selection of you beyond all doubt; for, if you do this, you will never fall. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}For in this way you will be given a triumphant admission into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Saviour, Jesus Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Transfiguration and the \uc1\u8220*Second Coming\uc1\u8221* of the Christ

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}I will, therefore, always be ready to remind you of all this, even though you know it and are firmly established in the truth that you now hold. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}But I think it my duty, as long as I live in this \uc1\u8220*tent,\uc1\u8221* to rouse you by awakening memories of the past; {\super\cf2\fs24 14}for I know that the time for this \uc1\u8220*tent\uc1\u8221* of mine to be put away is soon coming, as our Lord Jesus Christ himself assured me. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}So I will do my best to enable you, at any time after my departure, to call these truths to mind. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}For we were not following cleverly devised stories when we told you of the coming in power of our Lord Jesus Christ, but we had been eye-witnesses of his majesty. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}For he received honour and glory from God the Father, when from the glory of the Divine Majesty there were borne to his ears words such as these \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*This is my dearly loved son, who brings me great joy.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 18}These were the words that we heard, borne to our ears from heaven, when we were with him on that sacred mountain. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}And still stronger is the assurance that we have in the teaching of the prophets; to which you will do well to pay attention (as if it were a lamp shining in a gloomy place), until the day dawns and the morning star rises in your hearts. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}But first be assured of this: There is no prophetic teaching found in scripture that can be interpreted by a person\uc1\u8217*s unaided reason; {\super\cf2\fs24 21}for no prophetic teaching ever came in the old days at the mere wish of people, but people, moved by the Holy Spirit, spoke direct from God. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Warning against separating Christianity from a Holy Life

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}But there were false prophets also in the nation, just as there will be false teachers among you, people who will secretly introduce ruinous divisions, disowning even the Lord who bought them, and bringing speedy ruin on themselves. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}There will be many, too, who will follow their licentious courses, and cause the way of the truth to be maligned. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}In their covetousness they will try to make you a source of profit by their fabrications; but for a long time past their sentence has not been standing idle, nor their ruin slumbering. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Remember, God did not spare angels when they sinned, but sent them down to Tartarus, and consigned them to caverns of darkness, to be kept under guard for judgment. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Nor did he spare the world of old; though he preserved Noah, the preacher of righteousness, and seven others, when he brought a flood on the godless world. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}He condemned the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah and reduced them to ashes, holding them up as a warning to the godless of what was in store for them; {\super\cf2\fs24 7}but he rescued righteous Lot, whose heart was vexed by the wanton licentiousness of his neighbours; {\super\cf2\fs24 8}for, seeing and hearing what he did, as he lived his righteous life among them, day after day, Lot\uc1\u8217*s righteous soul was tortured by their wicked doings. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}The Lord, therefore, knows how to deliver the pious from temptation, and to keep the wicked, who are even now suffering punishment, in readiness for \uc1\u8220*the day of judgment\uc1\u8221* \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}especially those who, following the promptings of their lower nature, indulge their polluting passions and despise all control. Audacious and self-willed, they feel no awe of the celestial beings, maligning them, {\super\cf2\fs24 11}even where angels, though excelling them in strength and power, do not bring against them a malignant charge before the Lord. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}These people, however, like animals without reason, intended by nature to be caught and killed \uc1\u8211* these people, I say, malign those of whom they know nothing, and will assuredly perish through their own corruption, {\super\cf2\fs24 13}suffering themselves, as the penalty for the suffering that they have inflicted. They think that pleasure consists in the self-indulgence of the moment. They are a stain and a disgrace, indulging, as they do, in their wanton revelry, even while joining you at your feasts. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}They have eyes only for adulteresses, eyes never tired of sin; they entice weak souls; their minds are trained to covet; they live under a curse. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Leaving the straight road, they have gone astray and followed in the steps of Balaam, the son of Beor, who set his heart on the reward for wrong-doing, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}but was rebuked for his offence. A dumb animal spoke with a human voice, and checked the prophet\uc1\u8217*s madness. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}These people are like springs without water, or mists driven before a gale; and for them the blackest darkness has been reserved. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}With boastful and foolish talk, they appeal to the passions of people\uc1\u8217*s lower nature, and, by their profligacy, entice those who are just escaping from the people who live such misguided lives. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}They promise them freedom, while they themselves are slaves to corrupt habits; for a person is the slave of anything to which they give way. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}If, after having escaped the polluting influences of the world, through knowing our Lord and Saviour, Jesus Christ, people are again entangled in them, and give way to them, their last state has become worse than their first. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}It would, indeed, have been better for them not to have known the way of righteousness, than, after knowing it, to turn away from the holy command delivered to them. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}In their case is seen the truth of the proverb \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*A dog returns to what it has vomited\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*A sow after washing to her wallowing-place in the mud.\uc1\u8221* 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 A Reassertion of the \uc1\u8220*Second Coming\uc1\u8221* of the Christ

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}This, dear friends, is my second letter to you. In both of them I have tried, by appealing to your remembrance, to arouse your better feelings. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}I want you to recall what was foretold by the holy prophets, as well as the command of our Lord and Saviour given to you through your apostles. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}First be assured of this, that, as the age draws to an end, scoffers, led by their own passions, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}will come and ask scoffingly \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Where is his promised coming? Ever since our ancestors passed to their rest, everything remains just as it was when the world was first created!\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 5}For they wilfully shut their eyes to the fact that long ago the heavens existed; and the earth, also \uc1\u8211* formed out of water and by the action of water, by the fiat of God; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}and that by the same means the world which then existed was destroyed in a deluge of water. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}But the present heavens and earth, by the same fiat, have been reserved for fire, and are being kept for the day of the judgment and destruction of the godless.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}But you, dear friends, must never shut your eyes to the fact that, to the Lord, one day is the same as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}The Lord is not slow to fulfil his promise, as some count slowness; but he is forbearing with you, as it is not his will that any of you should perish, but that all should be brought to repentance. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}The day of the Lord will come like a thief; and on that day the heavens will pass away with a crash, the elements will be burnt up and dissolved, and the earth and all that is in it will be disclosed. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Now, since all these things are in the process of dissolution, think what you yourselves ought to be \uc1\u8211* what holy and pious lives you ought to lead, {\super\cf2\fs24 12}while you wait for the coming of the day of God and strive to make it come soon{\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   Or: and desire its coming. }. At its coming the heavens will be dissolved in fire, and the elements melted by heat, {\super\cf2\fs24 13}but we look for new heavens and a new earth, where righteousness will have its home, in fulfilment of the promise of God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore, dear friends, in expectation of these things, make every effort to be found by him spotless, blameless, and at peace. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Regard our Lord\uc1\u8217*s forbearance as your one hope of salvation. This is what our dear friend Paul wrote to you, with the wisdom that God gave him. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}It is the same in all his letters, when he speaks in them about these subjects. There are some things in them difficult to understand, which untaught and weak people distort, just as they do all other writings, to their own ruin. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}You must, therefore, dear friends, now that you know this beforehand, be on your guard against being led away by the errors of reckless people, and so lapsing from your present steadfastness; {\super\cf2\fs24 18}and advance in the love and knowledge of our Lord and Saviour, Jesus Christ. All glory be to him now and for ever.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 1 John (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 John\uc1\u8217*s First Letter
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Preface

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}We write to you about the Word of life, which has been in existence from the beginning. We write of what we have heard, of what we have seen with our eyes, of what we watched reverently and touched with our hands. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}That life was made visible, and we have seen it. We bear our testimony to it, and tell you of that eternal life which was with the Father and was made visible to us. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}It is of what we have seen and heard that we now tell you, so that you may have fellowship with us. And our fellowship is with the Father and with his Son, Jesus Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}We are writing all this to you that our joy may be complete.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Fellowship with God

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}This is the message which we have heard from him and announce to you: God is light, and there is no darkness in him at all. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}If we say that we have fellowship with him and yet continue to walk in the darkness, our words and our lives are a lie. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}But if we walk in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship with one another, and the blood of Jesus, his Son, cleanses us from all sin. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}If we say, \uc1\u8216*we have no sin,\uc1\u8217* then we are deceiving ourselves, and the truth is not in us. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}If we confess our sins, he is just and may be trusted to forgive our sins and cleanse us from all wrongdoing. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}If we say that we haven\uc1\u8217*t sinned, we make God a liar, and his Word is not in us. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 2}My children, I am writing to you to keep you from sinning. But if anyone does sin, we have an advocate with the Father \uc1\u8211* Jesus Christ, the righteous. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}He is the atoning sacrifice for our sins, and not for ours only, but the sins of the whole world. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}It is by keeping God\uc1\u8217*s commands that we can be sure we know him. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Whoever says \uc1\u8216*I know him,\uc1\u8217* but does not keep his commands, is a liar. The truth has no place in them. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}But the person who keeps God\uc1\u8217*s word, in them the love of God has indeed reached its perfection. This is how we can be sure we are in him: {\super\cf2\fs24 6}whoever claims to live in him should live just as Jesus did.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 A new commandment

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Dear friends, it is no new command that I am writing to you, but an old command, which you have had from the beginning. That old command is the message you have already heard. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Yet, in a way, it is a new command that I am writing to you \uc1\u8211* which is shown true in Christ\uc1\u8217*s life and in yours \uc1\u8211* for the darkness is passing away and the true light is already shining. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}The person who says that they are in the light, and yet hates others, is still in the darkness. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}The person who loves others is always in the light, and there is nothing within them to cause them to stumble. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}The person who hates is in the dark. They stumble along in the darkness; they do not know where they are going because the darkness blinds them.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Those who know God should not love the world

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 

\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Little children, I am writing to you
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
because your sins have been forgiven for Christ\uc1\u8217*s sake.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Parents, I am writing to you
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
because you have come to know him who has been from the beginning.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Young people, I am writing to you
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
because you have conquered the evil one.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Children, I write to you
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
because you have come to know the Father.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Parents, I write to you
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
because you have learned to know him who has been from the beginning.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Young people, I write to you
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
because you are strong,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
and God\uc1\u8217*s message is always in your hearts,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
and you have conquered the evil one.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Do not love the world or what the world can offer. When anyone loves the world, there is no love for the Father in them. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}For all that the world can offer \uc1\u8211* the desires for physical pleasure, the enticements to the eye, the arrogance of wealth \uc1\u8211* belongs, not to the Father, but to the world. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And the world, and all that it gratifies, is passing away, but they who do God\uc1\u8217*s will remain for ever.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Warnings against an antichrist

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}My children, it is the last hour. You were told that an antichrist was coming; and many antichrists have already arisen. This is why we know that this is the last hour. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}These people come from our ranks, but they were never truly part of us \uc1\u8211* if they had been then they would have stayed with us. They left so it would be clear that none of them really belonged to us. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}You, however, have been annointed by the Holy One. You all know the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}I am not writing to you because you do not know the truth, but because you do know it, and because no lie can come from the truth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Who is a liar, if not the one who denies that Jesus is the Christ? That person is the antichrist \uc1\u8211* one who rejects the Father and the Son. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}No one who rejects the Son has the Father; to acknowledge the Son is to have the Father also. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}As for you, you must let what you have heard from the beginning continue to live in you. If what you heard from the beginning dwells in you, you will remain both in the Son and the Father. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}And this is what he himself promised us \uc1\u8211* eternal life!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 26}In writing this to you, I have in mind those who are trying to mislead you. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}As for you, the anointing which you received from him remains with you. You do not need anyone to teach you. His anointing teaches you about everything. What it teaches you is true, it is not a lie. Do what it has taught you: abide in him. {\super\cf2\fs24 28}Yes, my children, remain in him, so that when he appears our confidence doesn\uc1\u8217*t fail us, and we are not ashamed to meet him at his coming. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}Since you know he is righteous, you realise that everyone who does what is right is his child. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 God\uc1\u8217*s Children

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}See what great love the Father has lavished on us: he lets us be called God\uc1\u8217*s children! For that is what we are. The reason why the world does not know us is that it has not learned to know him. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Dear friends, we are God\uc1\u8217*s children now, and what we will be has not yet been revealed. What we do know is that, when it is revealed, we will be like him, because we will see him as he is. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}And just as he is pure, everyone who has this hope, makes and keeps themselves pure.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Everyone who lives sinfully is living in violation of God\uc1\u8217*s law. Sin is lawlessness. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}You know that Christ appeared to take away our sins and that there is no sin in him. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}No one who lives in him continues to sin; the sinner has not seen or known him. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}My children, don\uc1\u8217*t let anyone mislead you. The person who does what is right is righteous, just as Christ is righteous. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}The person who lives in sin is a child of the devil, for the devil has been sinning from the beginning. To undo the devil\uc1\u8217*s work is the reason the Son of God appeared.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}No child of God sins, because God\uc1\u8217*s nature dwells in them. They can\uc1\u8217*t live in sin, because they are God\uc1\u8217*s children. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}By this it is made clear who are the children of God and who are the devil\uc1\u8217*s: anyone who doesn\uc1\u8217*t do what is right or doesn\uc1\u8217*t love others is not a child of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}For this is the message we heard from the beginning: we are to love one another. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}We must not be like Cain, who belonged to the evil one and murdered his brother. Why did he kill him? Because his actions were evil, and his brother\uc1\u8217*s were righteous.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Love each other

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Do not be suprised, friends, if the world hates you. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}We know that we have passed out of death into life, because we love each other. The person who does not love remains in a state of death. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}The person who hates another is a murderer, and you know that no murderer has eternal life dwelling within them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}This is how we know that love is: Christ gave his life for us. So we should lay down our own lives for each other. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}If anyone has material possessions, and sees one of our own in need, but closes their heart against that person, how can it be said that the love of God is within them? {\super\cf2\fs24 18}My children, our love must not be mere words or talk. It must be true and show itself in actions.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 19}This is how we will know we belong to the truth and reassure ourselves in God\uc1\u8217*s presence: {\super\cf2\fs24 20}though our conscience condemns us, God is greater than our conscience and knows everything. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Dear friends, if our conscience does not condemn us, then we approach God with confidence, {\super\cf2\fs24 22}and we receive from him whatever we ask, because we are keeping his commands, and are doing what pleases him. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}His command is that we should believe in his Son, Jesus Christ, and love one another, as Christ commanded us. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}The person who keeps his commands dwells in God and God dwells in them. And we are sure he lives in us because of the Spirit he has given us. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 True and False Inspiration

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 4}Dear friends, do not trust every spirit, but test the spirits to see whether they are from God, because many false prophets have gone out into the world.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}This is the way to recognise the Spirit of God: those who acknowledge Jesus Christ as come in the flesh have God\uc1\u8217*s Spirit, {\super\cf2\fs24 3}while a spirit that doesn\uc1\u8217*t acknowledge Jesus isn\uc1\u8217*t from God. Instead it is the spirit of the antichrist; you have heard that it was coming, and it is now already in the world!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}You, my children, come from God, and you have successfully resisted such people as these, because he who is in you is greater than the one who is in the world. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Those people belong to the world and therefore they speak as the world speaks, and the world listens to them. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}We come from God. Whoever knows God listens to us; the person who does not come from God does not listen to us. This is how we distinguish the spirit of truth and the spirit of deception.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 God is love

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Dear friends, let us love one another, because love comes from God and everyone who loves is a child of God and knows God. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Those who do not love know nothing of God, for God is love. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}This is how God showed his love among us: he sent his one and only Son into the world that we might live through him. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}This is what love is: it is not that we have loved God, but that he loved us and sent his Son to be an atoning sacrifice for our sins.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Dear friends, since God loved us in this way, we should love one another. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}No one has ever seen God, but if we love one another, God lives in us and his love reaches perfection within us. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}We know that we live in him, and he lives in us, because he has given us a measure of his Spirit. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Moreover, we have seen for ourselves and testify that the Father has sent the Son to be the Saviour of the world. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Whoever acknowledges that Jesus Christ is the Son of God, God lives in them, and they live in God. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}And so we have come to know and believe the love which God has for us.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
God is love; and whoever lives in love lives in God, and God lives in them. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}This is the way love has reached its perfection among us, so that we may have confidence on the day of judgment, because in this world we are like Christ. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}There is no fear in love; perfect love drives out fear because fear has to do with punishment. So anyone who is afraid has not reached perfection in love. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}We love, because God first loved us. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}If someone says \uc1\u8220*I love God,\uc1\u8221* and yet hates others, they are a liar. For the person who does not love their brother or sister, whom they have seen, cannot love God, whom they have not seen. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Indeed, we have this command from Christ: Those who love God must also love each other. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Faith and Confidence

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 5}Everyone who believes that Jesus is the Christ is a child of God, and everyone who loves a parent loves his child. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}By this we know that we love God\uc1\u8217*s children \uc1\u8211* when we love God and carry out his commands. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For to love God is to do what he commands and his commands are not a burden, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}for whatever is born of God overcomes the world. What is the victory by which the world is overcome? Our faith! {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Who can overcome the world but the person who believes that Jesus is the Son of God? {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Jesus Christ, the one who came by water and blood \uc1\u8211* not by water only but by water and blood \uc1\u8211* and the Spirit testifies to this because the Spirit is truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Indeed three testify: {\super\cf2\fs24 8}the Spirit, the water, and the blood, and these three agree. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}We accept human testimony, surely God\uc1\u8217*s testimony is even stronger! And God\uc1\u8217*s testimony is the testimony he has given about his Son. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}The person who believes in the Son of God has that testimony within them. The person who does not believe God has made God a liar, by not believing the testimony God has given about his Son. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}And this is that testimony: God gave us eternal life, and this life is in his Son. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Whoever has the Son has life; whoever who doesn\uc1\u8217*t have God\uc1\u8217*s Son does not have life.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Final words

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}I have written these things to you who believe in the name of God\uc1\u8217*s Son, so that you may know that you have eternal life. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}We can approach him with this confidence, that whenever we ask anything that is in accordance with his will, he listens to us. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}And if we know he hears us \uc1\u8211* whatever we ask \uc1\u8211* we know also that what we ask for is ours. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}If anyone sees one of our people committing some sin that is not a sin leading to death, they should ask, and God will give them life. I refer to those whose sin does not lead to death. There is a sin that leads to death. I am not saying that you should pray about that. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}All wrongdoing is sin, but there is sin that does not lead to death.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}We know that those who have been born of God do not keep sinning. God protects his children and the evil one cannot get hold of them. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}We know that we are God\uc1\u8217*s children, though the whole world lies in the power of the evil one. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}We also know that the Son of God has come and has given us understanding, so that we may know the true God \uc1\u8211* and we are in him who is true, by being in his Son Jesus Christ. He is the true God and eternal life. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}My children, guard yourselves against false ideas of God.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 2 John (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 John\uc1\u8217*s Second Letter
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Greetings

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}From the elder, to the lady chosen by God and her children. I truly love you all, and I am not the only one but all who know the truth love you as well. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}We love you for the sake of the truth, which lives in us and will be with us forever.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Grace, mercy, and peace will be ours \uc1\u8211* the gift of God, the Father, and of Jesus Christ, the Father\uc1\u8217*s Son \uc1\u8211* in truth and love.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Live in truth and love

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}It was a great joy to me to find the lives of some of your children guided by the truth, in obedience to the command that we received from the Father. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}And now I implore you, dear lady, let us love one another This is not a new command I am writing to you. It is the command we have had from the beginning. \uc1\u8211* Let us love one another. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And this is love \uc1\u8211* to live in obedience to the Father\uc1\u8217*s commands. This is the command as you learned from the beginning, to live a life of love. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}I say this because many deceivers have gone out into the world \uc1\u8211* men who do not acknowledge that Jesus Christ came in flesh and blood. Any such person is a deceiver and antichrist. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Take care so that you do not what we have worked for but instead receive your full reward. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Anyone who goes beyond and fails to live inside of the teaching of Christ does not have God. The person who lives inside that teaching \uc1\u8211* they have both the Father and the Son. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}If anyone comes to you and does not bring this teaching, do not receive them into your house or even welcome them; {\super\cf2\fs24 11}because the person who welcomes them is sharing with them in his evil work.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Final words

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Though I have many other things to tell you, I would rather not use paper and ink. Instead I hope to come and see you, and to speak with you face to face, so that our joy may be complete. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}The children of your sister, who is chosen by God, send you their greetings.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 3 John (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 John\uc1\u8217*s Third Letter
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Greetings

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}From the elder to his dear friend Gaius, whom he sincerely loves.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Dear friend, I pray that all may be well with you and that you may have good health \uc1\u8211* I know that all is well with your soul. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For it was a great joy to me, when some followers of the Lord came and testified to your fidelity to the truth. I know that your own life is guided by the truth. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Nothing gives me greater pleasure than to hear from time to time that the lives of my children are guided by the truth.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Gaius

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Dear friend, you are faithful in all the things you do for other followers \uc1\u8211* even when they are strangers to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}They themselves have testified before the church to your love. You will do well to help them on their way in a manner worthy of the service of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}For it was on behalf of Christ\uc1\u8217*s name that they set out, not accepting even one thing from the Gentiles. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Therefore, we should support people like them, and so take our share in their work for the truth.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Diotrephes and Demetrius

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}I wrote something to the church, but Diotrephes (who loves to be the leader among them) doesn\uc1\u8217*t welcome us. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}So if I come, I will bring up his actions in telling wicked nonsense about us. Not content with that, he not only refuses to personally welcome our friends who are followers, but actually stops those who would, and expels them from the church.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Dear friend, do not follow a bad example, but a good one. The person who does what is good is from God; the person who does what is bad has never seen God. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Everyone has always had a good word for Demetrius, and the truth itself speaks for him. Yes, and we also add our good word, and you know that what we say is true.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Final words

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 13}I have many things to tell you, but I would rather not use pen and ink. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}I hope to see you soon, and then we will speak face to face. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Peace be with you. The friends here send you their greetings. Greet each one of our friends.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Jude (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs60 The Letter from

\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 Jude
 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Introduction

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}To those who, having received the call, have been loved by God the Father and protected by Jesus Christ, From Jude, a servant of Jesus Christ, and the brother of James. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}May mercy, peace, and love be yours in ever increasing measure.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Warnings against moral corruption

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Dear friends, while I was making every effort to write to you about our common salvation, I felt that I must write to you at once to encourage you to fight in defence of the faith that has once for all been entrusted to the keeping of Christ\uc1\u8217*s people. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}For there have crept in among you certain godless people, whose sentence has long since been pronounced, and who make the mercy of God an excuse for profligacy, and disown our only lord and master, Jesus Christ.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Now I want to remind you \uc1\u8211* but you already know it all \uc1\u8211* that, though the Lord delivered the people from Egypt, yet he afterwards destroyed those who refused to believe in him; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}and that even those angels, who did not keep to their appointed spheres, but left their proper homes, have been kept by him for the judgment of the great day in everlasting chains and black darkness. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Like Sodom and Gomorrah and the towns near them, which gave themselves up to fornication, and fell into unnatural vice, these angels now stand out as a warning, undergoing, as they are, punishment in eternal fire.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Yet in the same way these people, too, cherishing vain dreams, pollute our human nature, reject control, and malign the celestial beings. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Yet even Michael, the archangel, when, in his dispute with the devil, he was arguing about the body of Moses, did not venture to charge him with maligning, but said merely \uc1\u8220*The Lord rebuke you!\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}But these people malign whatever they do not understand; while they use such things as they know by instinct (like the animals that have no reason) for their own corruption. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Alas for them! They walk in the steps of Cain; led astray by Balaam\uc1\u8217*s love of gain, they plunge into sin, and meet their ruin through rebellion like Korah. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}These are the people who are blots on your \uc1\u8220*love-feasts,\uc1\u8221* when they feast together and provide without scruple for themselves alone. They are clouds without rain, driven before the winds; they are leafless trees without a vestige of fruit, dead through and through, torn up by the roots; {\super\cf2\fs24 13}they are wild sea waves, foaming with their own shame; they are \uc1\u8220*wandering stars,\uc1\u8221* for which the blackest darkness has been reserved for ever.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}To these people, as to others, Enoch, the seventh in descent from Adam, declared \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*See! The Lord has come with his hosts of holy ones around him, {\super\cf2\fs24 15}to execute judgment on all people, and to convict all godless people of all their godless acts, which in their ungodliness they have committed, and of all the harsh words which they have spoken against him, godless sinners that they are!\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}These people are always murmuring, and complaining of their lot; they follow where their passions lead them; they have arrogant words on their lips; and they flatter others for the sake of what they can get from them.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}But you should, dear friends, recall what was foretold by the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ; {\super\cf2\fs24 18}how they used to say to you \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*As time draws to an end, there will be scoffers, who will be led by their godless passions.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 19}These are the people \uc1\u8211* animal and unspiritual \uc1\u8211* who cause divisions. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}But you must, dear friends, build up your characters on the foundation of your most holy faith, pray under the guidance of the Holy Spirit, {\super\cf2\fs24 21}and keep within the love of God, while waiting for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ, to bring you to eternal life. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}To some show pity, because they are in doubt. \uc1\u8220*Drag them out of the fire,\uc1\u8221* and save them. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}To others show pity, but with caution, hating the clothing polluted by their touch.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Ascription

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 24}To him who is able to guard you from falling, and to bring you into his glorious presence, blameless and rejoicing \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 25}to the one God, our Saviour, be ascribed, through Jesus Christ, our Lord, glory, majesty, power, and dominion, as it was before time began, is now, and will be for all time to come. Amen.
\par}
\sectd\sect{\header \pard\qr\plain\f0\fs16 Revelation (Page \chpgn) \par}{\pard \pagebb
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 The Revelation to John
  {\cf1 1}The Revelation of Jesus Christ, which God gave to him to make known to his servants, concerning what must shortly take place, and which he sent and revealed by his angel to his servant John, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}who testified to the message of God and to the testimony to Jesus Christ, omitting nothing of what he had seen. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Blessed is the one who reads, and blessed are they who listen to, the words of this prophecy, and lay to heart what is here written; for the time is near.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Messages to the Seven Churches

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}From John, to the seven churches which are in Roman Asia. Blessing and peace be yours from him who is, and who was, and who will be, and from the seven spirits that are before his throne, {\super\cf2\fs24 5}and from Jesus Christ, the faithful witness, the first-born from the dead, and the Ruler of all the kings of the earth. To him who loves us and freed us from our sins by his own blood \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 6}and he made us a kingdom of priests in the service of God, his Father! \uc1\u8211* to Him be ascribed glory and dominion for ever. Amen. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}He is coming among the clouds! Every eye will see him, even those who pierced him and all the nations of the earth will mourn over him. So will it be. Amen.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8220*I am the Alpha and the Omega,\uc1\u8221* says the Lord, the God who is, and who was, and who will be, the Almighty.
\par}

{\pard 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}I, John, who am your brother, and who share with you in the suffering and kingship and endurance of Jesus, found myself on the island called Patmos, for the sake of the message of God and the testimony to Jesus. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}I fell into a trance on the Lord\uc1\u8217*s day, and I heard behind me a loud voice, like the blast of a trumpet. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}It said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Write what you see in a book and send it to the seven churches, to Ephesus, Smyrna, Pergamus, Thyatira, Sardis, Philadelphia, and Laodicaea.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}I turned to see what voice it was that spoke to me; and when I turned, I saw seven golden lamps, {\super\cf2\fs24 13}and in the midst of the lamps one like a man, in a robe reaching to his feet, and with a golden sash across his breast. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}The hair of his head was as white as wool, as white as snow; his eyes were like flaming fire; {\super\cf2\fs24 15}and his feet were like brass as when molten in a furnace; his voice was like the sound of many streams, {\super\cf2\fs24 16}in his right hand he held seven stars, from his mouth came a sharp two-edged sword, and his face was like the sun in the fulness of its power. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}And, when I saw him, I fell at his feet like one dead. He laid his hand on me and said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Do not be afraid. I am the First and the Last, {\super\cf2\fs24 18}the Everliving. I died, and I am alive for ever and ever. And I hold the keys of death and of Hades. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Therefore write of what you have seen and of what is happening now and of what is about to take place \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 20}the mystic meaning of the seven stars which you saw in my right hand, and the seven golden lamps. The seven stars are the angels of the seven churches, and the seven lamps are the seven churches. 
\par}

{\pard 
 {\cf1 2}\uc1\u8216*To the angel of the church in Ephesus write
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0\li720 
{\super\cf2\fs24 1}These are the words of him who holds the seven stars in his right hand, and walks among the seven golden lamps: {\super\cf2\fs24 2}I know your life, your toil and endurance, and I know that you cannot tolerate evil-doers. I know, too, how you tested those who declare that they are apostles, though they are not, and how you proved them false. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}You possess endurance, and have borne much for my name, and have never grown weary. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}But this I have against you \uc1\u8211* You have abandoned your first love. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Therefore remember from what you have fallen, and repent, and live the life that you lived before; or else, I will come and remove your Lamp from its place, unless you repent. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}But this is in your favour \uc1\u8211* You hate the life lived by the Nikolaitans, and I also hate it. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Anyone with ears should hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches. To him who conquers \uc1\u8211* to him I will give the right to eat the fruit of the Tree of life, which stands in the Paradise of God.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}\uc1\u8216*To the angel of the church in Smyrna write:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0\li720 
These are the words of him who is the First and the Last, who died, but is restored to life: {\super\cf2\fs24 9}I know your persecution and your poverty \uc1\u8211* yet you are rich! I know, too, the slander that comes from those who declare that they are God\uc1\u8217*s people, {\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   God\uc1\u8217*s people: Literally \uc1\u8220*Jews.\uc1\u8221* These people claimed to be God\uc1\u8217*s people because they were Jews. }though they are not, but are a congregation of Satan. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Do not be afraid of what you are about to suffer. The devil is about to throw some of you into prison so that you may be tempted, and may undergo persecution for ten days. Be faithful even to death, and I will give you the Crown of life. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Let those who have ears hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches. Those who conquer will suffer no hurt from the Second Death.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}\uc1\u8216*To the angel of the church in Pergamus write:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0\li720 
These are the words of him who holds the sharp two-edged sword: {\super\cf2\fs24 13}I know where you live, where the throne of Satan stands. And yet you hold to my name, and you did not disown my faith even in the days of Antipas, my faithful witness, who was put to death among you where Satan dwells. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Yet I have a few things against you \uc1\u8211* You have among you those who hold to the teaching of Balaam, who taught Balak to put temptations in the way of the Israelites, so that they should eat idol-offerings and commit licentious acts. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Again you have among you those who hold in the same way to the teaching of the Nikolaitans. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}Therefore repent, or else, I will come quickly and contend with such people with words that will cut like a sword. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Let those who have ears hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches. To those who conquer \uc1\u8211* to them I will give a share of the mystic manna, and I will give them a white stone; and on the stone will be inscribed a new name, which no one knows except the person who receives it.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 18}\uc1\u8216*To the angel of the church in Thyatira write:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0\li720 
These are the words of the Son of God, whose eyes are like flaming fire, and whose feet are like brass: {\super\cf2\fs24 19}I know your life, your love, faith, service, and endurance; and I know that your life of late has been better than it was at first. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Yet I have this against you \uc1\u8211* You tolerate the woman Jezebel, who declares that she is a prophet, and misleads my servants by her teaching, until they commit licentious acts and eat idol-offerings. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}I gave her time to repent, but she is determined not to turn from her licentiousness. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Therefore I am laying her on a bed of sickness, and bringing great suffering on those who are unfaithful with her, unless they repent and turn from a life like hers. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}I will also put her children to death; and all the churches will learn that I am he who looks into people\uc1\u8217*s hearts and souls; and I will give to each one of you what their life deserves. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}But I say to the rest of you at Thyatira \uc1\u8211* all who do not accept such teaching, whose who did not learn the secrets of Satan, as people call them \uc1\u8211* I am not laying on you any further burden; {\super\cf2\fs24 25}only hold fast to what you have received, until I come. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}To those who conquer and are careful to live my life to the end \uc1\u8211* to them I will give authority over the nations, {\super\cf2\fs24 27}and they will rule them with an iron rod, as when earthen vessels are broken in pieces (as I myself have received from my Father) {\super\cf2\fs24 28}and I will give them the morning star. {\super\cf2\fs24 29}Let those who have ears hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}\uc1\u8216*To the angel of the church in Sardis write:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0\li720 
{\super\cf2\fs24 1}These are the words of him who has the seven spirits of God and the seven stars; \uc1\u8211* I know your life, and that people say of you that you are living, though you are dead. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Be on the watch, and strengthen what still survives, though once it was all but dead; for I have not found your life perfect in the eyes of my God. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Therefore remember what you have received and heard, and lay it to heart and repent. Unless you are on the watch, I will come like a thief, and you will not know at what hour I am coming to you. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Yet there are some few among you at Sardis who did not soil their robes; they will walk with me, robed in white, for they are worthy. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Those who conquer will be clothed in these white robes, and I will not strike their name out of the book of life; but I will own them before my Father, and before his angels. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Let those who have ears hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}\uc1\u8216*To the angel of the church in Philadelphia write:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0\li720 
These are the words of him who is holy and true, who holds the Key of David, who opens and no one will shut, and shuts and no one opens: {\super\cf2\fs24 8}I know your life (see, I have set a door open before you which no one is able to shut), I know that, though you have but little strength, you kept my teaching in mind, and did not disown my name. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Listen, I give some of the congregation of Satan, the people who declare that they are God\uc1\u8217*s people, {\super\chftn}{\footnote\pard\plain\chftn   God\uc1\u8217*s people: Literally \uc1\u8220*Jews.\uc1\u8221* These people claimed to be God\uc1\u8217*s people because they were Jews. }though they are not, but are lying \uc1\u8211* I will make them come and bow down at your feet, and they will learn that I loved you. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Because you kept in mind the story of my endurance, I will keep you in the hour of trial that is about to come on the whole world, the hour that will test all who are living on earth. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}I will come quickly. Hold to what you have received so that no one may take your crown. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Those who conquer \uc1\u8211* I will make them a pillar in the Temple of my God; and never more will they leave it; and I will write on them the name of my God and the name of the city of my God, the New Jerusalem, which is coming down out of heaven from my God, and I will write on them my new name. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}Let those who have ears hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 14}\uc1\u8216*To the angel of the church in Laodicaea write:
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0\li720 
These are the words of the Unchanging One, the witness faithful and true, the beginning of the Creation of God: {\super\cf2\fs24 15}I know your life; I know that you are neither cold nor hot. If only you were either cold or hot! {\super\cf2\fs24 16}But now, because you are lukewarm, neither hot nor cold, I am about to spit you out of my mouth. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}You say \uc1\u8220*I am rich and have grown rich, and I want for nothing,\uc1\u8221* and you do not know that you are wretched, miserable, poor, blind, naked! {\super\cf2\fs24 18}Therefore I counsel you to buy from me gold which has been refined by fire so that you may grow rich; and white robes, so that you may be clothed and your shameful nakedness be hidden; and ointment to anoint your eyes, so that you may see. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}All whom I love I rebuke and discipline. Therefore be in earnest and repent. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}I am standing at the door and knocking! If anyone hears my voice and opens the door, I will go in, and will feast with them, and they will feast with me. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}To those who conquer \uc1\u8211* to them I will give the right to sit beside me on my throne, as I, when I conquered, took my seat beside my Father on his throne. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}Let those who have ears hear what the Spirit is saying to the churches.\uc1\u8217* 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The Vision of the Seven Seals

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 4}After this, in my vision, I saw an open door in the heavens, and the first voice that I heard was like the blast of a trumpet speaking to me. It said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Come up here and I will show you what must take place.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Immediately after this I fell into a trance. There stood a throne in heaven, and on the throne was One seated. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}He who was seated on it was in appearance like a jasper and a sardius; and round the throne there was a rainbow of the colour of an emerald. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}And round the throne were twenty-four other thrones, and on these I saw twenty-four elders sitting clothed in white robes; and on their heads they had crowns of gold. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Out from the throne come flashes of lightning, cries, and peals of thunder! There are seven torches burning in front of the throne, which are the seven spirits of God; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}and in front of the throne is what seemed to be a sea of glass, resembling crystal, while within the space before the throne and round the throne are four creatures full of eyes in front and behind. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}The first creature is like a lion, the second creature like a calf, the third creature has a face like a man\uc1\u8217*s, and the fourth creature is like an eagle on the wing. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}These four creatures have each of them six wings, and all round, and within, they are full of eyes; and day and night they never cease to say \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Holy, holy, holy is the Lord, our God, the Almighty, who was, and who is, and who will be.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}And, whenever these creatures give praise and honour and thanks to him who is seated on the throne, to him who lives for ever and ever, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}the twenty-four elders prostrate themselves before him who is seated on the throne, and worship him who lives for ever and ever, and throw down their crowns before the throne, saying \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}\uc1\u8220*Worthy are you, our Lord and God, to receive all praise, and honour, and power, for you did create all things, and at your bidding they came into being and were created.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
