{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Then I saw what appeared to be a sea of glass mixed with fire; and, standing by this sea of glass, holding the harps of God, I saw those who had come victorious out of the conflict with the Beast and its image and the number that formed its name. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}They are singing the song of Moses, the servant of God, and the song of the Lamb \uc1\u8211*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
\uc1\u8220*Great and marvellous are your deeds, Lord, our God, the Almighty. Righteous and true are your ways, eternal King. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Who will not honour and praise your name, Lord? You alone are holy! All nations will come and worship before you, for your judgments have become manifest.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}After this I saw that the inmost shrine of the tent of testimony in heaven was opened, {\super\cf2\fs24 6}and out of it came the seven angels with the seven curses. They were adorned with precious stones, pure and bright, and had golden girdles round their breasts. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}One of the four creatures gave the seven angels seven golden bowls, filled with the wrath of God who lives for ever and ever. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}The Temple was filled with smoke from the glory and majesty of God; and no one could enter the Temple, until the seven curses inflicted by the seven angels were at an end.  {\cf1 16}Then I heard a loud voice, which came from the Temple, saying to the seven angels \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Go and empty the seven bowls of the wrath of God on the earth.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}The first angel went and emptied his bowl on the earth; and it turned to loathsome and painful sores on all who bore the brand of the Beast and who worshiped its image.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Then the second angel emptied his bowl on the sea; and it turned to blood like the blood of a corpse, and every living thing died \uc1\u8211* everything in the sea.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Then the third angel emptied his bowl on the rivers and springs of water; and it turned to blood. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}And I heard the angel of the Waters saying \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Righteous are you, you who is and who is, the Holy One, in inflicting this judgment; {\super\cf2\fs24 6}for men shed the blood of Christ\uc1\u8217*s people and of the prophets, and you have given them blood to drink. It is what they deserve.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 7}And I heard the response from the altar \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Yes, Lord, our God, the Almighty, true and righteous are they judgments.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Then the fourth angel emptied his bowl on the sun; and he was permitted to scorch men with fire; {\super\cf2\fs24 9}and men were scorched by the intense heat. They blasphemed the name of God who controlled these curses, yet they did not repent and give him praise.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Then the fifth angel emptied his bowl on the throne of the Beast; and darkness fell on its kingdom. Men gnawed their tongues for pain, {\super\cf2\fs24 11}and blasphemed the God of heaven, because of their pains and because of their sores; yet they did not repent of what they had done.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 12}Then the sixth angel emptied his bowl on the great river Euphrates; and the water in the river was dried up, so that the road for the kings of the East might be made ready. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}And I saw three foul spirits, like frogs, come from the mouth of the Dragon and from the mouth of the Beast and from the mouth of the false prophet. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}They are the spirits of demons, and perform marvels; they go to kings all over the world, to collect them for the battle on the great day of Almighty God. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}(\uc1\u8220*I am coming like a thief! Happy will he be who is on the watch, and keeps his clothing at hand, so that he will not have to walk about unclothed and let men see his nakedness.\uc1\u8221*) {\super\cf2\fs24 16}And the spirits collected the kings at the place called in Hebrew \uc1\u8220*Har-Magedon.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Then the seventh angel emptied his bowl on the air. (A loud voice came from the throne in the Temple; it said \uc1\u8220*All is over.\uc1\u8221*) {\super\cf2\fs24 18}There followed flashes of lightning, cries, and peals of thunder; and there was a great earthquake, such as had not occurred since man began to be on the earth \uc1\u8211* none so great; {\super\cf2\fs24 19}and the great city was torn in three, and the cities of the nation fell, and God remembered Babylon the Great, and gave her the maddening wine-cup of his wrath; {\super\cf2\fs24 20}and every island vanished, and the mountains disappeared. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Great hailstones, a pound in weight, are falling on men from the heavens. And men blasphemed God because of the curse of the hail, for it was a very terrible curse. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Doom of the Enemies of Christ

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 17}Then one of the seven angels who held the seven bowls came and spoke to me. \uc1\u8220*Come here,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*and I will show you the sentence passed on that Great Harlot who is seated at the meeting of many waters, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}and with whom all the kings of the earth have had licentious intercourse; while all who live on the earth have been make drunk by the wine of her licentiousness.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 3}And he bore me away in a trance to a lonely place, and I saw a woman seated on a scarlet Beast, which was covered with blasphemous names; it had seven heads and ten horns. {\super\cf2\fs24 4}The woman was clothed in purple and scarlet, and glittering with gold ornaments, precious stones, and pearls. In her hand she held a gold cup, full of idolatrous abominations, and the unclean fruits of her licentiousness; {\super\cf2\fs24 5}while on her forehead there was written this mystic name \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*BABYLON THE GREAT, THE MOTHER OF HARLOTS AND OF ALL IDOLATROUS ABOMINATIONS ON EARTH.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And I saw the woman drunk with the blood of Christ\uc1\u8217*s people and with the blood of the martyrs for Jesus. When I saw her, I was amazed beyond measure; {\super\cf2\fs24 7}but the angel said to me \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Why were you amazed? I will tell you the mystic meaning of the vision of this woman, and of the Beast, with the seven heads and ten horns, that carries her. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}The Beast that you saw was, but is not, and is about to rise out of the bottomless pit, and is on its way to destruction. Those who are living on earth will be amazed \uc1\u8211* those whose names have not been written in the book of life from the foundation of the world \uc1\u8211* when they see that the Beast was, but is not, and yet will come.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 9}(Here there is need for the discerning mind.) The seven heads are seven mountains on which the woman is seated. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}They are also seven kings; of whom five have fallen and one remains, while one is not yet come. When he comes, he must stay for a little while. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}So must the Beast that was, but is not. He counts as an eighth king, although he is one of the seven, and is on his way to destruction. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}The ten horns that you saw are ten kings, who have not yet received their kingdoms, but for an hour they receive the authority of kings, together with the Beast. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}These kings are of one mind in surrendering their power and authority to the Beast. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}They will fight with the Lamb, but the Lamb will conquer them, for he is Lord of lords and King of kings; so, too, will those with him who have received the call and are chosen and faithful. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}And the angel said to me \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*The waters that you saw, where the Harlot is seated, are throngs of people and men of all nations and languages. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}The ten horns that you saw, and the Beast \uc1\u8211* they will hate the Harlot, and cause her to become deserted and strip her bare; they will eat her flesh and utterly consume her with fire. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}For God has put it into their minds to carry out his purpose, in carrying out their common purpose and surrendering their kingdoms to the Beast, until God\uc1\u8217*s decrees will be executed. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}As for the woman whom you saw, she is the great city that holds sway over all the kings of the earth.\uc1\u8221* 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 18}After this I saw another angel, descending from heaven, invested with great authority; and the earth was illuminated by his splendour. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}With a mighty voice he cried \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*She has fallen! She has fallen \uc1\u8211* Babylon the Great! She has become an abode of demons, a stronghold of every wicked spirit, a stronghold of every foul and hateful bird. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}For, after drinking the maddening wine of her licentiousness, all the nations have fallen; while all the kings of the earth have had licentious intercourse with her, and the merchants of the earth have grown rich through the excess of her luxury.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Then I heard another voice from heaven saying \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Come out of her, my people, so that you may not participate in her sins, and that you may not suffer from the curses inflicted on her. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}For her sins are heaped up to the heavens, and God has not forgotten her misdeeds. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Pay her back the treatment with which she has treated you; yes, repay twice over what her actions deserve; in the cup which she mixed for you, mix for her as much again; {\super\cf2\fs24 7}for her self-glorification and her luxury, give her now an equal measure of torture and misery. In her heart she says \uc1\u8220*I sit here a queen; no widow am I; I will never know misery.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 8}Therefore in one day will these curses strike her \uc1\u8211* death, misery, and famine, and she will be utterly consumed by fire; for mighty is the Lord God who condemned her.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 9}All the kings of the earth who had licentious intercourse with her and shared her luxury will weep and lament over her, when they see the smoke from the burning city, {\super\cf2\fs24 10}while they stand at a distance, horrified at her torture, and cry \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Alas! Alas! Great city! Mighty city of Babylon! In a single hour your judgment fell.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 11}And the merchants of the earth weep and wail over her, because no longer does anyone buy their cargoes \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}their cargoes of gold, or silver, or precious stones, or pearls, or fine linen, or purple robes, or silk, or scarlet cloth; nor their many scented woods; nor their many articles of ivory; nor their many articles of choicest wood, or brass, or iron, or marble; {\super\cf2\fs24 13}nor their cinnamon, or spice, or incense, or perfumes, or frankincense, or wine, or oil, or fine flour, or wheat, or cattle, or sheep; nor their horses, or chariots, or slaves; nor the bodies and souls of people. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}The fruit that your soul craved is no longer within your reach, and all dainties and luxuries are lost to you, never to be found again. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}The merchants who sold these things, and grew rich by her, will stand at a distance weeping and wailing, horrified at her torture, and crying \uc1\u8211* {\super\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8216*Alas! Alas! Great city! City clothed in fine linen, and purple, and scarlet cloth! City adorned with gold ornaments, and precious stones, and pearls! {\super\cf2\fs24 17}In a single hour your vast wealth vanished.\uc1\u8217* Every ship\uc1\u8217*s captain and all who sail to any port, and sailors, and all who get their living from the sea, stood at a distance, {\super\cf2\fs24 18}and seeing the smoke from the burning city, cried \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*What city can compare with the Great city?\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 19}They threw dust on their heads, and, as they wept and wailed, they cried \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Alas! Alas! Great city! All who have ships on the sea grew rich through her magnificence. In a single hour it has vanished.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 20}Rejoice over her, heaven, and people of Christ, and apostles, and prophets, for God has avenged you on her! {\super\cf2\fs24 21}Then a mighty angel took up a stone like a great millstone, and threw it into the sea, crying \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*So will Babylon, the great city, be violently overthrown, never more to be seen. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}No more will the music of harpers, or minstrels, or flute players, or trumpeters be heard in you, no more will any worker, skilled in any art, be found in you; no more will the sound of a mill be heard in you; {\super\cf2\fs24 23}no more will the light of a lamp shine in you; no more will the voices of groom and bride be heard in you. Your merchants were the great men of the earth, for all the nations were deceived by your magical charms.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 24}Yes, and in her was to be found the blood of the prophets and of Christ\uc1\u8217*s people, and of all who have been put to death on the earth. 
\par}

