{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi0 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Then a voice said to me \uc1\u8220*Write \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Blessed are those who have been summoned to the marriage feast of the Lamb.\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8221* And the voice said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*These words of God are true.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}I prostrated myself at the feet of him who spoke to worship him, but he said to me \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*No! I am your fellow servant, and the fellow servant of your brothers and sisters who bear their testimony to Jesus. Worship God. For to bear testimony to Jesus needs the inspiration of the prophets.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Then I saw that heaven lay open. There appears a white horse; its rider is called \uc1\u8220*Faithful\uc1\u8221* and \uc1\u8220*True\uc1\u8221*; righteously does he judge and make war. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}His eyes are flaming fires; on his head there are many diadems, and he bears a name, written, which no one knows but himself; {\super\cf2\fs24 13}he has been clothed in a garment sprinkled with blood; and the name by which he is called is \uc1\u8220*The Word of God.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 14}The armies of heaven followed him, mounted on white horses and clothed in fine linen, white and pure. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}From his mouth comes a sharp sword, with which to smite the nations; and he will rule them with an iron rod. He treads the grapes in the press of the maddening wine of the wrath of Almighty God; {\super\cf2\fs24 16}and on his robe and on his thigh he has this name written \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*KING OF KINGS AND LORD OF LORDS.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Then I saw an angel standing on the sun. He cried in a loud voice to all the birds that fly in mid-heaven \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Gather and come to the great feast of God, {\super\cf2\fs24 18}to eat the flesh of kings, and the flesh of commanders, and the flesh of mighty men, and the flesh of horses and their riders, and the flesh of all free and enslaved, and of high and low.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 19}Then I saw the Beast and the kings of the earth and their armies, gathered together to fight with him who sat on the horse and with his army. {\super\cf2\fs24 20}The Beast was captured, and with him was taken the false prophet, who performed the marvels before the eyes of the Beast, with which he deceived those who had received the brand of the Beast and those who worshiped his image. Alive, they were thrown, both of them, into the lake of fire \uc1\u8211* of burning sulphur. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}The rest were killed by the sword which came out of the mouth of him who rode on the horse; and all the birds fed on their flesh. 
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 20}Then I saw an angel coming down from heaven, with the key of the bottomless pit and a great chain in his hand. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}He seized the Dragon, the primeval snake (who is the \uc1\u8220*devil\uc1\u8221* or \uc1\u8220*Satan\uc1\u8221*), and bound him in chains for a thousand years. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}He flung him into the bottomless pit and locked it, and set his seal on it; that he should not deceive the nations any more, until the thousand years were ended. After that he must be let loose for a while.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Then I saw thrones, and to those who took their seats on them authority was given to act as judges. And I saw the souls of those who had been beheaded because of the testimony to Jesus and because of the message of God, for they had refused to worship the Beast or its image, and had not received the brand on their foreheads and on their hands. They were restored to life, and they reigned with the Christ for a thousand years. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}(The rest of the dead were not restored to life until the thousand years were ended.) This is the first resurrection. {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Blessed and holy will he be who shares in that first resurrection. The second Death has no power over them; but they will be priests of God, and the Christ, and they will reign with him for the thousand years.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 7}When the thousand years are ended, Satan will be let loose from his prison, {\super\cf2\fs24 8}and he will come out to deceive the nations that live in the four corners of the earth \uc1\u8211* Gog and Magog. He will come to gather them together for battle; and their number will be as great as the sand on the sea-shore. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}They went up over the breadth of the whole earth, and surrounded the camp of Christ\uc1\u8217*s people and the city that he loves. Then fire fell from the heavens and consumed them; {\super\cf2\fs24 10}and the devil, their deceiver, was hurled into the lake of fire and sulphur, where the Beast and the false prophet already were, and they will be tortured day and night for ever and ever.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Then I saw a great white throne, and him who was seated on it. The earth and the heavens fled from his presence; no place was left for them. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}And I saw the dead, high and low, standing before the throne; and books were opened. Then another book was opened, the book of life; and the dead were judged, according to their actions, by what was written in the books. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}The sea gave up its dead, and Death and Hades gave up their dead; and they were judged, one by one, each according to his actions. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Then Death and Hades were hurled into the lake of fire. This is the Second Death \uc1\u8211* the lake of fire; {\super\cf2\fs24 15}and all whose names were not found written in the book of life were hurled into the lake of fire. 
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 The New Creation

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 21}Then I saw new heavens and a new earth. The former heavens and the former earth had passed away; and the sea has ceased to be. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}And I saw the Holy City, Jerusalem, descending new out of heaven from God, like a bride adorned in readiness for her husband. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}And I heard a loud voice from the throne, which said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*See! The tent of God is set up among people. God will live among them, and they will be his Peoples, and God himself will be among them, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}and he will wipe away all tears from their eyes. There will be no more death, nor will there be any more grief or crying or pain. The old order has passed away.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 5}And he who was seated on the throne said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*See, I make all things new!\uc1\u8221* And he said \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*Write this, for these words may be trusted and are true.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And he said to me \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8220*They are fulfilled. I am the Alpha and the Omega, the beginning and the End. To those who thirst I will give of the spring of the water of life, freely. {\super\cf2\fs24 7}Those who conquer will enter into possession of these things, and I will be their God, and they will be my children. {\super\cf2\fs24 8}But as for cowards, unbelievers, the degraded, murderers, the impure, sorcerers, idolaters, and all liars \uc1\u8211* their place will be in the burning lake of fire and sulphur. That is the Second Death.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 9}Then one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls, and were laden with the seven last curses, came and spoke to me. \uc1\u8220*Come here,\uc1\u8221* he said, \uc1\u8220*and I will show you the Bride, the Wife of the Lamb.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 10}He carried me away in a trance to a great high mountain, and showed me Jerusalem, the Holy City, descending out of heaven from God, filled with the glory of God. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Its brilliance was like a precious stone, like a jasper, transparent as crystal. {\super\cf2\fs24 12}It had a great high wall, in which were twelve gates; and at these gates there were twelve angels, and there were names inscribed on the gates, the names of the twelve tribes of the Israelites. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}There were three gates on the east, three gates on the north, three gates on the south, and three gates on the west. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}The wall of the city had twelve foundation stones, on which were the twelve names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}And the angel who was speaking to me had as a measure a gold rod, with which to measure the city and its gates and its wall. {\super\cf2\fs24 16}The city is square; the length and the breadth are the same. The angel measured with his rod; it was twelve hundred miles; its length, and breadth, and height are equal. {\super\cf2\fs24 17}Then he measured the wall; it was two hundred and eighty-eight feet, as people measure, that is as the angel measured. {\super\cf2\fs24 18}The material of the wall of the city was jasper, and the city was built of pure gold, which shone like clear glass. {\super\cf2\fs24 19}The foundations of the wall of the city were ornamented with every kind of precious stone. The first foundation stone was a jasper; the second a sapphire; the third a chalcedony; the fourth an emerald; {\super\cf2\fs24 20}the fifth a sardonyx; the sixth a carnelian; the seventh a chrysolite; the eighth a beryl; the ninth a topaz; the tenth a chrysoprase; the eleventh a hyacinth; and the twelfth an amethyst. {\super\cf2\fs24 21}The twelve gates were made of twelve pearls, each gate of one pearl. The street of the city was of pure gold, transparent as glass. {\super\cf2\fs24 22}And I saw no Temple there, for the Lord, our God, the Almighty, and the Lamb are its Temple. {\super\cf2\fs24 23}The city has no need of the sun or the moon to shine on it, for the glory of God illuminated it, and its Lamp was the Lamb. {\super\cf2\fs24 24}The nations walk by the light of it; and the kings of the earth bring their glory into it. {\super\cf2\fs24 25}Its gates will never be shut by day, and there will be no night there. {\super\cf2\fs24 26}And people will bring the glory and honour of the nations into it. {\super\cf2\fs24 27}Never will any unhallowed thing enter it, nor they whose life is shameful and false, but only those whose names have been written in the Lamb\uc1\u8217*s book of life.  {\cf1 22}And the angel showed me a river of the water of life, as clear as crystal, issuing from the throne of God and of the Lamb, {\super\cf2\fs24 2}in the middle of the street of the city. On each side of the river was a Tree of life which bore twelve kinds of fruit, yielding its fruit each month; and the leaves of the tree were for the healing of the nations. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Every thing that is accursed will cease to be. The throne of God and of the Lamb will be within it, and his servants will worship him; {\super\cf2\fs24 4}they will see his face, and his name will be on their foreheads. {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Night will cease to be. They have no need of the light of a lamp, nor have they the light of the sun; for the Lord God will be their light, and they will reign for ever and ever.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs36 Conclusion

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}Then the angel said to me \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*These words may be trusted and are true. The Lord, the God that inspires the prophets, sent his angel to show his servants what must quickly take place; {\super\cf2\fs24 7}and they said \uc1\u8220*I will come quickly.\uc1\u8221* Blessed will he be who lays to heart the words of the prophecy contained in this book.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}It was I, John, who heard and saw these things; and, when I heard and saw them, I prostrated myself in worship at the feet of the angel that showed them to me. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}But he said to me \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Forbear; I am your fellow servant, and the fellow servant of your fellow prophets, and of all who lay to heart the words in this book. Worship God.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}Then the angel said to me \uc1\u8211* \uc1\u8216*Do not keep secret the words of the prophecy contained in this book; for the time is near. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}Let the wrong-doer continue to do wrong; the filthy-minded continue to be filthy; the righteous continue to act righteously; and the holy-minded continue to be holy.\uc1\u8217* {\super\cf2\fs24 12}(\uc1\u8220*I will come quickly. I bring my rewards with me, to give to each what their actions deserve. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}I am the Alpha and the Omega, the First and the Last, the beginning and the End.\uc1\u8221*) {\super\cf2\fs24 14}Blessed will they be who wash their robes! They will have the right to approach the Tree of life, and may enter the city by the gates. {\super\cf2\fs24 15}Outside will be the filthy, the sorcerers, the impure, the murderers, the idolaters, and all who love the false and live it.
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8220*I, Jesus, sent my angel to bear testimony to you about these things before the churches. I am the Scion and the Offspring of David, the bright star of the Morning.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 17}\uc1\u8220*Come,\uc1\u8221* say the Spirit and the Bride; and all who hear, say \uc1\u8220*Come.\uc1\u8221* All who thirst, come; anyone who wants, take the water of life freely.
